om their errors and mistakes the wise and good learn wisdom for the future.','Plutarch','wisdom'),(175,'Where there is charity and wisdom, there is neither fear nor ignorance.','Francis of Assisi','wisdom'),(176,'Wisdom is knowing what to do next; virtue is doing it.','David Starr Jordan','wisdom'),(177,'Wisdom begins at the end.','Daniel Webster','wisdom'),(178,'The smallest deed is better than the greatest intention.','John Burroughs','wisdom'),(179,'Strong characters are brought out by change of situation, and gentle ones by permanence.','Jean Paul','wisdom'),(180,'Counsel woven into the fabric of real life is wisdom.','Walter Benjamin','wisdom'),(181,'It is much more difficult to measure nonperformance than performance.','Harold S. Geneen','wisdom'),(182,'Self-suggestion makes you master of yourself.','W. Clement Stone','wisdom'),(183,'Life is a travelling to the edge of knowledge, then a leap taken.','David Herbert Lawrence','wisdom'),(184,'Wisdom is always an overmatch for strength.','Phil Jackson','wisdom'),(185,'If you believe the doctors, nothing is wholesome; if you believe the theologians, nothing is innocent; if you believe the military, nothing is safe.','Lord Salisbury','wisdom'),(186,'Spectacular achievement is always preceded by unspectacular preparation.','Robert H. Schuller','wisdom'),(187,'Virtues are acquired through endeavor, which rests wholly upon yourself.','Sidney Lanier','wisdom'),(188,'Man\'s wisdom is his best friend; folly his worst enemy.','William Temple','wisdom'),(189,'The wisdom of the wise is an uncommon degree of common sense.','Dean Inge','wisdom'),(190,'It is wisdom in prosperity, when all is as thou wouldn\'t have it, to fear and suspect the worst.','Desiderius Erasmus','wisdom'),(191,'Every silver lining has a cloud.','Mary Kay Ash','wisdom'),(192,'Wise kings generally have wise counselors; and he must be a wise man himself who is capable of distinguishing one.','Diogenes','wisdom'),(193,'It is astonishing with how little wisd