r lost that is devoted to work.','Ralph Waldo Emerson','wisdom'),(209,'Raising children is an incredibly hard and risky business in which no cumulative wisdom is gained: each generation repeats the mistakes the previous one made.','Bill Cosby','wisdom'),(210,'Wisdom has its root in goodness, not goodness its root in wisdom.','Ralph Waldo Emerson','wisdom'),(211,'Perhaps religious conscience upsets the designs of those who feel that the highest wisdom and authority comes from government. But from the beginning, this nation trusted in God, not man. Religious liberty is the first freedom in our Constitution.','Mitt Romney','wisdom'),(212,'Start with God - the first step in learning is bowing down to God; only fools thumb their noses at such wisdom and learning.','King Solomon','wisdom'),(213,'In life, all good things come hard, but wisdom is the hardest to come by.','Lucille Ball','wisdom'),(214,'Excellence, then, is a state concerned with choice, lying in a mean, relative to us, this being determined by reason and in the way in which the man of practical wisdom would determine it.','Aristotle','wisdom'),(215,'Most of our pocket wisdom is conceived for the use of mediocre people, to discourage them from ambitious attempts, and generally console them in their mediocrity.','Robert Louis Stevenson','wisdom'),(216,'Wisdom comes alone through suffering.','Aeschylus','wisdom'),(217,'Cunning... is but the low mimic of wisdom.','Plato','wisdom'),(218,'I gave my beauty and my youth to men. I am going to give my wisdom and experience to animals.','Brigitte Bardot','wisdom'),(219,'We don\'t receive wisdom; we must discover it for ourselves after a journey that no one can take for us or spare us.','Marcel Proust','wisdom'),(220,'Knowledge which is divorced from justice, may be called cunning rather than wisdom.','Marcus Tullius Cicero','wisdom'),(221,'There are three classes of men; lovers of wisdom, lovers of honor, and lovers of gain.','Plato','wisdom'),(222,'A short saying often contains much wisdom.','Sophocles','wisdom'),(223,'To keep your secret is wisdom; but to expect others to keep it is folly.','Samuel Johnson','wisdom'),(224,'Through mutual understanding, sincerity and goodwill, and with great wisdom and broad views, the leaders on both sides should jointly initiate new opportunities for peace, stability, cooperation and mutual benefit.','Chen Shui-bian','wisdom'),(225,'Science is organized knowledge. Wisdom is organized life.','Immanuel Kant','wisdom'),(226,'War involves in its progress such a train of unforeseen circumstances that no human wisdom can calculate the end; it has but one thing certain, and that is to increase taxes.','Thomas Paine','wisdom'),(227,'The function of wisdom is to discriminate between good and evil.','Marcus Tullius Cicero','wisdom'),(228,'To know how to grow old is the master work of wisdom, and one of the most difficult chapters in the great art of living.','Herman Melville','wisdom'),(229,'We learn wisdom from failure much more than from success. We often discover what will do, by finding out what will not do; and probably he who never made a mistake never made a discovery.','Samuel Smiles','wisdom'),(230,'Wisdom allows nothing to be good that will not be so forever; no man to be happy but he that needs no other happiness than what he has within himself; no man to be great or powerful that is not master of himself.','Lucius Annaeus Seneca','wisdom'),(231,'The more tranquil a man becomes, the greater is his success, his influence, his power for good. Calmness of mind is one of the beautiful jewels of wisdom.','James Allen','wisdom'),(232,'Those who improve with age embrace the power of personal growth and personal achievement and begin to replace youth with wisdom, innocence with understanding, and lack of purpose with self-actualization.','Bo Bennett','wisdom'),(233,'In complete darkness we are all the same, it is only our knowledge and wisdom that separates us, don\'t let your eyes deceive you.','Janet Jackson','wisdom'),(234,'There is no pain equal to that which two lovers can inflict on one another. This should be made clear to all who contemplate such a union. The avoidance of this pain is the beginning of wisdom, for it is strong enough to contaminate the rest of our lives.','Cyril Connolly','wisdom'),(235,'Children also have artistic ability, and there is wisdom in there having it! The more helpless they are, the more instructive are the examples they furnish us; and they must be preserved free of corruption from an early age.','Paul Klee','wisdom'),(236,'If suffering brings wisdom, I would wish to be less wise.','William Butler Yeats','wisdom'),(237,'It is not wisdom but Authority that makes a law.','Thomas Hobbes','wisdom'),(238,'We have no words for speaking of wisdom to the stupid. He who understands the wise is wise already.','Georg C. Lichtenberg','wisdom'),(239,'Rightly defined philosophy is simply the love of wisdom.','Marcus Tullius Cicero','wisdom'),(240,'Wisdom alone is the science of other sciences.','Plato','wisdom'),(241,'Lord, bless me with the ability to achieve all that I can, and the wisdom to realize it doesn\'t all have to be by tomorrow!','William Eardley IV','wisdom'),(242,'Wisdom does not show itself so much in precept as in life - in firmness of mind and a mastery of appetite. It teaches us to do as well as to talk; and to make our words and actions all of a color.','Lucius Annaeus Seneca','wisdom'),(243,'Women always excel men in that sort of wisdom which comes from experience. To be a woman is in itself a terrible experience.','H. L. Mencken','wisdom'),(244,'What wisdom can you find that is greater than kindness?','Jean-Jacques Rousseau','wisdom'),(245,'Not engaging in ignorance is wisdom.','Bodhidharma','wisdom'),(246,'Gray hairs are signs of wisdom if you hold your tongue, speak and they are but hairs, as in the young.','Rabindranath Tagore','wisdom'),(247,'Silence is true wisdom\'s best reply.','Euripides','wisdom'),(248,'I do 