sdom, to know when it ought to be resisted, and when it be obeyed.','Nathaniel Hawthorne','wisdom'),(409,'He who is taught to live upon little owes more to his father\'s wisdom than he who has a great deal left him does to his father\'s care.','William Penn','wisdom'),(410,'I acknowledge the privilege of being alive in a human body at this moment, endowed with senses, memories, emotions, thoughts, and the space of mind in its wisdom aspect.','Alex Grey','wisdom'),(411,'It may almost be a question whether such wisdom as many of us have in our mature years has not come from the dying out of the power of temptation, rather than as the results of thought and resolution.','Anthony Trollope','wisdom'),(412,'Many people have their reputations as reporters and analysts because they are on television, batting around conventional wisdom. A lot of these people have never reported a story.','Bob Woodward','wisdom'),(413,'I\'m very accepting with my age. It\'s like notches on your belt: experience, wisdom, and a different kind of beauty. There comes a day when you\'ve become comfortable in your skin.','Zoe Saldana','wisdom'),(414,'In complete darkness, it is only knowledge and wisdom that separates us.','Janet Jackson','wisdom'),(415,'Vanity can easily overtake wisdom. It usually overtakes common sense.','Julian Casablancas','wisdom'),(416,'Mistakes are the usual bridge between inexperience and wisdom.','Phyllis Theroux','wisdom'),(417,'The truest greatness lies in being kind, the truest wisdom in a happy mind.','Ella Wheeler Wilcox','wisdom'),(418,'Now our founding fathers had the wisdom to know that social acceptance and popularity were fleeing, and that this country\'s principles needed to be rooted in strengths greater than the passions and the emotions of the times.','Chris Christie','wisdom'),(419,'One part of wisdom is knowing what you don\'t need anymore and letting it go.','Jane Fonda','wisdom'),(420,'I don\'t think I really have any wisdom. Stay out of trouble. Good luck. Stay away from women because they will burn you, haha.','Jason Aldean','wisdom'),(421,'Great wisdom is generous; petty wisdom is contentious. Great speech is impassioned, small speech cantankerous.','Zhuang Zi','wisdom'),(422,'No one ever found wisdom without also being a fool. Writers, alas, have to be fools in public, while the rest of the human race can cover its tracks.','Erica Jong','wisdom'),(423,'Logic is the beginning of wisdom, not the end.','Leonard Nimoy','wisdom'),(424,'If you have the guts to keep making mistakes, your wisdom and intelligence leap forward with huge momentum.','Holly Near','wisdom'),(425,'Silence at the proper season is wisdom, and better than any speech.','Plutarch','wisdom'),(426,'I always see where I didn\'t do things the right way. I only see the heavy lifting. That\'s a bit of my wisdom, if you want to call it that.','Vera Wang','wisdom'),(427,'As a parent and a citizen, I\'ll take a Bill Gates (or Warren Buffett) over Steve Jobs every time. If we must have billionaires, better they should ignore Jobs\'s example and instead embrace the morality and wisdom of the great industrialist-philanthropist Andrew Carnegie.','Eric Alterman','wisdom'),(428,'The wisdom of crowds works when the crowd is choosing the price of an ox, when there\'s a single numeric average. But if it\'s a design or something that matters, the decision is made by committee, and that\'s crap. You want people and groups who are able to think thoughts before they share.','Jaron Lanier','wisdom'),(429,'Of all our possessions, wisdom alone is imortal.','Isocrates','wisdom'),(430,'Humility is the only true wisdom by which we prepare our minds for all the possible changes of life.','George Arliss','wisdom'),(431,'Central banks don\'t have divine wisdom. They try to do the best analysis they can and must be prepared to stand or fall by the quality of that analysis.','Mary Kay Ash','wisdom'),(432,'I\'m married. My wife, Stella - a beautiful woman. She\'s brought a lot of 