d meaning of the book of Job, the best example of wisdom.','Paul Ricoeur','wisdom'),(459,'Wisdom finds its literary expression in wisdom literature.','Paul Ricoeur','wisdom'),(460,'Whether the aim is in heaven or on earth, wisdom or wealth, the essential condition of its pursuit and attainment is always security and order.','Johan Huizinga','wisdom'),(461,'Analysts may be correct that the presidential election won\'t primarily turn on entitlements reform, but by choosing Paul Ryan as his running mate, Mitt Romney can, contrary to conventional wisdom, make it a winning issue and lay the foundation for a reform mandate when he wins.','David Limbaugh','wisdom'),(462,'I covered my face because they had taken my wisdom teeth out.','Josh Brolin','wisdom'),(463,'No man is the wiser for his learning; it may administer matter to work in, or objects to work upon; but wit and wisdom are born with a man.','John Selden','wisdom'),(464,'One of the most beautiful passages of Rousseau is that in the sixth book of Confessions, where he describes the awakening in him of the literary sense. Of such wisdom, the poetic passion, the desire of beauty, the love of art for its own sake, has most.','Walter Pater','wisdom'),(465,'Wisdom too often never comes, and so one ought not to reject it merely because it comes late.','Felix Frankfurter','wisdom'),(466,'I left school at 16 but I wish I\'d gone to university - I think I would have studied English literature. I had a knack for that. But I don\'t think you have the kind of wisdom at 16 to make that decision.','Brendan Coyle','wisdom'),(467,'You know, it\'s sort of common wisdom among New York publishers that short story collections don\'t make money.','Chad Harbach','wisdom'),(468,'Wisdom and deep intelligence require an honest appreciation of mystery.','Thomas Moore','wisdom'),(469,'We all have within us a deep wisdom, but sometimes we don\'t know we have it.','Shakti Gawain','wisdom'),(470,'When I wrote Living in the Light, I wanted to share about how I live my own life and to encourage people to tap into their own inner wisdom.','Shakti Gawain','wisdom'),(471,'There is a universal, intelligent, life force that exists within everyone and everything. It resides within each one of use as a deep wisdom, an inner knowing. We can access this wonderful source of knowledge and wisdom through our intuition, an inner sense that tells us what feels right and true for us at any given moment.','Shakti Gawain','wisdom'),(472,'The all-seeing eye of God beheld our deplorable state; infinite pity touched the heart of the Father of mercies; and infinite wisdom laid the plan of our recovery.','David Brainerd','wisdom'),(473,'Now it is time to turn to an older wisdom that, while respecting material comfort and security as a basic right of all, also recognises that many of the most valuable things in life cannot be measured.','Michael D. Higgins','wisdom'),(474,'What I lack in energy, I have in wisdom.','Marcia Cross','wisdom'),(475,'Our bodies are at once the receiving and transmitting stations for life itself. It is the highest wisdom to recognize this fact and train our bodies to render them sensitive and responsive to nature. art and religion.','Ruth St. Denis','wisdom'),(476,'As you walk down the fairway of life you must smell the roses, for you only get to play one round.','Ben Hogan','wisdom'),(477,'Climb the mountains and get their good tidings.','John Muir','wisdom'),(478,'We should not judge people by their peak of excellence; but by the distance they have traveled from the point where they started.','Henry Ward Beecher','wisdom'),(479,'Honesty is the best policy.','Benjamin Franklin','wisdom'),(480,'Silence is a source of great strength.','Lao Tzu','wisdom'),(481,'A little knowledge that acts is worth infinitely more than much knowledge that is idle.','Khalil Gibran','wisdom'),(482,'A man begins cutting his wisdom teeth the first time he bites off more than he can chew.','Herb Caen','wisdom'),(483,'Knowing o