isdom.','Oprah Winfrey','wisdom'),(501,'I have learned throughout my life as a composer chiefly through my mistakes and pursuits of false assumptions, not by my exposure to founts of wisdom and knowledge.','Igor Stravinsky','wisdom'),(502,'I sought my father in the world of the black musician, because it contained wisdom, experience, sadness and loneliness. I was not ever interested in the music of boys. From my youngest years, I was interested in the music of men.','Eric Clapton','wisdom'),(503,'My government, you can be assured, will be less focused on personalities. It is about treating people with respect. I think complaining about the community not being able to see the wisdom of our ideas is the wrong approach.','Jay Weatherill','wisdom'),(504,'The greatest wisdom is to realize one\'s lack of it.','Constantin Stanislavski','wisdom'),(505,'God in His wisdom has decided that He will reward no works but His own.','Johannes Tauler','wisdom'),(506,'This society in which we live is radically changing. What previous generations saw as evil is now embraced as being good. It is a dangerous and slippery slope upon which we stand when we reject what Solomon called the beginning of wisdom - the fear of God.','Ray Comfort','wisdom'),(507,'The Divine of the Lord in heaven is love, for the reason that love is receptive of all things of heaven, such as peace, intelligence, wisdom and happiness.','Emanuel Swedenborg','wisdom'),(508,'I find that to be a fool as to worldly wisdom, and to commit my cause to God, not fearing to offend men, who take offence at the simplicity of truth, is the only way to remain unmoved at the sentiments of others.','John Woolman','wisdom'),(509,'However great an evil immorality may be, we must not forget that it is not without its beneficial consequences. It is only through extremes that men can arrive at the middle path of wisdom and virtue.','Wilhelm von Humboldt','wisdom'),(510,'Has fortune dealt you some bad cards. Then let wisdom make you a good gamester.','Francis Quarles','wisdom'),(511,'It is astonishing what force, purity, and wisdom it requires for a human being to keep clear of falsehoods.','Margaret Fuller','wisdom'),(512,'I\'ve always shied away from conventional wisdom, though I know the power of it.','Peter Jennings','wisdom'),(513,'To light one candle to God and another to the Devil is the principle of wisdom.','Jose Bergamin','wisdom'),(514,'My mom calls me an older soul because, growing up, she taught me stuff real early. Now I spend most of my time chasing wisdom, chasing understanding.','Ray Lewis','wisdom'),(515,'They whom truth and wisdom lead, can gather honey from a weed.','William Cowper','wisdom'),(516,'Wisdom consists of the anticipation of consequences.','Norman Cousins','wisdom'),(517,'Age is a terrible avenger. The lessons of life give you so much to work with, but by the time you\'ve got all this great wisdom, you don\'t get to be young anymore.','Elizabeth Wurtzel','wisdom'),(518,'The wisdom acquired with the passage of time is a useless gift unless you share it.','Esther Williams','wisdom'),(519,'A wholesome oblivion of one\'s neighbours is the beginning of wisdom.','Richard Le Gallienne','wisdom'),(520,'Great wisdom is generous; petty wisdom is contentious.','Zhuangzi','wisdom'),(521,'Even when you have doubts, take that step. Take chances. Mistakes are never a failure - they can be turned into wisdom.','Cat Cora','wisdom'),(522,'Age does not bring you wisdom, age brings you wrinkles.','Estelle Getty','wisdom'),(523,'Authority without wisdom is like a heavy ax without an edge, fitter to bruise than polish.','Anne Bradstreet','wisdom'),(524,'We learned in World War II that no single nation holds a monopoly on wisdom, morality or right to power, but that we must fight for the weak and promote democracy.','Joe Baca','wisdom'),(525,'Clinton is a big personality who has led a big life, and for some of the media conventional wisdom to boil it down to a view that \'all people are really interested in\' are a few moments of madness in the Oval Office gets him, the importance of the presidency, and the significance of his life, all wrong.','Alastair Campbell','wisdom'),(526,'Theology in general seems to me a substitution of human ingenuity for divine wisdom.','Julia Ward Howe','wisdom'),(527,'There is no knowledge, no light, no wisdom that you are in possession of, but what you have received it from some source.','Brigham Young','wisdom'),(528,'Conventional wisdom notwithstanding, there is no reason either in football or in poetry why the two should not meet in a man\'s life if he has the weight and cares about the words.','Archibald MacLeish','wisdom'),(529,'Doubt the conventional wisdom unless you can verify it with reason and experiment.','Steve Albini','wisdom'),(530,'He read his mind. He\'s a strange sort of man, isn\'t he? It\'s not just the advice and the wisdom that he has.','Omar Sharif','wisdom'),(531,'You want people walking away from the conversation with some kernel of wisdom or some kind of impact.','Harry Dean Stanton','wisdom'),(532,'All human wisdom works and has worries and grief as reward.','Johann Georg Hamann','wisdom'),(533,'To keep your secret is wisdom; to expect others to keep it is folly.','William Samuel Johnson','wisdom'),(534,'Nobility of spirit has more to do with simplicity than ostentation, wisdom rather than wealth, commitment rather than ambition.','Riccardo Muti','wisdom'),(535,'It is not from reason that justice springs, but goodness is born of wisdom.','Maurice Maeterlinck','wisdom'),(536,'For the subtlest folly proceeds from the subtlest wisdom.','John Webster','wisdom'),(537,'To know one\'s self is wisdom, but not to know one\'s neighbors is genius.','Minna Antrim','wisdom'),(538,'If they can prove that I am wrong by that time, I will give it up to their wisdom, but not after to any one\'s judgment, till I see the end of another year; for the Lord will begin with a new century; and I will see what he will do, before I will hearken to any man\'s judgment.','Joanna Southcott','wisdom'),(539,'Our experience is composed rather of illusions that of wisdom acquired.','Joseph Roux','wisdom'),(540,'The beginning of wisdom is to desire it.','Solomon Ibn Gabirol','wisdom'),(541,'It is not white hair that engenders wisdom.','Menander','wisdom'),(542,'The seven wise men of Greece, so famous for their wisdom all the world over, acquired all that fame, each of them, by a single sentence consisting of two or three words.','Robert South','wisdom'),(543,'Learning how to get in tune with your field of energy and understand how to create your energy, expand that energy, and move that energy through your body. Coming back to your center, and approaching life from that center-to-line place... That to me gave me strength and understanding and hopefully wisdom to solve life\'s problems and challenges.','Erin Gray','wisdom'),(544,'Words of wisdom are spoken by children at least as often as scientists.','James Newman','wisdom'),(545,'Beauty, the eternal Spouse of the Wisdom of God and Angel of his Presence thru\' all creation.','Robert Bridges','wisdom'),(546,'Wisdom is not acquired save as the result of investigation.','Sara Teasdale','wisdom'),(547,'What is all wisdom save a collection of platitudes?','Norman Douglas','wisdom'),(548,'The sublimity of wisdom is to do those things living, which are to be desired when dying.','Norman Douglas','wisdom'),(549,'This age thinks better of a gilded fool Than of a threadbare saint in wisdom\'s school.','Thomas Dekker','wisdom'),(550,'The \'wisdom of the crowds\' is the most ridiculous statement I\'ve heard in my life. Crowds are dumb.','Drew Curtis','wisdom'),(551,'I\'m not a money manager, but I can tell you what the conventional wisdom is. The younger you are, the more risk you can take on.','Maria Bartiromo','wisdom'),(552,'I have tried at every point to seek God\'s wisdom on the decisions I made, and I made it my business to speak up on behalf of 