ave talked about first-hand experience of the world as an important part of the path to wisdom, to enlightenment.','Bell Hooks','wisdom'),(586,'The thing that we possess, that machines don\'t, is the ability to exhibit wisdom.','Herbie Hancock','wisdom'),(587,'Without wisdom, the future has no meaning, no valuable purpose.','Herbie Hancock','wisdom'),(588,'You can practice to attain knowledge, but you can\'t practice to attain wisdom.','Herbie Hancock','wisdom'),(589,'The perceived wisdom is that people do not go in large numbers to black-and-white movies anymore - which is a great shame, but I\'d love to make a black-and-white movie one day.','Sam Mendes','wisdom'),(590,'As I visited the various neighborhoods in the campaign, I learned fast that it\'s a mistake to think that all of the wisdom and possible solutions to our problems are available only in this building.','Jane Byrne','wisdom'),(591,'I am thinking of taking a fifth wife. Why not? Solomon had a thousand wives and he is a synonym for wisdom.','John Barrymore','wisdom'),(592,'Spend time reflecting on your emotional and physical existence and how that applies to the voice. You have to apply that wisdom and experience when you sing - it\'s what comes through.','K. D. Lang','wisdom'),(593,'I\'m someone who\'s done the opposite of whatever the received wisdom is, to keep your career going into your 50s.','Elizabeth McGovern','wisdom'),(594,'I feel increasingly like age is very irrelevant. Quite often, cynicism is confused with wisdom, and my scorn is confused with a knowing, which I don\'t have.','Laura Marling','wisdom'),(595,'Wisdom is the knowledge of good and evil, not the strength to choose between the two.','John Cheever','wisdom'),(596,'There is as much wisdom in listening as there is in speaking - and that goes for all relationships, not just romantic ones.','Daniel Dae Kim','wisdom'),(597,'Lessons of wisdom have the most power over us when they capture the heart through the groundwork of a story, which engages the passions.','Laurence Sterne','wisdom'),(598,'Sciences may be learned by rote, but wisdom not.','Laurence Sterne','wisdom'),(599,'Wisdom oft times consists of knowing what to do next.','Herbert Hoover','wisdom'),(600,'Wisdom consists not so much in knowing what to do in the ultimate as knowing what to do next.','Herbert Hoover','wisdom'),(601,'We live in a culture that doesn\'t acknowledge or validate human intuition and doesn\'t encourage us to rely on our intuitive wisdom.','Shakti Gawain','wisdom'),(602,'A man of strength and wisdom, John Paul became an inspiration to generations of both Catholics and non-Catholics throughout the world by encouraging freedom, promoting peace and respecting all faiths.','Greg Walden','wisdom'),(603,'Ask Elizabeth is a community of voices, it\'s not me standing on a podium telling people how to run their lives, it\'s girls helping each other sharing their wisdom and advice and I create a space for them to do it.','Elizabeth Berkley','wisdom'),(604,'I have no agenda except to be funny. Neither I or the writers profess to offer any worldly wisdom.','Julia Louis-Dreyfus','wisdom'),(605,'Surely, God on high has not refused to give us enough wisdom to find ways to bring us an improvement in relations between the two great nations on earth.','Mikhail Gorbachev','wisdom'),(606,'I have no wisdom to share on dating.','Rachel Dratch','wisdom'),(607,'Practical wisdom is only to be learned in the school of experience. Precepts and instruction are useful so far as they go, but, without the discipline of real life, they remain of the nature of theory only.','Samuel Smiles','wisdom'),(608,'The experience gathered from books, though often valuable, is but the nature of learning; whereas the experience gained from actual life is one of the nature of wisdom.','Samuel Smiles','wisdom'),(609,'The wisdom of the wise, and the experience of ages, may be preserved by quotation.','Isaac D\'Israeli','wisdom'),(610,'If God had sufficient wisdom and power to construct such a beautiful world as this, then we must admit that his wisdom and power are immeasurably greater than that of man, and hence he is qualified to reign as king.','Orson Pratt','wisdom'),(611,'The first point of wisdom is to discern that which is false; the second, to know that which is true.','Lactantius','wisdom'),(612,'Never accept ultimatums, conventional wisdom, or absolutes.','Christopher Reeve','wisdom'),(613,'I do interviews because it\'s a chance to be myself. I sometimes wonder what I could have to say that would be of any interest. I don\'t have any great wisdom.','Parker Stevenson','wisdom'),(614,'Come, come, leave business to idlers, and wisdom to fools: they have need of \'em: wit be my faculty, and pleasure my occupation, and let father Time shake his glass.','William Congreve','wisdom'),(615,'The more I work with the body, keeping my assumptions in a temporary state of reservation, the more I appreciate and sympathize with a given disease. The body no longer appears as a sick or irrational demon, but as a process with its own inner logic and wisdom.','George MacDonald','wisdom'),(616,'We all admire the wisdom of people who come to us for advice.','Arthur Helps','wisdom'),(617,'A great memory is never made synonymous with wisdom, any more than a dictionary would be called a treatise.','John Henry Newman','wisdom'),(618,'True wisdom listens more, talks less and can get along with all types of people.','Kiana Tom','wisdom'),(619,'And when the world is created, it is created in such a way that those eternal objects of God\'s loving wisdom become actualities - interacting with one another, relating to God in the finite realm.','Rowan D. Williams','wisdom'),(620,'This fear of the Lord is indeed the beginning of wisdom. This consciousness of sin is the straight pathway to heaven.','Joseph Barber Lightfoot','wisdom'),(621,'After a gig I always head back to the hotel, remembering granny\'s words of wisdom. I cancel the late-night pizza and watch the Jonathan Ross show instead.','Jimmy Carr','wisdom'),(622,'Conventional wisdom holds that setting a timetable for getting American troops out of Iraq would be a mistake.','Nick Clooney','wisdom'),(623,'If an idea is indeed sensible, it will eventually become just part of the accepted wisdom.','Nigel Farage','wisdom'),(624,'There\'s the conventional wisdom, of which I have none, where you get a record deal, you get a publicist, you get a campaign, and you do the tour, but none of that adds up to things like nuance and subtlety and dynamic.','Chris Robinson','wisdom'),(625,'To suppose more than one supreme Source of infinite wisdom, power, and all perfections, is to assert that there is no supreme Being in existence.','Adam Clarke','wisdom'),(626,'Knowledge is the consequence of time, and multitude of days are fittest to teach wisdom.','Jeremy Collier','wisdom'),(627,'During the long process of history, by relying on our own diligence, courage and wisdom, Chinese people have opened up a good and beautiful home where all ethnic groups live in harmony and fostered an excellent culture that never fades.','Xi Jinping','wisdom'),(628,'Follow the wisdom of the great actor, James Cagney, you hit your mark, you look the other guy in the eye, and you tell the truth.','Larry Merchant','wisdom'),(629,'Wisdom alone is true ambition\'s aim, wisdom the source of virtue, and of fame, obtained with labour, for mankind employed, and then, when most you share it, best enjoyed.','William Whitehead','wisdom'),(630,'But the law of God came from heaven indeed. God wrote it with his finger, it is the fountain of all wisdom, and therefore shall it continue for ever, and never have an end.','John Jewel','wisdom'),(631,'I see a wiser person than when I was younger: having babies, and passing 30, were the turning points. What women in their 40s - I am 39 - lack in gorgeousness, they make up for in wisdom. I love ageing, despite the drawbacks - thinner, drier skin.','Thandie Newton','wisdom'),(632,'Wisdom is a kind of knowledge. It is knowledge of the nature, career, and consequences of human values.','Sidney Hook','wisdom'),(633,'Rich people without wisdom and learning are but sheep with golden fleeces.','Solon','wisdom'),(634,'To comprehend the Wisdom of this Injunction the better, and explain the Duty before us, it should be considered, that Government is the only Means by which human Happiness can be attained.','Charles Inglis','wisdom'),(635,'Be there a will, and wisdom finds a way.','George Crabbe','wisdom'),(636,'They are few in the midst of an overwhelming mass of brute force, and their submission is wisdom; but for a nation like England to submit to be robbed by any invader who chooses to visit her shores seemed to me to be nonsense.','George Combe','wisdom'),(637,'I have studied many philosophers and many cats. The wisdom of cats is infinitely superior.','Hippolyte Taine','wisdom'),(638,'Old myths, old gods, old heroes have never died. They are only sleeping at the bottom of our mind, waiting for our call. We have need for them. They represent the wisdom of our race.','Stanley Kunitz','wisdom'),(639,'The study of history is the beginning of political wisdom.','Jean Bodin','wisdom'),(640,'I am not one who was born in the custody of wisdom; I am one who is fond of olden times and intense in quest of the sacred knowing of the ancients.','Gustave Courbet','wisdom'),(641,'Even by common wisdom, there seem to be both people and objects in my dream that are outside myself, but clearly they were created in myself and are part of me, they are mental constructs in my own brain.','Ray Kurzweil','wisdom'),(642,'Memory is not wisdom; idiots can by rote repeat volumes. Yet what is wisdom without memory?','Martin Farquhar Tupper','wisdom'),(643,'I continue to believe, contrary to the given wisdom, that it\'s more interesting to have an album - or, indeed, an individual song - which has variety rather than homogeneity.','Peter Hammill','wisdom'),