ndulge in homespun wisdom here before so distinguished an assembly, especially as I am to be followed by a representative of science.','Knut Hamsun','wisdom'),(656,'I\'ve led a school whose faculty and students examine and discuss and debate every aspect of our law and legal system. And what I\'ve learned most is that no one has a monopoly on truth or wisdom. I\'ve learned that we make progress by listening to each other, across every apparent political or ideological divide.','Elena Kagan','wisdom'),(657,'After all my possessions had been burned, God gave me the wisdom to return to Jerusalem.','Shmuel Y. Agnon','wisdom'),(658,'The key to wisdom is knowing all the right questions.','John A. Simone, Sr.','wisdom'),(659,'Preconceived notions are the locks on the door to wisdom.','Merry Browne','wisdom'),(660,'Pessimism is only the name that men of weak nerves give to wisdom.','Bernard De Voto','wisdom'),(661,'We thought, because we had power, we had wisdom.','Stephen Vincent Benet','wisdom'),(662,'After the knowledge of, and obedience to, the will of God, the next aim must be to know something of His attributes of wisdom, power, and goodness as evidenced by His handiwork.','James Prescott Joule','wisdom'),(663,'Much of the wisdom of one age, is the folly of the next.','Charles Simmons','wisdom'),(664,'Wisdom is keeping a sense of fallibility of all our views and opinions.','Gerald Brenan','wisdom'),(665,'They see me as being this Super Mom on TV who also can more than handle a difficult husband, and they assume I\'m going to be just full of wisdom as a mother and wife myself.','Patricia Richardson','wisdom'),(666,'Now all the knowledge and wisdom that is in creatures, whether angels or men, is nothing else but a participation of that one eternal, immutable and increased wisdom of God.','Ralph Cudworth','wisdom'),(667,'Remembering is painful, it\'s difficult, but it can be inspiring and it can give wisdom.','Paul Greengrass','wisdom'),(668,'Even wisdom has to yield to 