e out how to tackle abuse.','Tori Amos','technology'),(811,'Like all technology, social media is neutral but is best put to work in the service of building a better world.','Simon Mainwaring','technology'),(812,'Non-profits must become deeply engaged in the ways that their donor communities are using social technology.','Simon Mainwaring','technology'),(813,'Technology is teaching us to be human again.','Simon Mainwaring','technology'),(814,'Find the human in the technology. The currency marketers trade in has not changed even if the methods have. Emotion is what we exchange.','Simon Mainwaring','technology'),(815,'Social media is not about the exploitation of technology but service to community.','Simon Mainwaring','technology'),(816,'The creative destruction that social media is currently unleashing will change more than technology or the leader board of the Fortune 100. It is driving a qualitative shift in the nature of relationships between brands and their customers.','Simon Mainwaring','technology'),(817,'Social technology gives leaders a vital new platform with which to connect their companies to the myriad stakeholders who have an interest in their well being.','Simon Mainwaring','technology'),(818,'Refuse to accept the belief that your professional relevance, career success or financial security turns on the next update on the latest technology. Sometimes it\'s good to put the paddle down and just let the canoe glide.','Simon Mainwaring','technology'),(819,'Not since the digital revolution in the early \'90s has technology placed such a comprehensive burden on business, employees and individuals to reinvent their business plans, services and products, and themselves to keep pace with the changing marketplace.','Simon Mainwaring','technology'),(820,'Let\'s hope brands recognize that the true power of this technology is not its reach but its ability to communicate substance that adds meaning to our lives. Otherwise, brands will be investing in technology that