rkness with humor... I\'m not an extremely suicidal or sad person.','Peter Steele','sad'),(2576,'You have to sound sad first of all, then maybe later you can sound good.','Steve Lacy','sad'),(2577,'In Mississippi, you don\'t admit that you\'re gay. It\'s just an awkward thing down South, which is sad.','Lance Bass','sad'),(2578,'Everything takes me longer than I expect. It\'s the sad truth about life.','Donna Tartt','sad'),(2579,'I often feel like I have this spirit living inside of me, always dressing in like short mini skirts... but then I start to discover myself. So there are eight spirits, mischievous ones, sad ones, handsome ones, wise ones, and crazy ones.','Bai Ling','sad'),(2580,'We tell them that we believe it will be beautiful because that is our specialty, we only create joy and beauty. We have never done a sad work. Through the drawings, we hope a majority will be able to visualize it.','Christo','sad'),(2581,'It\'s so sad: anything that has to do with God, people want to dispel.','Sylvia Browne','sad'),(2582,'My father comes from a generation of film that actors my age don\'t even know about, which is really sad.','Amber Tamblyn','sad'),(2583,'When I look back at those pictures of my mother performing - and listen to her recordings - it makes me sad to think that all of that joy she found in her work came to an end. I wish she hadn\'t had to make that sacrifice, even if it was for the benefit of my father and siblings and me.','Marlo Thomas','sad'),(2584,'I\'m not a very serious person. You know how they say that clowns are very funny in public and are really sad at home? I\'m really kind of stupid at home and more serious in public.','Roland Joffe','sad'),(2585,'Sad Patience, too near neighbour to despair.','Matthew Arnold','sad'),(2586,'The sad thing about any business I suppose, but in mine you see it particularly, is that you\'re always asked to do what you\'ve already done.','Jeremy Irons','sad'),(2587,'But now Americans, they felt a sense of peac