en absolutely fantastic to have worked in the 50\'s when you had all of the great Broadway composers and when West Side Story didn\'t win the Tony Award.','Andrew Lloyd Webber','sad'),(2598,'I wrote the song For A Dancer for a friend of mine who died in a fire. He was in the sauna in a house that burned down, so he had no idea anything was going on. It was very sad.','Jackson Browne','sad'),(2599,'Someone once accused me of being like Eliot Ness. I sad no sir, I\'m not E.N., but I can promise you that I\'m not Al Capone!','Robert Stack','sad'),(2600,'I enjoyed in every way my 12 years of playing Archie, and I wasn\'t personally sad about finishing a long job.','Carroll O\'Connor','sad'),(2601,'Lately, I\'ve been a little sad that I\'m not a gay man.','Gina Gershon','sad'),(2602,'I know for works for me - those wonderful sad love songs.','Toni Braxton','sad'),(2603,'In a sad twist of fate, the bill to reauthorize the Patriot Act was debated on the floor of the House of Representatives the same day that terrorists struck again.','Jim Sensenbrenner','sad'),(2604,'I have a stepladder. It\'s a very nice stepladder but it\'s sad that I never knew my real ladder.','Craig Charles','sad'),(2605,'I\'ve grown as a person. The dynamics on this set are very demanding because we work a lot of hours, it\'s very sad material, so there\'s always someone upset because it\'s really heavy stuff.','Elisabeth Rohm','sad'),(2606,'The South is very beautiful but its beauty makes one sad because the lives that people live here, and have lived here, are so ugly.','James Baldwin','sad'),(2607,'It\'s fun to sing sad songs. And it\'s fun to listen to sad songs. Enjoyable. Satisfying. Something.','Richard Thompson','sad'),(2608,'That\'s what so sad about a lot of modern music, in my opinion, so many young bands never stay around long enough to fulfill their ultimate promise. They only get halfway there or a quarter of the way there.','Alan Vega','sad'),(2609,'It can be really powerful to write something when you\'re sad.','Kathryn Stockett','sad'),(2610,'If you don\'t physically age gracefully, it\'s a bit sad. I think Steven Tyler can get away anything, because he still looks like he did in \'73. Especially from row Z backwards in an arena. As long as the Stones keep their hair and don\'t get fat they\'ll get away with the wrinkles.','Joe Elliott','sad'),(2611,'I\'m proud of my invention, but I\'m sad that it is used by terrorists.','Mikhail Kalashnikov','sad'),(2612,'But I now entered on my fifteenth year - a sad epoch in the life of a slave girl. My master began to whisper foul words in my ear. Young as I was, I could not remain ignorant of their import.','Harriet Ann Jacobs','sad'),(2613,'Since I had the baby I can\'t tolerate anything violent or sad, I saw the Matrix and I had my eyes closed through a lot of it, though I didn\'t need to. I would peek, and then think, oh OK, I can see that.','Lisa Kudrow','sad'),(2614,'What I am sad about is that there is now, in America, no equivalent to the art circuit.','Richard Attenborough','sad'),(2615,'The sad fact is that the same terrorist scenarios, if they occurred in five different States, there could be five different sets of responses to the American people. We need, at a minimum, a level of coordination on communicating threats to the public.','Vito Fossella','sad'),(2616,'If you have ever been in a real tragic or sad situation, the words that come out are hopelessly inadequate and kind of cliched.','Erika Slezak','sad'),(2617,'I know that some endeavor to throw the mantle of romance over the subject and treat woman like some ideal existence, not liable to the ills of life. Let those deal in fancy who have nothing better to deal in; we have to do with sober, sad realities, with stubborn facts.','Ernestine Rose','sad'),(2618,'Of these years nought remains in memory but the sad feeling that we have advanced and only grown older.','Max Muller','sad'),(2619,'His death was the first time that Ed Wynn ever made anyone sad.','Red Skelton','sad'),(2620,'They\'re not willing to admit that I\'ve also shed blood and tears and often paid dearly for my success. This makes me feel extremely sad.','Zhang Ziyi','sad'),(2621,'I love playing football, being out on the pitch with a ball, and I will be a little sad when that ends.','Dennis Bergkamp','sad'),(2622,'I would be sad if it ended now. It\'s been the best job I\'ve had by a long shot, especially creatively because the writing is so good. Every week I get the script and I laugh out loud and get excited for the different stuff we get to do.','Sarah Chalke','sad'),(2623,'It\'s very simple, I just tell my sad story, and people weep.','Corazon Aquino','sad'),(2624,'I am sure that the sad days and happenings were rare, and that I lived the joyous and careless life of other children; but just because the happy days were so habitual to me they made no impression upon my mind, and I can no longer recall them.','Pierre Loti','sad'),(2625,'I\'ve been looking forward to doing an album, but it\'s really sad to see how many doors have been closed because of the gay thing. I thought it was about the music.','Jai Rodriguez','sad'),(2626,'I think he Oswald felt he was a failure and for the United States and for President Kennedy and all of us. He knew he was a failure at everything he tried, frustrated, with a very sad life, but he was a Marxist.','John Sherman Cooper','sad'),(2627,'When I was in Paris, all of the German refugees began to flow in and it was a very sad time.','Elliott Carter','sad'),(2628,'It is easy enough to praise men for the courage of their convictions. I wish I could teach the sad young of this mealy generation the courage of their confusions.','John Ciardi','sad'),(2629,'My lasting impression of Truman Capote is that he was a terribly gentle, terribly sensitive, and terribly sad man.','Alvin Ailey','sad'),(2630,'It always makes me sad when I think of how I saw Wagner wasting his vitality, not only by singing their parts