ding spring water.','Brad Delson','sad'),(2640,'It\'s astonishing what some women will put up with just to have a warm body. Some of the brightest women I know are just obsessed with that search. It\'s very sad.','Judith Rossner','sad'),(2641,'I had a vocal coach. It\'s a sad thing, but I had to hire someone so that I could get my Australian accent back.','Anthony LaPaglia','sad'),(2642,'Since it\'s based on my parents, it\'s more emotionally close to me than some of my more surreal plays. And then I like the balance of the comic and the sad. It should play as funny, but you should care about the characters and feel sad for them.','Christopher Durang','sad'),(2643,'Bob summed it up best when he was on his knees at the end of the night saying, \'Don\'t trust in Guided By Voices.\' You were there; was the show awful or something? I know it was sloppy, but they\'re not really that tight anyway, but was it embarrassing, was it sad?','Kim Deal','sad'),(2644,'I love the script and I just thought it was a great role. Like I say, it\'s like this - the script is like this sad, funny, desperate love song to the lost American man.','Oliver Platt','sad'),(2645,'It\'s really sad for me that in the United States the Latino community is losing its culture and language, especially among kids born here - a lot of them can\'t even speak our language.','Romeo Santos','sad'),(2646,'It\'s the sad thing about entertainment, it\'s not always about who is the best.','Jake Roberts','sad'),(2647,'I\'m certainly no victim in this. I don\'t want to come off as a sad sack; I pissed a lot of people off.','Harry Anderson','sad'),(2648,'Why do we capital-N Nerds love Mars so much? Because it\'s beautiful, it\'s tough, it\'s buried in our mythic, childhood memories. It\'s covered with human triumphs but also with sad stories of failure.','Greg Bear','sad'),(2649,'It always made me sad that there were kids who didn\'t have homes.','Lauren Holly','sad'),(2650,'I think it\'s sad that movies and televi