 crowds, but our own hearts are the sole confidants of our sorrows.','Edward G. Bulwer-Lytton','sad'),(2754,'Those who gave away their wings are sad not to see them fly.','Antonio Porchia','sad'),(2755,'Actually, the moment of victory is wonderful, but also sad. It means that your trip is ended.','Bill Toomey','sad'),(2756,'Every human walks around with a certain kind of sadness. They may not wear it on their sleeves, but it\'s there if you look deep.','Taraji P. Henson','sad'),(2757,'Nobody understands another\'s sorrow, and nobody another\'s joy.','Franz Schubert','sad'),(2758,'First, accept sadness. Realize that without losing, winning isn\'t so great.','Alyssa Milano','sad'),(2759,'I had sadness for breakfast.','Andy Milonakis','sad'),(2760,'Red is the ultimate cure for sadness.','Bill Blass','sad'),(2761,'They say it\'s better to bury your sadness in a graveyard or garden that waits for the spring to wake from its sleep and burst into green.','Conor Oberst','sad'),(2762,'Sadness is also a kind of defence.','Ivo Andric','sad'),(2763,'One should either be sad or joyful. Contentment is a warm sty for eaters and sleepers.','Eugene O\'Neill','sad'),(2764,'You have to let it all hang out, let go of the ideas that were more comfortable and embrace some of the sadness in your life.','Madeleine Peyroux','sad'),(2765,'Everything\'s complicated, even those things that seem flat in their bleakness or sadness.','Nick Hornby','sad'),(2766,'The excursion is the same when you go looking for your sorrow as when you go looking for your joy.','Eudora Welty','sad'),(2767,'Art is the most beautiful deception of all. And although people try to incorporate the everyday events of life in it, we must hope that it will remain a deception lest it become a utilitarian thing, sad as a factory.','Claude Debussy','sad'),(2768,'Proud people breed sad sorrows for themselves.','Emily Bronte','sad'),(2769,'He is a hard man who is only just, and a sad one who is only wise.','Voltaire','sad'),(2770,'It\'s nice to be with someone, but I don\'t think you need to be in a relationship to feel complete. That would be really sad.','Kristin Davis','sad'),(2771,'Falling in love is awesome, but I\'m never drawn to happy songs per se, so whenever you sit down to write a heartbreak song and you\'re happily in love, it\'s like, \'OK, now I have to go back to a sad place to get something good.\'','Miranda Lambert','sad'),(2772,'I\'m sad to report that in the past few years, ever since uncertainty became our insistent 21st century companion, leadership has taken a great leap backwards to the familiar territory of command and control.','Margaret J. Wheatley','sad'),(2773,'It is a sad fact about our culture that a poet can earn much more money writing or talking about his art than he can by practicing it.','W. H. Auden','sad'),(2774,'The Indian Summer of life should be a little sunny and a little sad, like the season, and infinite in wealth and depth of tone, but never hustled.','Henry Adams','sad'),(2775,'I would not know how I am supposed to feel about many stories if not for the fact that the TV news personalities make sad faces for sad stories and happy faces for happy stories.','Dave Barry','sad'),(2776,'It is a sad thing when men have neither the wit to speak well nor the judgment to hold their tongues.','Jean de la Bruyere','sad'),(2777,'All pictures are unnatural. All pictures are sad because they\'re about dead people. Paintings you don\'t think of in a special time or with a specific event. With photos I always think I\'m looking at something dead.','David Bailey','sad'),(2778,'He who is not just is severe, he who is not wise is sad.','Voltaire','sad'),(2779,'The display of grief makes more demands than grief itself. How few men are sad in their own company.','Lucius Annaeus Seneca','sad'),(2780,'It\'s sad, actually, because my anxiety keeps me from enjoying things as much as I should at this age.','Amanda Seyfried','sad'),(2781,'But it\'s a journey and the sad thing is you only learn from experience, so as much as someone can tell you things, you have to go out there and make your own mistakes in order to learn.','Emma Watson','sad'),(2782,'If you don\'t know about pain and trouble, you\'re in sad shape. They make you appreciate life.','Evel Knievel','sad'),(2783,'There\'s no excuse to be bored. Sad, yes. Angry, yes. Depressed, yes. Crazy, yes. But there\'s no excuse for boredom, ever.','Viggo Mortensen','sad'),(2784,'Sometimes I wonder if suicides aren\'t in fact sad guardians of the meaning of life.','Vaclav Havel','sad'),(2785,'A sad fact of life lately at the Museum of Modern Art is that when it comes to group shows of contemporary painting from the collection, the bar has been set pretty low.','Jerry Saltz','sad'),(2786,'Among the many reasons assignable for the sad decay of true Christianity, perhaps the neglecting to assemble ourselves together, in religious societies, may not be one of the least.','George Whitefield','sad'),(2787,'I think you have to know how you feel when you\'re sad and it\'s healthy to mourn if a relationship ends.','Leighton Meester','sad'),(2788,'Better by far you should forget and smile than that you should remember and be sad.','Christina G. Rossetti','sad'),(2789,'It\'s sad, something coming to an end. It cracks you open, in a way - cracks you open to feeling.','Jennifer Aniston','sad'),(2790,'Everybody has a right to like or dislike anything or anyone. From a flower to a flavor to a book or a composition but it is very sad that in our country we actually fight over such things in an unseemly manner.','Ravi Shankar','sad'),(2791,'When I did the film Generations, in which the character died, I felt like a guest for the first time. That made me very sad.','William Shatner','sad'),(2792,'Good humor is the health of the soul, sadness is its poison.','Lord Chesterfield','sad'),(2793,'It\'s a sad man my friend who\'s livin\' in his own skin and can\'t stand the company.','Bruce Springsteen','sad'),(2794,'We\'re taught to be ashamed of confusion, anger, fear and sadness, and to me they\'re of equal value to happiness, excitement and inspiration.','Alanis Morissette','sad'),(2795,'I can see the humorous side of things and enjoy the fun when it comes; but look where I will, there seems to me always more sadness than joy in life.','Jerome K. Jerome','sad'),(2796,'Can I see another\'s woe, and not be in sorrow too? Can I see another\'s grief, and not seek for kind relief?','William Blake','sad'),(2797,'Do not make best friends with a melancholy sad soul. They always are heavily loaded, and you must bear half.','Francois Fenelon','sad'),(2798,'An ounce of cheerfulness is worth a pound of sadness to serve God with.','Thomas Fuller','sad'),(2799,'Our sweetest songs are those that tell of saddest thought.','Percy Bysshe Shelley','sad'),(2800,'Experiencing sadness and anger can make you feel more creative, and by being creative, you can get beyond your pain or negativity.','Yoko Ono','sad'),(2801,'Melancholy and sadness are the start of doubt... doubt is the beginning of despair; despair is the cruel beginning of the differing degrees of wickedness.','Isidore Ducasse Lautreamont','sad'),(2802,'My father\'s death, my move, and my frightening and difficult delivery created a tremendous amount of stress, pain, and sadness for me. I was practically devastated beyond recovery.','Brooke Shields','sad'),(2803,'The rose and the thorn, and sorrow and gladness are linked together.','Saadi','sad'),(2804,'In deep sadness there is no place for sentimentality.','William S. Burroughs','sad'),(2805,'When I seemed to be irritable or sad, my father would quote the learned Dr. Knight, and then say, \'Just go to sleep.\' Like all smart aleck kids, I thought the advice was silly. But as I\'ve grown older, I\'ve realized just how smart Knight was.','Ben Stein','sad'),(2806,'I really believe that all of us have a lot of darkness in our souls. Anger, rage, fear, sadness. I don\'t think that\'s only reserved for people who have horrible upbringings. I think it really exists and is part of the human condition. I think in the course of your life you figure out ways to deal with that.','Kevin Bacon','sad'),(2807,'I was raised in an atmosphere of \'everything\'s fine.\' But as I got older, I was like, \'Well no, everything\'s not fine. There is stuff that\'s sad.\' I am a really sensitive person. I think I am too sensitive sometimes.','Ellen DeGeneres','sad'),(2808,'My parents\' divorce left me with a lot of sadness and pain and acting, and especially humour, was my way of dealing with all that.','Jennifer Aniston','sad'),(2809,'The keenest sorrow is to recognize ourselves as the sole cause of all our adversities.','Sophocles','sad'),(2810,'I get mad. I get sad. I have all those emotions. But I just like to keep them to myself. I don\'t think my fans need to be bothered with if I\'m mad or sad about something. I should just be concerned that they are keeping up with my music or I\'m making them happy with my show.','Demi Lovato','sad'),(2811,'Sadness flies away on the wings of time.','Jean de La Fontaine','sad'),(2812,'It\'s a source of great sadness to me that my father died without having seen me do anything worthwhile. He was constantly having to make excuses for me.','Daniel Day-Lewis','sad'),(2813,'Dying is only one thing to be sad over... Living unhappily is something else.','Morrie Schwartz','sad'),(2814,'In this world, full often, our joys are only the tender shadows which our sorrows cast.','Henry Ward Beecher','sad'),(2815,'It is one of the most saddening things in life that, try as we may, we can never be certain of making people happy, whereas we can almost always be certain of making them unhappy.','Thomas Huxley','sad'),(2816,'It doesn\'t hurt to feel sad from time to time.','Willie Nelson','sad'),(2817,'If you win all the time, you lose the drama in life. To make the happy moments happy, you need the sad moments too.','Doug Davidson','sad'),(2818,'In LA, I mean, here\'s this place full of desperate and sad people who take their only pleasure from destroying others for the purposes of their own self-aggrandizement.','Heather Donahue','sad'),(2819,'A lot of our entertainment throws into detail the stagnation and illness of how we live today-it\'s sad and it\'s sick... and it\'s profitable.','Heather Donahue','sad'),(2820,'I like \'Bewitched\' off the first album because it\'s one of the happiest songs I\'ve ever written and, as any writer will tell you, happy songs are a million times more difficult to write than sad songs.','Malcolm Wilson','sad'),(2821,'I probably have the worst wardrobe. It\'s the most ill-fitting with the worst patterns and colors and the most nipple rubbage. There\'s bad chafing, and it\'s always tight in all the wrong places. What\'s sad is that I\'m kinda getting used to it.','Josh Hopkins','sad'),(2822,'I think that the Information Age is great, but there\'s a downside to it obviously as well, and it\'s that false information can be perpetuated so quickly. And it\'s sad that so many people will believe it.','Josh Hopkins','sad'),(2823,'A marriage is no amusement but a solemn act, and generally a sad one.','Queen Victoria','sad'),(2824,'Well, I did Marlene 15 years ago and that\'s in the style. It\'s somehow similar and not similar because Marlene was much more aggressive, funny and sad.','Maximilian Schell','sad'),(2825,'Scientology is probably one of the most misunderstood things, and it\'s sad that it\'s so misunderstood.','Stanley Clarke','sad'),(2826,'I think it\'s sad to me that I had to make a decision to not play the game that I feel like I\'m best at and that I love. But if it was just about the game itself, I\'d be there in a heartbeat. But that\'s not how the real world works.','Tiffeny Milbrett','sad'),(2827,'I don\'t know how the poor farmers deal with such situations in real life. It\'s really sad.','Sanjay Dutt','sad'),(2828,'I\'m convinced I got signed because of who I am. And it makes me sad.','Jeff Buckley','sad'),(2829,'I am not a sad clown. I am not a sad clown.','Nathan Lane','sad'),(2830,'I think that the majority of messages are validating messages to confirm the survival of conscious. And many times that validation message is negative or sad.','John Edward','sad'),(2831,'Nolan has the strangest affect on people. You know, I think there\'s something very sad and little boy about him, but at the same time the way he goes about everything is so awkward and obnoxious. He can never say the right thing, you know? And I think if he just didn\'t try so hard and calmed down, people might actually like him a bit more!','Gabriel Mann','sad'),(2832,'I mean, I was just one of the ones who got exposed, and because of the position I was in, where I was in my life, it went mainstream. A lot of people got out of it after my situation, not because I went to prison but because it was sad for them to see me go through something that was so pointless, that could have been avoided.','Michael Vick','sad'),(2833,'I would never have become music director of the Chicago Symphony, which would have been an extremely sad loss.','Georg Solti','sad'),(2834,'I was so sad from losing two of my dogs and my mother. I had this vision of all these animals sitting behind bars. They had no control and were scared. That\'s why I got into fostering and adopting animals out.','Linda Blair','sad'),(2835,'When I was leaving I kind of felt a little bit sad, because I made some friends down in skid row.','Pras Michel','sad'),(2836,'I only really watch sport. That\'s where you see real joy. I don\'t like watching much else on TV, because it\'s generally either twisted or sad.','Roger Milla','sad'),(2837,'I wanted to be a dancer my whole life. And when I gave it up to act, I always had a really sad part of myself that missed it and missed performing and missed being physical in that way.','Lyndsy Fonseca','sad'),(2838,'The sad truth is that excellence makes people nervous.','Shana Alexander','sad'),(2839,'It\'s sad that women characters have lost so much ground in popular movies. Didn\'t \'Thelma and Louise\' prove that women want to see women doing things on film? Thelma and Louise were in a classic car; they were being chased by cops; they shot up a truck - and women loved it.','Robin Quivers','sad'),(2840,'I\'m terribly sad about Farrah\'s passing. She was incredibly brave, and God will be welcoming her with open arms.','Cheryl Ladd','sad'),(2841,'You have to keep hobbies in L.A. Otherwise, it\'s sad.','Lake Bell','sad'),(2842,'When you are joyous, look deep into your heart and you shall find it is only that which has given you sorrow that is giving you joy. When you are sorrowful look again in your heart, and you shall see that in truth you are weeping for that which has been your delight.','Khalil Gibran','sad'),(2843,'Every man has his secret sorrows which the world knows not; and often times we call a man cold when he is only sad.','Henry Wadsworth Longfellow','sad'),(2844,'It\'s sad when someone you know becomes someone you knew.','Henry Rollins','sad'),(2845,'If my world were to cave in tomorrow, I would look back on all the pleasures, excitements and worthwhilenesses I have been lucky enough to have had. Not the sadness, not my miscarriages or my father leaving home, but the joy of everything else. It will have been enough.','Audrey Hepburn','sad'),(2846,'Sadness is but a wall between two gardens.','Khalil Gibran','sad'),(2847,'I seldom think about my limitations, and they never make me sad. Perhaps there is just a touch of yearning at times; but it is vague, like a breeze among flowers.','Helen Keller','sad'),(2848,'Affliction comes to us, not to make us sad but sober; not to make us sorry but wise.','H. G. Wells','sad'),(2849,'A sad soul can kill quicker than a germ.','John Steinbeck','sad'),(2850,'Make the most of your regrets; never smother your sorrow, but tend and cherish it till it comes to have a separate and integral interest. To regret deeply is to live afresh.','Henry David Thoreau','sad'),(2851,'Participate joyfully in the sorrows of the world. We cannot cure the world of sorrows, but we can choose to live in joy.','Joseph Campbell','sad'),(2852,'Live by this credo: have a little laugh at life and look around you for happiness instead of sadness. Laughter has always brought me out of unhappy situations.','Red Skelton','sad'),(2853,'I\'ve cried, and you\'d think I\'d be better for it, but the sadness just sleeps, and it stays in my spine the rest of my life.','Conor Oberst','sad'),(2854,'Isn\'t it sad to go to your grave without ever wondering why you were born? Who, with such a thought, would not spring from bed, eager to resume discovering the world and rejoicing to be part of it?','Richard Dawkins','sad'),(2855,'And I remember going to the record studio and there was a park across the street and I\'d see all the children playing and I would cry because it would make me sad that I would have to work instead.','Michael Jackson','sad'),(2856,'The word \'happiness\' would lose its meaning if it were not balanced by sadness.','Carl Jung','sad'),(2857,'The walls we build around us to keep sadness out also keeps out the joy.','Jim Rohn','sad'),(2858,'The tragedy of life is in what dies inside a man while he lives - the death of genuine feeling, the death of inspired response, the awareness that makes it possible to feel the pain or the glory of other men in yourself.','Norman Cousins','sad'),(2859,'I do believe that if you haven\'t learnt about sadness, you cannot appreciate happiness.','Nana Mouskouri','sad'),(2860,'One must not let oneself be overwhelmed by sadness.','Jackie Kennedy','sad'),(2861,'We look before and after, And pine for what is not; Our sincerest laughter With some pain is fraught; Our sweetest songs are those that tell of saddest thought.','Percy Bysshe Shelley','sad'),(2862,'Sad things happen. They do. But we don\'t need to live sad forever.','Mattie Stepanek','sad'),(2863,'Every life has a measure of sorrow, and sometimes this is what awakens us.','Steven Tyler','sad'),(2864,'It is sadder to find the past again and find it inadequate to the present than it is to have it elude you and remain forever a harmonious conception of memory.','F. Scott Fitzgerald','sad'),(2865,'For all sad words of tongue and pen, The saddest are these, \'It might have been\'.','John Greenleaf Whittier','sad'),(2866,'We never taste a perfect joy; our happiest successes are mixed with sadness.','Pierre Corneille','sad'),(2867,'I don\'t have many sad days.','Billy Graham','sad'),(2868,'War is very sad and small life is pathetically fragile at times.','Henry Rollins','sad'),(2869,'A lot of sad stories in a row - that wears on you.','Elizabeth Edwards','sad'),(2870,'Among the reasons people keep sad stories to themselves is that they do not want anyone to feel sorry for them. I don\'t. I don\'t want you to feel sorry for me.','Judith Moore','sad'),(2871,'I\'ve got to be high class... Which is sad, because I like bars.','Daniel Craig','sad'),(2872,'The sad thing is that I feel so boring because \'Twilight\' is literally how every conversation I have these days begins - whether it\'s someone I\'m meeting for the first time or someone I just haven\'t seen in a while. The first thing I want to say to them is, \'It\'s insane! And, as a person, I can\'t do anything!\'','Kristen Stewart','sad'),(2873,'There\'s never been a culture that wasn\'t obsessed with food. The sort of sad thing is that our obsession is no longer with food, but with the price of food.','Jonathan Safran Foer','sad'),(2874,'Our religion is itself profoundly sad - a religion of universal anguish, and one which, because of its very catholicity, grants full liberty to the individual and asks no better than to be celebrated in each man\'s own language - so long as he knows anguish and is a painter.','Charles Baudelaire','sad'),(2875,'I have a piece of great and sad news to tell you: I am dead.','Jean Cocteau','sad'),(2876,'I was a very good girl for a long time, that\'s what really drew me to acting. The stage was the perfect place to be outrageous, to be sad, to be angry, to be all these different things.','Joan Allen','sad'),(2877,'It is a sad commentary of our times when our young must seek advice and counsel from \"Dear Abby\" instead of going to Mom and Dad.','Abigail Van Buren','sad'),(2878,'It\'s much easier to write when you\'re sad. But you can end up isolated and depressed because you almost need to put yourself in that situation to have that angst to write from.','Natalie Imbruglia','sad'),(2879,'I\'ll always be sad that my marriage ended.','Shania Twain','sad'),(2880,'For my wrap present, Colin Farrell gave me a first edition book. I got so involved with this character and I was so sad when the movie was over that when I got home and I tried to read the book I got really emotional and I started crying.','Salma Hayek','sad'),(2881,'When you\'re going through something, whether it\'s a wonderful thing like having a child or a sad thing like losing somebody, you often feel like \'Oh my God, I\'m so overwhelmed; I\'m dealing with this huge thing on my own.\' In fact, poetry\'s a nice reminder that, no, everybody goes through it. These are universal experiences.','Caroline Kennedy','sad'),(2882,'But I\'m not like sad, depressed miserable person. I guess sometimes I give off that impression.','Edward Furlong','sad'),(2883,'There were points in my life where I felt oddly irresistible to women. I\'m not in that state now and that makes me sad.','Jack Nicholson','sad'),(2884,'I think I would be very sad if I wasn\'t able to have a baby.','Nicole Kidman','sad'),(2885,'The monarchy is foremost a business, and it\'s important to them that the British public continue to finance the excessive luxurious lifestyles of the now quite enormous, wasteful and useless \'royal\' family. I find it very sad.','Steven Patrick Morrissey','sad'),(2886,'What I really tried to do with Helen was make her show this sad side of her. She was married off at 16, was so young and living in this castle that can\'t leave because of how she looks, and married to a man she hates and three times her age.','Diane Kruger','sad'),(2887,'You can\'t have an up without a down, a right without a left, a back without a front - or a happy without a sad.','Harlan Coben','sad'),(2888,'I would love to be married. But it\'s not a necessity like the way that I feel I need and want to have children. It would be wonderful to have a husband, and I would feel blessed to do it. But I would feel sad for the rest of my life if I had no kids.','Mindy Kaling','sad'),(2889,'I don\'t know what to say to that, but I have to agree with Johnny that, yeah, we do touch upon things that most men would rather not admit: That we feel pain, we cry, get sad and sometimes don\'t deal well with disappointment.','Peter Steele','sad'),(2890,'Acting gave me the opportunity to do outrageous things. It allowed me to be sad, happy, angry and lustful, even if it was just vicariously.','Joan Allen','sad'),(2891,'At a time when 2500 American soldiers have given their lives for the cause of bringing democracy to Iraq, it is sad and frustrating to watch the Republican establishment disgrace the exercise of democracy in our own House of Representatives.','Earl Blumenauer','sad'),(2892,'It\'s a sad fact about our culture that a poet can earn much more money writing or talking about his art than he can by practicing it.','W. H. Auden','sad'),(2893,'I think it is really sad that when people lose their homes they kind of lose their minds too.','Margaret Cho','sad'),(2894,'The \'80s were fabulous. The \'90s sucked, and the \'70s were just a sad, sad time in human history. Go 1980s! There\'s something that\'s just so cute about that time. And not just yellow nail polish and \'I\'m a loner.\'','Jennifer Sky','sad'),(2895,'I was sad that Corpse Bride was so short. I would\'ve liked to have had her around for way longer. She doesn\'t actually have that many scenes.','Helena Bonham Carter','sad'),(2896,'As a writer, or as a filmmaker, you have to present yourself, and part of what yourself is is what you\'re interested in, or what you think is funny, or what you think is sad, or what you think is horrible.','Charlie Kaufman','sad'),(2897,'You know, why at the end of your life should you assemble thousands of pages of \'Why am I so sad, why am I so depressed?\' Instead, assemble thousands of pages of why you\'re so content.','Elizabeth Gilbert','sad'),(2898,'As somebody who, in my second marriage, insisted on a prenuptial agreement, I can also testify that sometimes it is an act of love to chart the exit strategy before you enter the union, in order to make sure that not only you, but your partner as well, knows that there will be no World War III should hearts and minds, for any sad reason, change.','Elizabeth Gilbert','sad'),(2899,'It\'s sad that the most glorious of sexual experiences can make us feel guilty, ashamed, embarrassed, and abnormal.','Sue Johanson','sad'),(2900,'The funny thing is I\'m not bothered or sad about being on my own - after all I\'ve never had a husband.','Francesca Annis','sad'),(2901,'With my schedule being so crazy, I can\'t call every day or hang out with my friends like I used to and that\'s definitely sad.','Jordin Sparks','sad'),(2902,'My comedy is for children from three to 93. You do need a slightly childish sense of humour and if you haven\'t got that, it\'s very sad.','Norman Wisdom','sad'),(2903,'I remember a time when all my fans were crying and sad and going through hell. Now, we\'re trying to uplift each other and accept ourselves for who we are, even if nobody else does.','Mary J. Blige','sad'),(2904,'The attacks on the World Trade Center and the Pentagon shook our nation to the core. Americans were deeply frightened, sad, and angry, and they rallied around a President who, at the time, showed impressive certitude and calm.','Eliot Spitzer','sad'),(2905,'The sad duty of politics is to establish justice in a sinful world.','Reinhold Niebuhr','sad'),(2906,'Watergate provides a model case study of the interaction and powers of each of the branches of government. It also is a morality play with a sad and dramatic ending.','Bob Woodward','sad'),(2907,'I was at the Olympic Games winning medals and I still doubted my image. I doubted what I looked like. That\'s sad.','Shawn Johnson','sad'),(2908,'People say you should read your criticism because it will make you a better person but it doesn\'t. It just makes you a sad bitter old showbiz nightmare.','Jo Brand','sad'),(2909,'It is sad to see a woman sacrificing the ties of the affections even to do good.','Maria Mitchell','sad'),(2910,'My dad was a homicide cop in the gay neighborhood in the city when gay neighborhoods were desperate, depressing, sad places run by the mob. The only gay people he\'d met when I came out to him were corpses.','Dan Savage','sad'),(2911,'As a songwriter I hate this whole, \'If it\'s a sad song, it has to sound like a sad song thing.\' And that goes all the way back to my days with the Format. I\'m an insane narcissist, so if I have to get something off my chest, I\'ll get something off my chest.','Nate Ruess','sad'),(2912,'Well the country songs themselves are three-chord stories, ballads which are mostly sad. If you are already feeling sorry for yourself when you listen to them they will take you to an even sadder place.','Willie Nelson','sad'),(2913,'I do not take steroids. I never have. It\'s sad to me that people want to point fingers. I don\'t do that. That\'s not me. I wouldn\'t feel like a human being.','Jackie Joyner-Kersee','sad'),(2914,'I\'ve met so many fans of daytime television who\'ve watched the shows with their moms and grandmas and feel like they\'ve known the characters their whole lives. It\'s sad for them to have to say goodbye to their favorite soaps and characters. We don\'t want that to happen to the \'Days\' fans.','Alison Sweeney','sad'),(2915,'I\'m not sad at all about turning 40.','Halle Berry','sad'),(2916,'Morality comes with the sad wisdom of age, when the sense of curiosity has withered.','Graham Greene','sad'),(2917,'When you are joyous, look deep into your heart and you shall find it is only that which has given you sorrow that is giving you joy. When you are sorrowful look again in your heart, and you shall see that in truth you are weeping for that which has been your delight.','Khalil Gibran','sad'),(2918,'Every man has his secret sorrows which the world knows not; and often times we call a man cold when he is only sad.','Henry Wadsworth Longfellow','sad'),(2919,'It\'s sad when someone you know becomes someone you knew.','Henry Rollins','sad'),(2920,'If my world were to cave in tomorrow, I would look back on all the pleasures, excitements and worthwhilenesses I have been lucky enough to have had. Not the sadness, not my miscarriages or my father leaving home, but the joy of everything else. It will have been enough.','Audrey Hepburn','sad'),(2921,'Sadness is but a wall between two gardens.','Khalil Gibran','sad'),(2922,'I seldom think about my limitations, and they never make me sad. Perhaps there is just a touch of yearning at times; but it is vague, like a breeze among flowers.','Helen Keller','sad'),(2923,'Affliction comes to us, not to make us sad but sober; not to make us sorry but wise.','H. G. Wells','sad'),(2924,'A sad soul can kill quicker than a germ.','John Steinbeck','sad'),(2925,'Make the most of your regrets; never smother your sorrow, but tend and cherish it till it comes to have a separate and integral interest. To regret deeply is to live afresh.','Henry David Thoreau','sad'),(2926,'Participate joyfully in the sorrows of the world. We cannot cure the world of sorrows, but we can choose to live in joy.','Joseph Campbell','sad'),(2927,'Live by this credo: have a little laugh at life and look around you for happiness instead of sadness. Laughter has always brought me out of unhappy situations.','Red Skelton','sad'),(2928,'I\'ve cried, and you\'d think I\'d be better for it, but the sadness just sleeps, and it stays in my spine the rest of my life.','Conor Oberst','sad'),(2929,'Isn\'t it sad to go to your grave without ever wondering why you were born? Who, with such a thought, would not spring from bed, eager to resume discovering the world and rejoicing to be part of it?','Richard Dawkins','sad'),(2930,'And I remember going to the record studio and there was a park across the street and I\'d see all the children playing and I would cry because it would make me sad that I would have to work instead.','Michael Jackson','sad'),(2931,'The word \'happiness\' would lose its meaning if it were not balanced by sadness.','Carl Jung','sad'),(2932,'The walls we build around us to keep sadness out also keeps out the joy.','Jim Rohn','sad'),(2933,'The tragedy of life is in what dies inside a man while he lives - the death of genuine feeling, the death of inspired response, the awareness that makes it possible to feel the pain or the glory of other men in yourself.','Norman Cousins','sad'),(2934,'I do believe that if you haven\'t learnt about sadness, you cannot appreciate happiness.','Nana Mouskouri','sad'),(2935,'One must not let oneself be overwhelmed by sadness.','Jackie Kennedy','sad'),(2936,'We look before and after, And pine for what is not; Our sincerest laughter With some pain is fraught; Our sweetest songs are those that tell of saddest thought.','Percy Bysshe Shelley','sad'),(2937,'Sad things happen. They do. But we don\'t need to live sad forever.','Mattie Stepanek','sad'),(2938,'Every life has a measure of sorrow, and sometimes this is what awakens us.','Steven Tyler','sad'),(2939,'It is sadder to find the past again and find it inadequate to the present than it is to have it elude you and remain forever a harmonious conception of memory.','F. Scott Fitzgerald','sad'),(2940,'For all sad words of tongue and pen, The saddest are these, \'It might have been\'.','John Greenleaf Whittier','sad'),(2941,'We never taste a perfect joy; our happiest successes are mixed with sadness.','Pierre Corneille','sad'),(2942,'Beauty makes idiots sad and wise men merry.','George Jean Nathan','sad'),(2943,'They say geniuses mostly have great mothers. They mostly have sad fates.','David Herbert Lawrence','sad'),(2944,'I love my past, I love my present. I am not ashamed of what I have had, and I am not sad because I no longer have it.','Sidonie Gabrielle Colette','sad'),(2945,'They say such nice things about people at their funerals that it makes me sad that I\'m going to miss mine by just a few days.','Garrison Keillor','sad'),(2946,'How sad it is that we give up on people who are just like us.','Fred Rogers','sad'),(2947,'Women often postpone their lives, thinking that if they\'re not with a partner then it doesn\'t really count. They\'re still searching for their prince, in a way. And as much as we don\'t discuss that, because it\'s too embarrassing and too sad, I think it really does exist.','Jane Campion','sad'),(2948,'I think people appreciate a songwriter who shows different sides. The whole angst thing is cool, but if that\'s all you\'ve got, it\'s just boring. Everything I write, whether it\'s happy or sad, has a sense of humor to it.','Katy Perry','sad'),(2949,'Poverty makes you sad as well as wise.','Bertolt Brecht','sad'),(2950,'The sad souls of those who lived without blame and without praise.','Dante Alighieri','sad'),(2951,'Sad people dislike the happy, and the happy the sad; the quick thinking the sedate, and the careless the busy and industrious.','Horace','sad'),(2952,'The president we have today is a typical Washington politician that\'s prone to hyperbole and decisiveness and false outrage. And I think it\'s very sad - very sad to watch.','Marco Rubio','sad'),(2953,'The sad thing is most people have to check with someone before they do the things that make them happy. We\'re all passing through; the least we can do is be happy, and the only way to do that is by being selfish.','Gene Simmons','sad'),(2954,'It is a historical error for those who were not there to just refer to August 28th as \'I Have a Dream\' speech day. That is a real disservice to those who were there. It was a sad day. It was not a celebration environment.','Jesse Jackson','sad'),(2955,'There must be something solemn, serious, and tender about any attitude which we denominate religious. If glad, it must not grin or snicker; if sad, it must not scream or curse.','William James','sad'),(2956,'Man is born passionate of body, but with an innate though secret tendency to the love of Good in his main-spring of Mind. But God help us all! It is at present a sad jar of atoms.','Lord Byron','sad'),(2957,'I am very sad for men and women trapped in any relationship where there is cruelty, dominance, inequity. I long for the liberation of all people.','Jasmine Guy','sad'),(2958,'The sad truth is that without complex business partnerships between African elites and European traders and commercial agents, the slave trade to the New World would have been impossible, at least on the scale it occurred.','Henry Louis Gates','sad'),(2959,'The sad truth is that the civil rights movement cannot be reborn until we identify the causes of black suffering, some of them self-inflicted. Why can\'t black leaders organize rallies around responsible sexuality, birth within marriage, parents reading to their children and students staying in school and doing homework?','Henry Louis Gates','sad'),(2960,'I love jazz music and sad music. I\'m a sentimental guy. I\'m a romantic guy.','Fred Durst','sad'),(2961,'I once made the mistake of going for a whole row of false eyelashes, which was just wrong as it gave me a sad, puppy-eyed look.','Sienna Miller','sad'),(2962,'Better by far you should forget and smile that you should remember and be sad.','Christina Rossetti','sad'),(2963,'Few women, I fear, have had such reason as I have to think the long sad years of youth were worth living for the sake of middle age.','Dwight D. Eisenhower','sad'),(2964,'Being on your own would be sad, sick and weird. I don\'t trust myself. I need that balance.','Daniel Craig','sad'),(2965,'The death of any man aged 56 is very sad for his widow and family. And no one would deny that Steve Jobs was a brilliant and highly innovative technician, with great business flair and marketing ability.','A. N. Wilson','sad'),(2966,'Los Angeles can be a really sad city.','Adam Lambert','sad'),(2967,'Good humor is the health of the soul, sadness is its poison.','Lord Chesterfield','sad'),(2968,'It\'s a sad man my friend who\'s livin\' in his own skin and can\'t stand the company.','Bruce Springsteen','sad'),(2969,'We\'re taught to be ashamed of confusion, anger, fear and sadness, and to me they\'re of equal value to happiness, excitement and inspiration.','Alanis Morissette','sad'),(2970,'I can see the humorous side of things and enjoy the fun when it comes; but look where I will, there seems to me always more sadness than joy in life.','Jerome K. Jerome','sad'),(2971,'Can I see another\'s woe, and not be in sorrow too? Can I see another\'s grief, and not seek for kind relief?','William Blake','sad'),(2972,'Do not make best friends with a melancholy sad soul. They always are heavily loaded, and you must bear half.','Francois Fenelon','sad'),(2973,'An ounce of cheerfulness is worth a pound of sadness to serve God with.','Thomas Fuller','sad'),(2974,'Our sweetest songs are those that tell of saddest thought.','Percy Bysshe Shelley','sad'),(2975,'Experiencing sadness and anger can make you feel more creative, and by being creative, you can get beyond your pain or negativity.','Yoko Ono','sad'),(2976,'Melancholy and sadness are the start of doubt... doubt is the beginning of despair; despair is the cruel beginning of the differing degrees of wickedness.','Isidore Ducasse Lautreamont','sad'),(2977,'My father\'s death, my move, and my frightening and difficult delivery created a tremendous amount of stress, pain, and sadness for me. I was practically devastated beyond recovery.','Brooke Shields','sad'),(2978,'The rose and the thorn, and sorrow and gladness are linked together.','Saadi','sad'),(2979,'In deep sadness there is no place for sentimentality.','William S. Burroughs','sad'),(2980,'When I seemed to be irritable or sad, my father would quote the learned Dr. Knight, and then say, \'Just go to sleep.\' Like all smart aleck kids, I thought the advice was silly. But as I\'ve grown older, I\'ve realized just how smart Knight was.','Ben Stein','sad'),(2981,'I really believe that all of us have a lot of darkness in our souls. Anger, rage, fear, sadness. I don\'t think that\'s only reserved for people who have horrible upbringings. I think it really exists and is part of the human condition. I think in the course of your life you figure out ways to deal with that.','Kevin Bacon','sad'),(2982,'I was raised in an atmosphere of \'everything\'s fine.\' But as I got older, I was like, \'Well no, everything\'s not fine. There is stuff that\'s sad.\' I am a really sensitive person. I think I am too sensitive sometimes.','Ellen DeGeneres','sad'),(2983,'My parents\' divorce left me with a lot of sadness and pain and acting, and especially humour, was my way of dealing with all that.','Jennifer Aniston','sad'),(2984,'The keenest sorrow is to recognize ourselves as the sole cause of all our adversities.','Sophocles','sad'),(2985,'I get mad. I get sad. I have all those emotions. But I just like to keep them to myself. I don\'t think my fans need to be bothered with if I\'m mad or sad about something. I should just be concerned that they are keeping up with my music or I\'m making them happy with my show.','Demi Lovato','sad'),(2986,'Sadness flies away on the wings of time.','Jean de La Fontaine','sad'),(2987,'It\'s a source of great sadness to me that my father died without having seen me do anything worthwhile. He was constantly having to make excuses for me.','Daniel Day-Lewis','sad'),(2988,'Dying is only one thing to be sad over... Living unhappily is something else.','Morrie Schwartz','sad'),(2989,'In this world, full often, our joys are only the tender shadows which our sorrows cast.','Henry Ward Beecher','sad'),(2990,'It is one of the most saddening things in life that, try as we may, we can never be certain of making people happy, whereas we can almost always be certain of making them unhappy.','Thomas Huxley','sad'),(2991,'It doesn\'t hurt to feel sad from time to time.','Willie Nelson','sad'),(2992,'The good times of today, are the sad thoughts of tomorrow.','Bob Marley','sad'),(2993,'For me, singing sad songs often has a way of healing a situation. It gets the hurt out in the open into the light, out of the darkness.','Reba McEntire','sad'),(2994,'It is sad not to love, but it is much sadder not to be able to love.','Miguel de Unamuno','sad'),(2995,'Usually when people are sad, they don\'t do anything. They just cry over their condition. But when they get angry, they bring about a change.','James Russell Lowell','sad'),(2996,'I am convinced that material things can contribute a lot to making one\'s life pleasant, but, basically, if you do not have very good friends and relatives who matter to you, life will be really empty and sad and material things cease to be important.','David Rockefeller','sad'),(2997,'A comfortable old age is the reward of a well-spent youth. Instead of its bringing sad and melancholy prospects of decay, it would give us hopes of eternal youth in a better world.','Maurice Chevalier','sad'),(2998,'Every word, facial expression, gesture, or action on the part of a parent gives the child some message about self-worth. It is sad that so many parents don\'t realize what messages they are sending.','Virginia Satir','sad'),(2999,'Hear me, my chiefs! I am tired. My heart is sick and sad. From where the sun now stands, I will fight no more forever.','Chief Joseph','sad'),(3000,'Let my soul smile through my heart and my heart smile through my eyes, that I may scatter rich smiles in sad hearts.','Paramahansa Yogananda','sad'),(3001,'The sad truth is that most evil is done by people who never make up their minds to be good or evil.','Hannah Arendt','sad'),(3002,'I hold the world but as the world, Gratiano; A stage where every man must play a part, And mine is a sad one.','William Shakespeare','sad'),(3003,'I had rather have a fool to make me merry than experience to make me sad and to travel for it too!','William Shakespeare','sad'),(3004,'I didn\'t really want to live, so anything that was an investment in time made me angry... but also I just felt sad. When the hopelessness is hurting you, it\'s the fixtures and fittings that finish you off.','Angelina Jolie','sad'),(3005,'It is a very sad thing that nowadays there is so little useless information.','Oscar Wilde','sad'),(3006,'So many gods, so many creeds, so many paths that wind and wind while just the art of being kind is all the sad world needs.','Ella Wheeler Wilcox','sad'),(3007,'Christmas makes everything twice as sad.','Doug Coupland','sad'),(3008,'You can never control who you fall in love with, even when you\'re in the most sad, confused time of your life. You don\'t fall in love with people because they\'re fun. It just happens.','Kirsten Dunst','sad'),(3009,'If we don\'t make earnest moves toward real solutions, then each day we move one day closer to revolution and anarchy in this country. This is the sad, and yet potentially joyous, state of America.','Louis Farrakhan','sad'),(3010,'For I have learned to look on nature, not as in the hour of thoughtless youth, but hearing oftentimes the still, sad music of humanity.','William Wordsworth','sad'),(3011,'And in real life endings aren\'t always neat, whether they\'re happy endings, or whether they\'re sad endings.','Stephen King','sad'),(3012,'The closing of a door can bring blessed privacy and comfort - the opening, terror. Conversely, the closing of a door can be a sad and final thing - the opening a wonderfully joyous moment.','Andy Rooney','sad'),(3013,'Wondrous is the strength of cheerfulness, and its power of endurance - the cheerful man will do more in the same time, will do it; better, will preserve it longer, than the sad or sullen.','Thomas Carlyle','sad'),(3014,'I am an optimist, unrepentant and militant. After all, in order not to be a fool an optimist must know how sad a place the world can be. It is only the pessimist who finds this out anew every day.','Peter Ustinov','sad'),(3015,'There are more than 300,000 families in the Gulf region that lost their homes and are waiting for peace of mind. The hurricane exposed the sad reality of poverty in America. We saw, in all its horrific detail, the vulnerabilities of living in inadequate housing and the heartbreak of losing one\'s home.','Harry Connick, Jr.','sad'),(3016,'It is sad to grow old but nice to ripen.','Brigitte Bardot','sad'),(3017,'Crying is cleansing. There\'s a reason for tears, happiness or sadness.','Dionne Warwick','sad'),(3018,'Heavy hearts, like heavy clouds in the sky, are best relieved by the letting of a little water.','Christopher Morley','sad'),(3019,'You get used to sadness, growing up in the mountains, I guess.','Loretta Lynn','sad'),(3020,'The reason for the sadness of this modern age and the men who live in it is that it looks for the truth in everything and finds it.','Edmond de Goncourt','sad'),(3021,'Your joys and sorrows. You can never tell them. You cheapen the inside of yourself if you do tell them.','Greta Garbo','sad'),(3022,'Sad will be the day for any man when he becomes contented with the thoughts he is thinking and the deeds he is doing - where there is not forever beating at the doors of his soul some great desire to do something larger; which he knows he was meant and made to do.','Phillips Brooks','sad'),(3023,'What else does anxiety about the future bring you but sorrow upon sorrow?','Thomas a Kempis','sad'),(3024,'Time takes away the grief of men.','Desiderius Erasmus','sad'),(3025,'Sorrows are like thunderclouds, in the distance they look black, over our heads scarcely gray.','Jean Paul','sad'),(3026,'The saddest thing that befalls a soul Is when it loses faith in God and woman.','Alexander Smith','sad'),(3027,'God is in the sadness and the laughter, in the bitter and the sweet.','Neale Donald Walsch','sad'),(3028,'We tell our triumphs to the crowds, but our own hearts are the sole confidants of our sorrows.','Edward G. Bulwer-Lytton','sad'),(3029,'Those who gave away their wings are sad not to see them fly.','Antonio Porchia','sad'),(3030,'Actually, the moment of victory is wonderful, but also sad. It means that your trip is ended.','Bill Toomey','sad'),(3031,'Every human walks around with a certain kind of sadness. They may not wear it on their sleeves, but it\'s there if you look deep.','Taraji P. Henson','sad'),(3032,'Nobody understands another\'s sorrow, and nobody another\'s joy.','Franz Schubert','sad'),(3033,'First, accept sadness. Realize that without losing, winning isn\'t so great.','Alyssa Milano','sad'),(3034,'I had sadness for breakfast.','Andy Milonakis','sad'),(3035,'Red is the ultimate cure for sadness.','Bill Blass','sad'),(3036,'They say it\'s better to bury your sadness in a graveyard or garden that waits for the spring to wake from its sleep and burst into green.','Conor Oberst','sad'),(3037,'Sadness is also a kind of defence.','Ivo Andric','sad'),(3038,'One should either be sad or joyful. Contentment is a warm sty for eaters and sleepers.','Eugene O\'Neill','sad'),(3039,'You have to let it all hang out, let go of the ideas that were more comfortable and embrace some of the sadness in your life.','Madeleine Peyroux','sad'),(3040,'Everything\'s complicated, even those things that seem flat in their bleakness or sadness.','Nick Hornby','sad'),(3041,'The excursion is the same when you go looking for your sorrow as when you go looking for your joy.','Eudora Welty','sad'),(3042,'Nobody wants to hear R&B. It\'s sad. If you want to be on the radio you got to stay young.','Jamie Foxx','sad'),(3043,'Marketing has supplanted story as the primary force behind the worthiness of making a film, and that\'s a very sad thing. It\'s film only as a function of consumerism rather than as an important component of our culture, and that\'s everywhere around the world.','Alexander Payne','sad'),(3044,'The question I love to get asked is: \'What\'s the hardest part of your job?\' And literally, the answer is probably real sad, but it\'s to just to be me. Like, it\'s really hard, because I think people, you know, have a set idea of what a pop star should be.','Kelly Clarkson','sad'),(3045,'The best quality about Kobe Bryant? You want me to be honest? I don\'t know. I\'ll tell you why. I open my arms to everybody. But he never stepped forward for the embrace. So I never really got to know him. I don\'t know anything about him, and it\'s kinda sad.','Shaquille O\'Neal','sad'),(3046,'Dwight is a sad clown. You\'ve seen those paintings of sad clown.','Rainn Wilson','sad'),(3047,'I know what I look like - a weird, sad clown puppet. I\'m fine with that.','Rainn Wilson','sad'),(3048,'It\'s time to say goodbye, but I think goodbyes are sad and I\'d much rather say hello. Hello to a new adventure.','Ernie Harwell','sad'),(3049,'I was very sad to hear of the death of Ronnie Barker, who was such a warm, friendly and encouraging presence to have when I started in television. He was also a great comic actor to learn from.','John Cleese','sad'),(3050,'You know, I think we Indians are afraid to show and celebrate our happiness, lest things change around. But I feel that it\'s okay to be sad and okay to show when you are happy.','Shahrukh Khan','sad'),(3051,'I think as an American society, when we\'re paying too many taxes or dealing with war, we don\'t want to see sad things at the movies.','Zoe Saldana','sad'),(3052,'It\'s a sad day when the leaders of the free world engage in such deception and trickery. I voted against this unnecessary war and will continue to argue that the best way to support our troops is to bring them home.','Major R. Owens','sad'),(3053,'That is sad until one recalls how many bad books the world may yet be spared because of the busyness of writers.','Gore Vidal','sad'),(3054,'We\'ve got people looking at our seamy side and our sad side a lot of the time because that\'s easier. It\'s much more difficult to make a film about happiness with lots of jokes in it.','Emma Thompson','sad'),(3055,'Of course it\'s true: the public want to see young people - young people are the people who go to the cinema. It\'s a sad fact of life, but you\'ve got to accept it and not whine about it.','Joan Collins','sad'),(3056,'I was sad to see anybody leave, we had a very nice family on that show. I was very sad to see momma go, Victoria and especially Linda. My god that was my wife on the show, in fact my wife calls her wife.','Larry Hagman','sad'),(3057,'I always think of the live show first, where the song is gonna go in the show. That\'s why they aren\'t sad songs. When I play, I want to make people happy, not sad. It\'s such a pleasure for me to do what I do, and I want other people to feel some form of that pleasure, too.','Jason Mraz','sad'),(3058,'At that time, I feel sad, and I feel no one knows how hard I work and how many tears. They only know the score. At that time, I feel very lonely because no one understands since they haven\'t been world No. 1 before.','Yani Tseng','sad'),(3059,'But you see, that\'s the gilded prison of fashion. We\'re riding in private jets, and meantime I was so incredibly, painfully sad and lonely.','Janice Dickinson','sad'),(3060,'I happen to be interested in watching a face age. I like faces of women aging so it makes me personally quite sad. That\'s a 