aptain\'s ready room died it was always a sad moment.','Patrick Stewart','sad'),(3169,'To the indefinite, uncertain mind of the American radical the most contradictory ideas and methods are possible. The result is a sad chaos in the radical movement, a sort of intellectual hash, which has neither taste nor character.','Emma Goldman','sad'),(3170,'Ladies and gentlemen, it is with great sadness that I announce that I will resign as Australia\'s Minister for Foreign Affairs. I am sad because I love this job. I\'m totally dedicated to the work that we are doing in Australia\'s name around the world, and I believe that we have achieved many good results for Australia, and I\'m proud of them.','Kevin Rudd','sad'),(3171,'You know how sad your life is when you know the release date of DVDs.','Heston Blumenthal','sad'),(3172,'It makes me so desperately sad to witness just how unforgivably wretched our world has become.','Ralph Steadman','sad'),(3173,'We\'re sad about some of the losses of members of great seniority and distinction in the Congress, and some very new members, who will no longer be serving with us.','Nancy Pelosi','sad'),(3174,'All he cares about is going out there with his Jack Daniels bottle. Nothing has changed. That\'s kind of sad. If David was doing better than he used to be, then that would be different. But it was a joke and he made it that way.','Sammy Hagar','sad'),(3175,'People say, oh it\'s a shame, you\'re not nostalgic about the \'60s. Well actually, it\'s quite good, when you think of it. Wouldn\'t it be sad if I was sitting here wishing it back?','Robert Wyatt','sad'),(3176,'Divorce was very sad, obviously, but now I\'ve gotten over it.','Natalie Imbruglia','sad'),(3177,'I like singer-songwriters, and I find sad songs comforting rather than depressing. It makes you realise you\'re not alone in the world.','Natalie Imbruglia','sad'),(3178,'I have had stalkers over the years. The police deal with it but it is very scary. One man kept turning up whe