ne in their fifties being childlike becomes a little sad. You\'ve got to be careful.','Rowan Atkinson','sad'),(3231,'I didn\'t want to be on the losing side. I was fed up with Jewish weakness, timidity and fear. I didn\'t want any more Jewish sentimentality and Jewish suffering. I was sickened by our sad songs.','Lionel Blue','sad'),(3232,'The sad and horrible conclusion is that no one cared that Jews were being murdered... This is the Jewish lesson of the Holocaust and this is the lesson which Auschwitz taught us.','Ariel Sharon','sad'),(3233,'I\'m a person who likes these sort of movies... sad but moving \'art movies\' that normally are at a festival and then they go to a small art house theater and disappear.','Zach Braff','sad'),(3234,'I\'m not sad about any of my life. It\'s so unconventional. It doesn\'t look anything like I thought it would.','Edie Falco','sad'),(3235,'I love music videos, I really do. I think it\'s kind of sad that it\'s a dying art form.','Adam Levine','sad'),(3236,'Women are reputed never to be disgusted. The sad fact is that they often are, but not with men; following the lead of men, they are most often disgusted with themselves.','Germaine Greer','sad'),(3237,'Well, darkness with humor... I\'m not an extremely suicidal or sad person.','Peter Steele','sad'),(3238,'You have to sound sad first of all, then maybe later you can sound good.','Steve Lacy','sad'),(3239,'In Mississippi, you don\'t admit that you\'re gay. It\'s just an awkward thing down South, which is sad.','Lance Bass','sad'),(3240,'Everything takes me longer than I expect. It\'s the sad truth about life.','Donna Tartt','sad'),(3241,'I often feel like I have this spirit living inside of me, always dressing in like short mini skirts... but then I start to discover myself. So there are eight spirits, mischievous ones, sad ones, handsome ones, wise ones, and crazy ones.','Bai Ling','sad'),(3242,'Beauty makes idiots sad and wise men merry.','George Jean Nathan','sad'),(3243,'They 