illiam Shatner','sad'),(3604,'Good humor is the health of the soul, sadness is its poison.','Lord Chesterfield','sad'),(3605,'It\'s a sad man my friend who\'s livin\' in his own skin and can\'t stand the company.','Bruce Springsteen','sad'),(3606,'We\'re taught to be ashamed of confusion, anger, fear and sadness, and to me they\'re of equal value to happiness, excitement and inspiration.','Alanis Morissette','sad'),(3607,'I can see the humorous side of things and enjoy the fun when it comes; but look where I will, there seems to me always more sadness than joy in life.','Jerome K. Jerome','sad'),(3608,'Can I see another\'s woe, and not be in sorrow too? Can I see another\'s grief, and not seek for kind relief?','William Blake','sad'),(3609,'Do not make best friends with a melancholy sad soul. They always are heavily loaded, and you must bear half.','Francois Fenelon','sad'),(3610,'An ounce of cheerfulness is worth a pound of sadness to serve God with.','Thomas Fuller','sad'),(3611,'Our sweetest songs are those that tell of saddest thought.','Percy Bysshe Shelley','sad'),(3612,'Experiencing sadness and anger can make you feel more creative, and by being creative, you can get beyond your pain or negativity.','Yoko Ono','sad'),(3613,'Melancholy and sadness are the start of doubt... doubt is the beginning of despair; despair is the cruel beginning of the differing degrees of wickedness.','Isidore Ducasse Lautreamont','sad'),(3614,'My father\'s death, my move, and my frightening and difficult delivery created a tremendous amount of stress, pain, and sadness for me. I was practically devastated beyond recovery.','Brooke Shields','sad'),(3615,'The rose and the thorn, and sorrow and gladness are linked together.','Saadi','sad'),(3616,'In deep sadness there is no place for sentimentality.','William S. Burroughs','sad'),(3617,'When I seemed to be irritable or sad, my father would quote the learned Dr. Knight, and then say, \'Just go to sleep.\' Like all smart aleck kids, I thought the advice was silly. But as I\'ve grown older, I\'ve realized just how smart Knight was.','Ben Stein','sad'),(3618,'I really believe that all of us have a lot of darkness in our souls. Anger, rage, fear, sadness. I don\'t think that\'s only reserved for people who have horrible upbringings. I think it really exists and is part of the human condition. I think in the course of your life you figure out ways to deal with that.','Kevin Bacon','sad'),(3619,'I was raised in an atmosphere of \'everything\'s fine.\' But as I got older, I was like, \'Well no, everything\'s not fine. There is stuff that\'s sad.\' I am a really sensitive person. I think I am too sensitive sometimes.','Ellen DeGeneres','sad'),(3620,'My parents\' divorce left me with a lot of sadness and pain and acting, and especially humour, was my way of dealing with all that.','Jennifer Aniston','sad'),(3621,'The keenest sorrow is to recognize ourselves as the sole cause of all our adversities.','Sophocles','sad'),(3622,'I get mad. I get sad. I have all those emotions. But I just like to keep them to myself. I don\'t think my fans need to be bothered with if I\'m mad or sad about something. I should just be concerned that they are keeping up with my music or I\'m making them happy with my show.','Demi Lovato','sad'),(3623,'Sadness flies away on the wings of time.','Jean de La Fontaine','sad'),(3624,'It\'s a source of great sadness to me that my father died without having seen me do anything worthwhile. He was constantly having to make excuses for me.','Daniel Day-Lewis','sad'),(3625,'Dying is only one thing to be sad over... Living unhappily is something else.','Morrie Schwartz','sad'),(3626,'In this world, full often, our joys are only the tender shadows which our sorrows cast.','Henry Ward Beecher','sad'),(3627,'It is one of the most saddening things in life that, try as we may, we can never be certain of making people happy, whereas we can almost always be certain of making them unhappy.','Thomas Huxley','sad'),(3628,'It doesn\'t hurt to feel sad from time to time.','Willie Nelson','sad'),(3629,'Beauty makes idiots sad and wise men merry.','George Jean Nathan','sad'),(3630,'They say geniuses mostly have great mothers. They mostly have sad fates.','David Herbert Lawrence','sad'),(3631,'I love my past, I love my present. I am not ashamed of what I have had, and I am not sad because I no longer have it.','Sidonie Gabrielle Colette','sad'),(3632,'They say such nice things about people at their funerals that it makes me sad that I\'m going to miss mine by just a few days.','Garrison Keillor','sad'),(3633,'How sad it is that we give up on people who are just like us.','Fred Rogers','sad'),(3634,'Women often postpone their lives, thinking that if they\'re not with a partner then it doesn\'t really count. They\'re still searching for their prince, in a way. And as much as we don\'t discuss that, because it\'s too embarrassing and too sad, I think it really does exist.','Jane Campion','sad'),(3635,'I think people appreciate a songwriter who shows different sides. The whole angst thing is cool, but if that\'s all you\'ve got, it\'s just boring. Everything I write, whether it\'s happy or sad, has a sense of humor to it.','Katy Perry','sad'),(3636,'Poverty makes you sad as well as wise.','Bertolt Brecht','sad'),(3637,'The sad souls of those who lived without blame and without praise.','Dante Alighieri','sad'),(3638,'Sad people dislike the happy, and the happy the sad; the quick thinking the sedate, and the careless the busy and industrious.','Horace','sad'),(3639,'The president we have today is a typical Washington politician that\'s prone to hyperbole and decisiveness and false outrage. And I think it\'s very sad - very sad to watch.','Marco Rubio','sad'),(3640,'The sad thing is most people have to check with someone before they do the things that make them happy. We\'re all passing through; the least we can do is be happy, and the only way to do that is by being selfish.','Gene Simmons','sad'),(3641,'It is a historical error for those who were not there to just refer to August 28th as \'I Have a Dream\' speech day. That is a real disservice to those who were there. It was a sad day. It was not a celebration environment.','Jesse Jackson','sad'),(3642,'There must be something solemn, serious, and tender about any attitude which we denominate religious. If glad, it must not grin or snicker; if sad, it must not scream or curse.','William James','sad'),(3643,'Man is born passionate of body, but with an innate though secret tendency to the love of Good in his main-spring of Mind. But God help us all! It is at present a sad jar of atoms.','Lord Byron','sad'),(3644,'I am very sad for men and women trapped in any relationship where there is cruelty, dominance, inequity. I long for the liberation of all people.','Jasmine Guy','sad'),(3645,'The sad truth is that without complex business partnerships between African elites and European traders and commercial agents, the slave trade to the New World would have been impossible, at least on the scale it occurred.','Henry Louis Gates','sad'),(3646,'The sad truth is that the civil rights movement cannot be reborn until we identify the causes of black suffering, some of them self-inflicted. Why can\'t black leaders organize rallies around responsible sexuality, birth within marriage, parents reading to their children and students staying in school and doing homework?','Henry Louis Gates','sad'),(3647,'I love jazz music and sad music. I\'m a sentimental guy. I\'m a romantic guy.','Fred Durst','sad'),(3648,'I once made the mistake of going for a whole row of false eyelashes, which was just wrong as it gave me a sad, puppy-eyed look.','Sienna Miller','sad'),(3649,'Better by far you should forget and smile that you should remember and be sad.','Christina Rossetti','sad'),(3650,'Few women, I fear, have had such reason as I have to think the long sad years of youth were worth living for the sake of middle age.','Dwight D. Eisenhower','sad'),(3651,'Being on your own would be sad, sick and weird. I don\'t trust myself. I need that balance.','Daniel Craig','sad'),(3652,'The death of any man aged 56 is very sad for his widow and family. And no one would deny that Steve Jobs was a brilliant and highly innovative technician, with great business flair and marketing ability.','A. N. Wilson','sad'),(3653,'Los Angeles can be a really sad city.','Adam Lambert','sad'),(3654,'51st State was one that I loved doing because the character was so out there, and in a way I was sad to leave the character behind. I\'m afraid I could never be that cool in real life!','Emily Mortimer','sad'),(3655,'With any group of people in life, sad things happen, and crazy things, and happy things. When you\'re in the public eye, it\'s just amplified, that\'s all.','Margot Kidder','sad'),(3656,'Country fans need to support country music by buying albums and concert tickets for traditional artists or the music will just fade away. And that would be really sad.','George Jones','sad'),(3657,'What makes old age so sad is not that our joys but our hopes cease.','Jean Paul','sad'),(3658,'I was in a bar and I said to a friend, \'You know, we\'ve become those 40-year-old guys we used to look at and say, \'Isn\'t it sad?\'','George Clooney','sad'),(3659,'My solo album is dead and buried. We had the funeral. It was sad and I cried a lot but it made such a beautiful corpse that we had an open casket.','Shirley Manson','sad'),(3660,'When I design and wonder what the point is, I think of someone having a bad time in their life. Maybe they are sad and they wake up and put on something I have made and it makes them feel just a bit better. So, in that sense, fashion is a little help in the life of a person. But only a little.','Miuccia Prada','sad'),(3661,'I\'ve traveled around the country and I read local newspapers and all of that, and it\'s a sad, sad thing to go from city to city and see the small newspapers and they\'re tiny. They\'re tiny not only in size but also in scope.','Jim Lehrer','sad'),(3662,'I find America falling in love with a TV show flattering and interesting, but at the same time a little sad.','David Schwimmer','sad'),(3663,'The sad part about our past is that religions, ironically enough, are responsible for creating the most destructive idea that has ever been visited upon the human race: the idea that there is such a thing as \'better.\'','Neale Donald Walsch','sad'),(3664,'I find it sad that by not talking about who I sleep with, that makes me mysterious. There was a time when I would have been called a gentleman.','Kevin Spacey','sad'),(3665,'If I get the forty additional years statisticians say are likely coming to me, I could fit in at least one, maybe two new lifetimes. Sad that only one of those lifetimes can include being the mother of young children.','Anna Quindlen','sad'),(3666,'I think that\'s very sad, that I haven\'t allowed my heart to be broken. I have broken a few.','Sally Field','sad'),(3667,'Apart from the fact that your physical ability starts to decline, I also think someone in their fifties being childlike becomes a little sad. You\'ve got to be careful.','Rowan Atkinson','sad'),(3668,'I didn\'t want to be on the losing side. I was fed up with Jewish weakness, timidity and fear. I didn\'t want any more Jewish sentimentality and Jewish suffering. I was sickened by our sad songs.','Lionel Blue','sad'),(3669,'The sad and horrible conclusion is that no one cared that Jews were being murdered... This is the Jewish lesson of the Holocaust and this is the lesson which Auschwitz taught us.','Ariel Sharon','sad'),(3670,'I\'m a person who likes these sort of movies... sad but moving \'art movies\' that normally are at a festival and then they go to a small art house theater and disappear.','Zach Braff','sad'),(3671,'I\'m not sad about any of my life. It\'s so unconventional. It doesn\'t look anything like I thought it would.','Edie Falco','sad'),(3672,'I love music videos, I really do. I think it\'s kind of sad that it\'s a dying art form.','Adam Levine','sad'),(3673,'Women are reputed never to be disgusted. The sad fact is that they often are, but not with men; following the lead of men, they are most often disgusted with themselves.','Germaine Greer','sad'),(3674,'Well, darkness with humor... I\'m not an extremely suicidal or sad person.','Peter Steele','sad'),(3675,'You have to sound sad first of all, then maybe later you can sound good.','Steve Lacy','sad'),(3676,'In Mississippi, you don\'t admit that you\'re gay. It\'s just an awkward thing down South, which is sad.','Lance Bass','sad'),(3677,'Everything takes me longer than I expect. It\'s the sad truth about life.','Donna Tartt','sad'),(3678,'I often feel like I have this spirit living inside of me, always dressing in like short mini skirts... but then I start to discover myself. So there are eight spirits, mischievous ones, sad ones, handsome ones, wise ones, and crazy ones.','Bai Ling','sad'),(3679,'Crying is cleansing. There\'s a reason for tears, happiness or sadness.','Dionne Warwick','sad'),(3680,'Heavy hearts, like heavy clouds in the sky, are best relieved by the letting of a little water.','Christopher Morley','sad'),(3681,'You get used to sadness, growing up in the mountains, I guess.','Loretta Lynn','sad'),(3682,'The reason for the sadness of this modern age and the men who live in it is that it looks for the truth in everything and finds it.','Edmond de Goncourt','sad'),(3683,'Your joys and sorrows. You can never tell them. You cheapen the inside of yourself if you do tell them.','Greta Garbo','sad'),(3684,'Sad will be the day for any man when he becomes contented with the thoughts he is thinking and the deeds he is doing - where there is not forever beating at the doors of his soul some great desire to do something larger; which he knows he was meant and made to do.','Phillips Brooks','sad'),(3685,'What else does anxiety about the future bring you but sorrow upon sorrow?','Thomas a Kempis','sad'),(3686,'Time takes away the grief of men.','Desiderius Erasmus','sad'),(3687,'Sorrows are like thunderclouds, in the distance they look black, over our heads scarcely gray.','Jean Paul','sad'),(3688,'The saddest thing that befalls a soul Is when it loses faith in God and woman.','Alexander Smith','sad'),(3689,'God is in the sadness and the laughter, in the bitter and the sweet.','Neale Donald Walsch','sad'),(3690,'We tell our triumphs to the crowds, but our own hearts are the sole confidants of our sorrows.','Edward G. Bulwer-Lytton','sad'),(3691,'Those who gave away their wings are sad not to see them fly.','Antonio Porchia','sad'),(3692,'Actually, the moment of victory is wonderful, but also sad. It means that your trip is ended.','Bill Toomey','sad'),(3693,'Every human walks around with a certain kind of sadness. They may not wear it on their sleeves, but it\'s there if you look deep.','Taraji P. Henson','sad'),(3694,'Nobody understands another\'s sorrow, and nobody another\'s joy.','Franz Schubert','sad'),(3695,'First, accept sadness. Realize that without losing, winning isn\'t so great.','Alyssa Milano','sad'),(3696,'I had sadness for breakfast.','Andy Milonakis','sad'),(3697,'Red is the ultimate cure for sadness.','Bill Blass','sad'),(3698,'They say it\'s better to bury your sadness in a graveyard or garden that waits for the spring to wake from its sleep and burst into green.','Conor Oberst','sad'),(3699,'Sadness is also a kind of defence.','Ivo Andric','sad'),(3700,'One should either be sad or joyful. Contentment is a warm sty for eaters and sleepers.','Eugene O\'Neill','sad'),(3701,'You have to let it all hang out, let go of the ideas that were more comfortable and embrace some of the sadness in your life.','Madeleine Peyroux','sad'),(3702,'Everything\'s complicated, even those things that seem flat in their bleakness or sadness.','Nick Hornby','sad'),(3703,'The excursion is the same when you go looking for your sorrow as when you go looking for your joy.','Eudora Welty','sad'),(3704,'I\'ve been on Prozac for 12 years and I\'m off it now. I know what it feels like to be excited and sad again. I haven\'t felt like this in 12 years; I\'m like a giddy little kid.','Jonathan Davis','sad'),(3705,'Whenever the lion fish in the fish tank in the captain\'s ready room died it was always a sad moment.','Patrick Stewart','sad'),(3706,'To the indefinite, uncertain mind of the American radical the most contradictory ideas and methods are possible. The result is a sad chaos in the radical movement, a sort of intellectual hash, which has neither taste nor character.','Emma Goldman','sad'),(3707,'Ladies and gentlemen, it is with great sadness that I announce that I will resign as Australia\'s Minister for Foreign Affairs. I am sad because I love this job. I\'m totally dedicated to the work that we are doing in Australia\'s name around the world, and I believe that we have achieved many good results for Australia, and I\'m proud of them.','Kevin Rudd','sad'),(3708,'You know how sad your life is when you know the release date of DVDs.','Heston Blumenthal','sad'),(3709,'It makes me so desperately sad to witness just how unforgivably wretched our world has become.','Ralph Steadman','sad'),(3710,'We\'re sad about some of the losses of members of great seniority and distinction in the Congress, and some very new members, who will no longer be serving with us.','Nancy Pelosi','sad'),(3711,'All he cares about is going out there with his Jack Daniels bottle. Nothing has changed. That\'s kind of sad. If David was doing better than he used to be, then that would be different. But it was a joke and he made it that way.','Sammy Hagar','sad'),(3712,'People say, oh it\'s a shame, you\'re not nostalgic about the \'60s. Well actually, it\'s quite good, when you think of it. Wouldn\'t it be sad if I was sitting here wishing it back?','Robert Wyatt','sad'),(3713,'Divorce was very sad, obviously, but now I\'ve gotten over it.','Natalie Imbruglia','sad'),(3714,'I like singer-songwriters, and I find sad songs comforting rather than depressing. It makes you realise you\'re not alone in the world.','Natalie Imbruglia','sad'),(3715,'I have had stalkers over the years. The police deal with it but it is very scary. One man kept turning up where we filmed \'Countdown in Leeds,\' which was scary. It was sad as he\'d been sectioned and thought I was talking to him through the TV.','Carol Vorderman','sad'),(3716,'\'The Taxi Ride,\' from my second album, is one people want to hear a lot. I\'m consciously trying to walk on the sunny side of the street, to really lift myself into a place of greater positivity, and that\'s a sad song.','Jane Siberry','sad'),(3717,'I find it amusing on one level, poignant on another, when people try to get recognition from an outside source. It\'s sad.','Grace Slick','sad'),(3718,'Ideally, I would love to mix singing and acting, but you can only be a pop star for so many years. I mean, at 30 it\'s a little bit sad, right?','Rachel Stevens','sad'),(3719,'I think a lot of people think that my parents\' deaths is why I write such sad songs, but that\'s not true. Those songs may just be the woman I am.','Shelby Lynne','sad'),(3720,'I\'m sad to see the passing of the great drug warriors. I certainly did my part in that battle and I don\'t regret any of it.','Marc Maron','sad'),(3721,'As virtuous men pass mildly away, and whisper to their souls to go, whilst some of their sad friends do say, the breath goes now, and some say no.','John Donne','sad'),(3722,'It\'s incredible that they censor films. It\'s sad.','Dario Argento','sad'),(3723,'I\'ve always been drawn to Marilyn Monroe, but certain aspects of her story may be too sad to tell.','Sherilyn Fenn','sad'),(3724,'My mother sent me to psychiatrists since the age of four because she didn\'t think little boys should be sad. When my brother was born, I stared out the window for days. Can you imagine that?','Andy Kaufman','sad'),(3725,'Even modern English people are imperious, superior, ridden by class. All of the hypocrisy and the difficulties that are endemic in being British also make it an incredibly fertile place culturally. A brilliant place to live. Sad but true.','Pete Townshend','sad'),(3726,'It\'s sad when people break up.','Pete Townshend','sad'),(3727,'I feel quite sad for the young musicians coming up because they may never get to pay their rent properly. It doesn\'t matter what the genre; nowadays, it\'s so much harder than it ever was.','Bryan Adams','sad'),(3728,'I\'ve never thought of my characters as being sad. On the contrary, they are full of life. They didn\'t choose tragedy. Tragedy chose them.','Juliette Binoche','sad'),(3729,'Now I\'ll read anytime, anywhere. I love reading in front of the space heater. Isn\'t that a sad confession? But it\'s like my substitute for the roaring fireplace of yore.','Karen Russell','sad'),(3730,'We have newsreaders behaving like actors, lowering their voices if it\'s a sad story, as if we didn\'t know it\'s a sad story. There isn\'t a single cool newsreader.','Tom Baker','sad'),(3731,'And it\'s sad because it\'s like a surprise to people - almost an anomaly - when artists are actually refined and trained on an instrument. That\'s the last thing people think about.','Vanessa Carlton','sad'),(3732,'It\'s really a sad story, and I liked that. The songs on this album talk about relationships in every aspect.','Aaliyah','sad'),(3733,'I felt sad because everyday I had to wake up early to practice before going to school. After school I had to go back to tennis again, and then after tennis I had homework. I didn\'t have time to play.','Li Na','sad'),(3734,'If I was sad or afraid, I would sit in a corner and sing. If I was happy I would jump into the middle of the room and sing. It was how I expressed my emotions.','Nana Mouskouri','sad'),(3735,'Love Is Louder is a movement that is hopefully going to bring some awareness and make some noise when it comes to teens who are feeling suicidal or even just sad, outcasts, and being bullied, and really feel like they have nowhere to turn to.','Brittany Snow','sad'),(3736,'The old know what they want; the young are sad and bewildered.','Logan P. Smith','sad'),(3737,'Atari is a very sad story.','Steve Wozniak','sad'),(3738,'Home will always be Northern Ireland but my schedule means for the next few years I won\'t be there as much. I can\'t do the same things that I did a year ago. That is I\'m something conscious of, but I\'m not sad about it. It\'s fine.','Rory McIlroy','sad'),(3739,'I\'m incredibly sad that my mother\'s not here to see my kids and that my kids don\'t get to know her. And she didn\'t meet my husband. That\'s one of the hardest things. I don\'t even know how to put that into words.','Stella McCartney','sad'),(3740,'When I was a child people simply looked about them and were moderately happy; today they peer beyond the seven seas, bury themselves waist deep in tidings, and by and large what they see and hear makes them unutterably sad.','E. B. White','sad'),(3741,'I\'m so grounded, it\'s sad.','Patti LaBelle','sad'),(3742,'With the other fellow actors who have gone astray, I think it\'s sad that society wants to label the business as doing this to people. It\'s really not true.','Tina Yothers','sad'),(3743,'It\'s very rare that things are true about yourself that are on the Internet. It\'s just sad sometimes. So you definitely try and stay away from it as much as possible.','Taylor Lautner','sad'),(3744,'However, we might oppose it, abortion is a sad feature of modern life.','Robert Casey','sad'),(3745,'You will soon find that I am a bit obsessive about my work. And that is a little sad, one often feels strangely restricted, not finding time to simmer, although one actually has many interests.','Arne Jacobsen','sad'),(3746,'Life can be challenging and sad... but music is the easy part.','St. Vincent','sad'),(3747,'What makes me sad about school is that the people who are unhappy are unhappy because they don\'t believe it will change. And I just want to say: \'It does! High school ends and it\'s over.\' I will tell anyone that it\'s OK to be unhappy at school, make lots of mistakes and then it will be over.','Alice Englert','sad'),(3748,'NASA has been one of the most successful public investments in motivating students to do well and achieve all they can achieve. It\'s sad that we are turning the programme in a direction where it will reduce the amount of motivation and stimulation it provides to young people.','Neil Armstrong','sad'),(3749,'If I don\'t make it, I\'ll be very sad that there are things I didn\'t do, but I\'m happy that I\'ve done what I have.','Stephen Jay Gould','sad'),(3750,'So many schools are getting rid of music programs and it\'s really sad because I know that when I started singing and stuff it was something that I always wanted to do and I never believed in myself to be able to do it.','Hilary Duff','sad'),(3751,'Well, you know, too much democracy is a sort of sad thing.','Ann Richards','sad'),(3752,'People are so codified - it\'s sad.','Jean Paul Gaultier','sad'),(3753,'Saturdays and Sundays, America in the year 2009 does not in some ways differ significantly from the country that existed almost 50 years ago. This is truly sad.','Eric Holder','sad'),(3754,'It\'s a sad fact about our culture that a poet can earn much more money writing or talking about his art than he can by practicing it.','W. H. Auden','sad'),(3755,'I think it is really sad that when people lose their homes they kind of lose their minds too.','Margaret Cho','sad'),(3756,'The \'80s were fabulous. The \'90s sucked, and the \'70s were just a sad, sad time in human history. Go 1980s! There\'s something that\'s just so cute about that time. And not just yellow nail polish and \'I\'m a loner.\'','Jennifer Sky','sad'),(3757,'I was sad that Corpse Bride was so short. I would\'ve liked to have had her around for way longer. She doesn\'t actually have that many scenes.','Helena Bonham Carter','sad'),(3758,'As a writer, or as a filmmaker, you have to present yourself, and part of what yourself is is what you\'re interested in, or what you think is funny, or what you think is sad, or what you think is horrible.','Charlie Kaufman','sad'),(3759,'You know, why at the end of your life should you assemble thousands of pages of \'Why am I so sad, why am I so depressed?\' Instead, assemble thousands of pages of why you\'re so content.','Elizabeth Gilbert','sad'),(3760,'As somebody who, in my second marriage, insisted on a prenuptial agreement, I can also testify that sometimes it is an act of love to chart the exit strategy before you enter the union, in order to make sure that not only you, but your partner as well, knows that there will be no World War III should hearts and minds, for any sad reason, change.','Elizabeth Gilbert','sad'),(3761,'It\'s sad that the most glorious of sexual experiences can make us feel guilty, ashamed, embarrassed, and abnormal.','Sue Johanson','sad'),(3762,'The funny thing is I\'m not bothered or sad about being on my own - after all I\'ve never had a husband.','Francesca Annis','sad'),(3763,'With my schedule being so crazy, I can\'t call every day or hang out with my friends like I used to and that\'s definitely sad.','Jordin Sparks','sad'),(3764,'My comedy is for children from three to 93. You do need a slightly childish sense of humour and if you haven\'t got that, it\'s very sad.','Norman Wisdom','sad'),(3765,'I remember a time when all my fans were crying and sad and going through hell. Now, we\'re trying to uplift each other and accept ourselves for who we are, even if nobody else does.','Mary J. Blige','sad'),(3766,'The attacks on the World Trade Center and the Pentagon shook our nation to the core. Americans were deeply frightened, sad, and angry, and they rallied around a President who, at the time, showed impressive certitude and calm.','Eliot Spitzer','sad'),(3767,'The sad duty of politics is to establish justice in a sinful world.','Reinhold Niebuhr','sad'),(3768,'Watergate provides a model case study of the interaction and powers of each of the branches of government. It also is a morality play with a sad and dramatic ending.','Bob Woodward','sad'),(3769,'I was at the Olympic Games winning medals and I still doubted my image. I doubted what I looked like. That\'s sad.','Shawn Johnson','sad'),(3770,'People say you should read your criticism because it will make you a better person but it doesn\'t. It just makes you a sad bitter old showbiz nightmare.','Jo Brand','sad'),(3771,'It is sad to see a woman sacrificing the ties of the affections even to do good.','Maria Mitchell','sad'),(3772,'My dad was a homicide cop in the gay neighborhood in the city when gay neighborhoods were desperate, depressing, sad places run by the mob. The only gay people he\'d met when I came out to him were corpses.','Dan Savage','sad'),(3773,'As a songwriter I hate this whole, \'If it\'s a sad song, it has to sound like a sad song thing.\' And that goes all the way back to my days with the Format. I\'m an insane narcissist, so if I have to get something off my chest, I\'ll get something off my chest.','Nate Ruess','sad'),(3774,'Well the country songs themselves are three-chord stories, ballads which are mostly sad. If you are already feeling sorry for yourself when you listen to them they will take you to an even sadder place.','Willie Nelson','sad'),(3775,'I do not take steroids. I never have. It\'s sad to me that people want to point fingers. I don\'t do that. That\'s not me. I wouldn\'t feel like a human being.','Jackie Joyner-Kersee','sad'),(3776,'I\'ve met so many fans of daytime television who\'ve watched the shows with their moms and grandmas and feel like they\'ve known the characters their whole lives. It\'s sad for them to have to say goodbye to their favorite soaps and characters. We don\'t want that to happen to the \'Days\' fans.','Alison Sweeney','sad'),(3777,'I\'m not sad at all about turning 40.','Halle Berry','sad'),(3778,'Morality comes with the sad wisdom of age, when the sense of curiosity has withered.','Graham Greene','sad'),(3779,'Nobody wants to hear R&B. It\'s sad. If you want to be on the radio you got to stay young.','Jamie Foxx','sad'),(3780,'Marketing has supplanted story as the primary force behind the worthiness of making a film, and that\'s a very sad thing. It\'s film only as a function of consumerism rather than as an important component of our culture, and that\'s everywhere around the world.','Alexander Payne','sad'),(3781,'The question I love to get asked is: \'What\'s the hardest part of your job?\' And literally, the answer is probably real sad, but it\'s to just to be me. Like, it\'s really hard, because I think people, you know, have a set idea of what a pop star should be.','Kelly Clarkson','sad'),(3782,'The best quality about Kobe Bryant? You want me to be honest? I don\'t know. I\'ll tell you why. I open my arms to everybody. But he never stepped forward for the embrace. So I never really got to know him. I don\'t know anything about him, and it\'s kinda sad.','Shaquille O\'Neal','sad'),(3783,'Dwight is a sad clown. You\'ve seen those paintings of sad clown.','Rainn Wilson','sad'),(3784,'I know what I look like - a weird, sad clown puppet. I\'m fine with that.','Rainn Wilson','sad'),(3785,'It\'s time to say goodbye, but I think goodbyes are sad and I\'d much rather say hello. Hello to a new adventure.','Ernie Harwell','sad'),(3786,'I was very sad to hear of the death of Ronnie Barker, who was such a warm, friendly and encouraging presence to have when I started in television. He was also a great comic actor to learn from.','John Cleese','sad'),(3787,'You know, I think we Indians are afraid to show and celebrate our happiness, lest things change around. But I feel that it\'s okay to be sad and okay to show when you are happy.','Shahrukh Khan','sad'),(3788,'I think as an American society, when we\'re paying too many taxes or dealing with war, we don\'t want to see sad things at the movies.','Zoe Saldana','sad'),(3789,'It\'s a sad day when the leaders of the free world engage in such deception and trickery. I voted against this unnecessary war and will continue to argue that the best way to support our troops is to bring them home.','Major R. Owens','sad'),(3790,'That is sad until one recalls how many bad books the world may yet be spared because of the busyness of writers.','Gore Vidal','sad'),(3791,'We\'ve got people looking at our seamy side and our sad side a lot of the time because that\'s easier. It\'s much more difficult to make a film about happiness with lots of jokes in it.','Emma Thompson','sad'),(3792,'Of course it\'s true: the public want to see young people - young people are the people who go to the cinema. It\'s a sad fact of life, but you\'ve got to accept it and not whine about it.','Joan Collins','sad'),(3793,'I was sad to see anybody leave, we had a very nice family on that show. I was very sad to see momma go, Victoria and especially Linda. My god that was my wife on the show, in fact my wife calls her wife.','Larry Hagman','sad'),(3794,'I always think of the live show first, where the song is gonna go in the show. That\'s why they aren\'t sad songs. When I play, I want to make people happy, not sad. It\'s such a pleasure for me to do what I do, and I want other people to feel some form of that pleasure, too.','Jason Mraz','sad'),(3795,'At that time, I feel sad, and I feel no one knows how hard I work and how many tears. They only know the score. At that time, I feel very lonely because no one understands since they haven\'t been world No. 1 before.','Yani Tseng','sad'),(3796,'But you see, that\'s the gilded prison of fashion. We\'re riding in private jets, and meantime I was so incredibly, painfully sad and lonely.','Janice Dickinson','sad'),(3797,'I happen to be 