ng','sad'),(3860,'No not really, it is just like real life. Not everyday you are happy and not everyday you are sad.','Dakota Fanning','sad'),(3861,'I like everything perfect. Everything has to be neat. My sister is 5, and she\'s more messy than I am. I make my bed every morning, everything\'s perfect. My shoes are all arranged. It\'s sad. I\'m a little like Ray, a little bit.','Dakota Fanning','sad'),(3862,'My little son, Atticus, desperately needs his dad and I haven\'t been there for him... and that\'s sad.','Daniel Baldwin','sad'),(3863,'I love music and musicians. And seeing great artists dropped from labels was really frustrating and sad to me.','Rosanna Arquette','sad'),(3864,'I talked to ex-wives of musicians of the \'70s for research. They\'re the funniest people in the world, yet there is this sad, beautiful thing in their eyes that says they\'ve seen more than they could ever possibly tell you.','Kate Hudson','sad'),(3865,'What happened was very sad. Mr. Lacey told the staff that he was disappointed and appalled that the front of the book was all commentary and that he wanted hard news.','Sydney Schanberg','sad'),(3866,'But probably my favorite music, believe it or not, is sad music.','Walton Goggins','sad'),(3867,'I just want real reactions. I want people to laugh from the gut, be sad from the gut - or get angry from the gut.','Andy Kaufman','sad'),(3868,'It\'s sad when girls think they don\'t have anything going on except being pretty.','Keri Russell','sad'),(3869,'It\'s sad to know I\'m done. But looking back, I\'ve got a lot of great memories.','Bonnie Blair','sad'),(3870,'This Olympics is almost a little sad. It is my final Olympics. There are a lot of good memories.','Bonnie Blair','sad'),(3871,'The day Dick Cheney is going to run for president, I\'ll kill myself. All we need is another liar... I think he\'d like to run, but it would be a sad day for the country if he does.','Helen Thomas','sad'),(3872,'You want people to feel something when you tell a story, whether they feel happy or whether they feel sad.','Harry Dean Stanton','sad'),(3873,'Well, you can\'t be depressed and sad 24 hours a day.','Julia Sweeney','sad'),(3874,'It is sad that the Republican leadership is not as interested as they say they are in protecting the institution of marriage as they are in waging a campaign to divide and distract the American people from the real issues that need to be addressed.','Kendrick Meek','sad'),(3875,'It would be sad if we lost our instinct and our courage to love and protect.','Emeli Sande','sad'),(3876,'I often say the last role I played that really touched me and where I was able to access what I really am was Bonnie, which is kind of sad when you think how early in my career that was.','Faye Dunaway','sad'),(3877,'I had to choose, I\'d be so sad. They are flip sides of the same coin. I love both comedy and drama.','Dianne Wiest','sad'),(3878,'I recently turned down a film that I didn\'t want my kids to see. Priorities shift. Sometimes I\'m sad about that, but not enough to do anything about it.','Dianne Wiest','sad'),(3879,'When you are joyous, look deep into your heart and you shall find it is only that which has given you sorrow that is giving you joy. When you are sorrowful look again in your heart, and you shall see that in truth you are weeping for that which has been your delight.','Khalil Gibran','sad'),(3880,'Every man has his secret sorrows which the world knows not; and often times we call a man cold when he is only sad.','Henry Wadsworth Longfellow','sad'),(3881,'It\'s sad when someone you know becomes someone you knew.','Henry Rollins','sad'),(3882,'If my world were to cave in tomorrow, I would look back on all the pleasures, excitements and worthwhilenesses I have been lucky enough to have had. Not the sadness, not my miscarriages or my father leaving home, but the joy of everything else. It will have been enough.','Audrey Hepburn','sad'),(3883,'Sadness is but a wall between two gardens.','Khalil Gibran','sad'),(3884,'I seldom think about my limitations, and they never make me sad. Perhaps there is just a touch of yearning at times; but it is vague, like a breeze among flowers.','Helen Keller','sad'),(3885,'Affliction comes to us, not to make us sad but sober; not to make us sorry but wise.','H. G. Wells','sad'),(3886,'A sad soul can kill quicker than a germ.','John Steinbeck','sad'),(3887,'Make the most of your regrets; never smother your sorrow, but tend and cherish it till it comes to have a separate and integral interest. To regret deeply is to live afresh.','Henry David Thoreau','sad'),(3888,'Participate joyfully in the sorrows of the world. We cannot cure the world of sorrows, but we can choose to live in joy.','Joseph Campbell','sad'),(3889,'Live by this credo: have a little laugh at life and look around you for happiness instead of sadness. Laughter has always brought me out of unhappy situations.','Red Skelton','sad'),(3890,'I\'ve cried, and you\'d think I\'d be better for it, but the sadness just sleeps, and it stays in my spine the rest of my life.','Conor Oberst','sad'),(3891,'Isn\'t it sad to go to your grave without ever wondering why you were born? Who, with such a thought, would not spring from bed, eager to resume discovering the world and rejoicing to be part of it?','Richard Dawkins','sad'),(3892,'And I remember going to the record studio and there was a park across the street and I\'d see all the children playing and I would cry because it would make me sad that I would have to work instead.','Michael Jackson','sad'),(3893,'The word \'happiness\' would lose its meaning if it were not balanced by sadness.','Carl Jung','sad'),(3894,'The walls we build around us to keep sadness out also keeps out the joy.','Jim Rohn','sad'),(3895,'The tragedy of life is in what dies inside a man while he lives - the death of genuine feeling, the death of inspired response, the awareness that makes it possible to feel the pain or the glory of other men in yourself.','Norman Cousins','sad'),(3896,'I do believe that if you haven\'t learnt about sadness, you cannot appreciate happiness.','Nana Mouskouri','sad'),(3897,'One must not let oneself be overwhelmed by sadness.','Jackie Kennedy','sad'),(3898,'We look before and after, And pine for what is not; Our sincerest laughter With some pain is fraught; Our sweetest songs are those that tell of saddest thought.','Percy Bysshe Shelley','sad'),(3899,'Sad things happen. They do. But we don\'t need to live sad forever.','Mattie Stepanek','sad'),(3900,'Every life has a measure of sorrow, and sometimes this is what awakens us.','Steven Tyler','sad'),(3901,'It is sadder to find the past again and find it inadequate to the present than it is to have it elude you and remain forever a harmonious conception of memory.','F. Scott Fitzgerald','sad'),(3902,'For all sad words of tongue and pen, The saddest are these, \'It might have been\'.','John Greenleaf Whittier','sad'),(3903,'We never taste a perfect joy; our happiest successes are mixed with sadness.','Pierre Corneille','sad'),(3904,'It always makes me sad when I think of how I saw Wagner wasting his vitality, not only by singing their parts to some of his artists, but acting out the smallest details, and of how few they were who were responsive to his wishes.','Anton Seidl','sad'),(3905,'And the sad truth is that nobody wants me to write comedy. The Exorcist not only ended that career, it expunged all memory of its existence.','William Peter Blatty','sad'),(3906,'Film-makers are always going to be interested in making movies that plug into society around them. That\'s what a vibrant, artistically alert community should be doing. After all, it would be sad if we only made films about alien robots.','Mark Boal','sad'),(3907,'What if the Soviet intervention was a blessing in disguise? It saved the myth that if the Soviets were not to intervene, there would have been some flowering authentic democratic socialism and so on. I\'m a little bit more of a pessimist there. I think that the Soviets - it\'s a very sad lesson - by their intervention, saved the myth.','Slavoj Zizek','sad'),(3908,'We all like stories that make us cry. It\'s so nice to feel sad when you\'ve nothing in particular to feel sad about.','Anne Sullivan','sad'),(3909,'The word of God is full of sad and grave counsel, full of the knowledge of God, of examples of virtues, and of correction of vices, of the end of this life, and of the life to come.','John Jewel','sad'),(3910,'I\'ve had moments where I realize my body isn\'t going to withstand many more seasons, but I am very satisfied with my career and I am trying not to look at retirement as a sad thing.','Cat Osterman','sad'),(3911,'I think it\'s a terrible thing to write and not enjoy it. It\'s a sad thing. But of course a lot of people do work because they need to eat. And we all need to eat, but that\'s not the only reason to work. You couldn\'t have paid me not to write.','Anne Perry','sad'),(3912,'I don\'t wanta do any Blues or any sad songs.','Bob Livingston','sad'),(3913,'I just did an interview where I was asked whether I drink beer or whisky, and I was sad to reveal that I\'m pounding spring water.','Brad Delson','sad'),(3914,'It\'s astonishing what some women will put up with just to have a warm body. Some of the brightest women I know are just obsessed with that search. It\'s very sad.','Judith Rossner','sad'),(3915,'I had a vocal coach. It\'s a sad thing, but I had to hire someone so that I could get my Australian accent back.','Anthony LaPaglia','sad'),(3916,'Since it\'s based on my parents, it\'s more emotionally close to me than some of my more surreal plays. And then I like the balance of the comic and the sad. It should play as funny, but you should care about the characters and feel sad for them.','Christopher Durang','sad'),(3917,'Bob summed it up best when he was on his knees at the end of the night saying, \'Don\'t trust in Guided By Voices.\' You were there; was the show awful or something? I know it was sloppy, but they\'re not really that tight anyway, but was it embarrassing, was it sad?','Kim Deal','sad'),(3918,'I love the script and I just thought it was a great role. Like I say, it\'s like this - the script is like this sad, funny, desperate love song to the lost American man.','Oliver Platt','sad'),(3919,'It\'s really sad for me that in the United States the Latino community is losing its culture and language, especially among kids born here - a lot of them can\'t even speak our language.','Romeo Santos','sad'),(3920,'It\'s the sad thing about entertainment, it\'s not always about who is the best.','Jake Roberts','sad'),(3921,'I\'m certainly no victim in this. I don\'t want to come off as a sad sack; I pissed a lot of people off.','Harry Anderson','sad'),(3922,'Why do we capital-N Nerds love Mars so much? Because it\'s beautiful, it\'s tough, it\'s buried in our mythic, childhood memories. It\'s covered with human triumphs but also with sad stories of failure.','Greg Bear','sad'),(3923,'It always made me sad that there were kids who didn\'t have homes.','Lauren Holly','sad'),(3924,'I think it\'s sad that movies and television have caused the theatre to fade as a popular art form. I hope to get young people into the theatre and expose them to Shakespeare.','Kelly McGillis','sad'),(3925,'The world would be a very sad place if readers could only love one story.','Sylvia Day','sad'),(3926,'The sad thing is, when it comes to diet, is that even when well-intentioned Feds try to do right by us, they fail. Either they\'re outvoted by puppets of agribusiness, or they are puppets of agribusiness.','Mark Bittman','sad'),(3927,'It is a sad commentary that today we face a choice between having schools that are a monument to our past - or schools that will be the lifeblood of our future. But since that is our choice, let us resolve to choose wisely.','Ted Kulongoski','sad'),(3928,'One of the reasons I wanted to teach deaf children was because it made me very sad that they spoke so clumsily and that they moved with less grace that I knew was possible of deaf people.','Stephanie Beacham','sad'),(3929,'I\'ve grown as a person. The dynamics on this set are very demanding because we work a lot of hours, it\'s very sad material, so there\'s always someone upset because it\'s really heavy stuff.','Elisabeth Rohm','sad'),(3930,'The South is very beautiful but its beauty makes one sad because the lives that people live here, and have lived here, are so ugly.','James Baldwin','sad'),(3931,'It\'s fun to sing sad songs. And it\'s fun to listen to sad songs. Enjoyable. Satisfying. Something.','Richard Thompson','sad'),(3932,'That\'s what so sad about a lot of modern music, in my opinion, so many young bands never stay around long enough to fulfill their ultimate promise. They only get halfway there or a quarter of the way there.','Alan Vega','sad'),(3933,'It can be really powerful to write something when you\'re sad.','Kathryn Stockett','sad'),(3934,'If you don\'t physically age gracefully, it\'s a bit sad. I think Steven Tyler can get away anything, because he still looks like he did in \'73. Especially from row Z backwards in an arena. As long as the Stones keep their hair and don\'t get fat they\'ll get away with the wrinkles.','Joe Elliott','sad'),(3935,'I\'m proud of my invention, but I\'m sad that it is used by terrorists.','Mikhail Kalashnikov','sad'),(3936,'But I now entered on my fifteenth year - a sad epoch in the life of a slave girl. My master began to whisper foul words in my ear. Young as I was, I could not remain ignorant of their import.','Harriet Ann Jacobs','sad'),(3937,'Since I had the baby I can\'t tolerate anything violent or sad, I saw the Matrix and I had my eyes closed through a lot of it, though I didn\'t need to. I would peek, and then think, oh OK, I can see that.','Lisa Kudrow','sad'),(3938,'What I am sad about is that there is now, in America, no equivalent to the art circuit.','Richard Attenborough','sad'),(3939,'The sad fact is that the same terrorist scenarios, if they occurred in five different States, there could be five different sets of responses to the American people. We need, at a minimum, a level of coordination on communicating threats to the public.','Vito Fossella','sad'),(3940,'If you have ever been in a real tragic or sad situation, the words that come out are hopelessly inadequate and kind of cliched.','Erika Slezak','sad'),(3941,'I know that some endeavor to throw the mantle of romance over the subject and treat woman like some ideal existence, not liable to the ills of life. Let those deal in fancy who have nothing better to deal in; we have to do with sober, sad realities, with stubborn facts.','Ernestine Rose','sad'),(3942,'Of these years nought remains in memory but the sad feeling that we have advanced and only grown older.','Max Muller','sad'),(3943,'His death was the first time that Ed Wynn ever made anyone sad.','Red Skelton','sad'),(3944,'They\'re not willing to admit that I\'ve also shed blood and tears and often paid dearly for my success. This makes me feel extremely sad.','Zhang Ziyi','sad'),(3945,'I love playing football, being out on the pitch with a ball, and I will be a little sad when that ends.','Dennis Bergkamp','sad'),(3946,'I would be sad if it ended now. It\'s been the best job I\'ve had by a long shot, especially creatively because the writing is so good. Every week I get the script and I laugh out loud and get excited for the different stuff we get to do.','Sarah Chalke','sad'),(3947,'It\'s very simple, I just tell my sad story, and people weep.','Corazon Aquino','sad'),(3948,'I am sure that the sad days and happenings were rare, and that I lived the joyous and careless life of other children; but just because the happy days were so habitual to me they made no impression upon my mind, and I can no longer recall them.','Pierre Loti','sad'),(3949,'I\'ve been looking forward to doing an album, but it\'s really sad to see how many doors have been closed because of the gay thing. I thought it was about the music.','Jai Rodriguez','sad'),(3950,'I think he Oswald felt he was a failure and for the United States and for President Kennedy and all of us. He knew he was a failure at everything he tried, frustrated, with a very sad life, but he was a Marxist.','John Sherman Cooper','sad'),(3951,'When I was in Paris, all of the German refugees began to flow in and it was a very sad time.','Elliott Carter','sad'),(3952,'It is easy enough to praise men for the courage of their convictions. I wish I could teach the sad young of this mealy generation the courage of their confusions.','John Ciardi','sad'),(3953,'My lasting impression of Truman Capote is that he was a terribly gentle, terribly sensitive, and terribly sad man.','Alvin Ailey','sad'),(3954,'I was always depressed growing up. There wasn\'t a reason for it, I just was. I was sad and morose. I cried a lot, I wrote a lot, and I read a lot; and that was how I dealt with it.','Amanda Hocking','sad'),(3955,'There is the glamour side of it, which allows you to meet great variety of people with whom you simply can have a good time, but there\'s also the sad side of it that drags you into a superficial and artificial world.','Karolina Kurkova','sad'),(3956,'I didn\'t know my mother had it. I think a lot of women don\'t know their mothers had it; that\'s the sad thing about depression. You know, you don\'t function anymore. You shut down. You feel like you are in a void.','Marie Osmond','sad'),(3957,'It can make you sad to look at pictures from your youth. So there\'s a trick to it. The trick is not to look at the later pictures.','Jerry Stiller','sad'),(3958,'\'The Killing\' has a really great combination of qualities: Even though it\'s very sad and deals with mourning and grief, it\'s still exciting. It\'s about real people and it doesn\'t shy from the painful points of life.','Joel Kinnaman','sad'),(3959,'You see so many artists who are so talented end up living sad, empty lives. This industry takes so much out of you that without the accountability and leaving God in the center, you can be left so empty and void.','Stacie Orrico','sad'),(3960,'I\'ve been getting into Nick Drake lately, the folk singer. Sad, gorgeous stuff.','Anthony Doerr','sad'),(3961,'I have been to several wars to draw. I went to Vietnam. And made drawings in Vietnam during that period of the war there, and found that to be a very very sad situation.','Gerald Scarfe','sad'),(3962,'So war is an extremely sad business, because the majority of people don\'t want to be in it.','Gerald Scarfe','sad'),(3963,'Football is a sad game.','George Best','sad'),(3964,'All the things that happen to people in the industry today, the actors, what they have to put up with, all the people wanting to know every single moment of their lives - I think it\'s really sad.','Tab Hunter','sad'),(3965,'It was sad when Sid Vicious died... I was freaked out when Phil Lynott died from Thin Lizzy. I cried. It was too crazy.','Dee Dee Ramone','sad'),(3966,'Don\'t Cry Daddy is a pretty sad song. He got to the end of it and it was just real quiet and Elvis says, I\'m gonna cut that someday for my daddy. And, by God, he did. He lived up to his word.','Mac Davis','sad'),(3967,'It\'s a sad day when a cartoon is doing more and cares more and pays more attention to the environment than our president.','Kathy Najimy','sad'),(3968,'I think when I\'m in love, I really am very good with calling, little faxes, and visiting and I really put a lot of effort into it. I\'m really not the one that\'s not available because of work and I\'m very sad when I actually leave.','Franka Potente','sad'),(3969,'The books are funny and sad, and that\'s what people respond to.','Paula Danziger','sad'),(3970,'It\'s sad - it\'s sad for us old enough to remember when directors ruled, and films were substantially better than they are today. But it\'s hard to argue with those kinds of grosses.','Mark Rydell','sad'),(3971,'I used to sit near Marilyn Monroe in the Actor\'s Studio. She\'d get dressed up because that was her identity. Sad. Those cameras wouldn\'t leave her alone. She didn\'t know where to hide.','Doris Roberts','sad'),(3972,'The day you think there is no improvements to be made is a sad one for any player.','Lionel Messi','sad'),(3973,'I\'m sad and blue, about nobody but you. I told you that I loved you right from the start, you told me the same and now you try to break my little heart.','Leon Redbone','sad'),(3974,'Though I know he loves me, tonight my heart is sad; his kiss was not so wonderful as all the dreams I had.','Sara Teasdale','sad'),(3975,'Nothing is more sad than the death of an illusion.','Arthur Koestler','sad'),(3976,'My childhood, I would say, was a bit sad.','Columba Bush','sad'),(3977,'My childhood, I would say, was a bit sad. Society resents that.','Columba Bush','sad'),(3978,'One of the sad things about contemporary journalism is that it actually matters very little. The world now is almost inured to the power of journalism. The best journalism would manage to outrage people. And people are less and less inclined to outrage.','David Simon','sad'),(3979,'If I can procure three hundred good substantial names of persons, or bodies, or institutions, I cannot fail to do well for my family, although I must abandon my life to its success, and undergo many sad perplexities and perhaps never see again my own beloved America.','John James Audubon','sad'),(3980,'Informed by our sad experience of history, we require nothing short of a foundation for lasting democracy.','Ibrahim Babangida','sad'),(3981,'It\'s sad that we have become so accustomed to bad service that we\'re shocked when we get good service.','Neil Cavuto','sad'),(3982,'I am co-writing a screenplay now and I\'m working on the rights to another story I want to do. So I plan to produce and direct. So, for me, I don\'t really feel that I am vulnerable to that sad baggage that comes with the business of filmmaking.','Kerry Washington','sad'),(3983,'Deep down, I reckon the sweetest moment will come when it\'s finally all over. When, at last, I know that I can stop fighting. Of course it\'ll also be a little sad. The sweetest moments, y\'know, always come with just a little sadness.','Evander Holyfield','sad'),(3984,'\'Vegas\' was something very close to me. I had such a blast doing that. I\'m still a little upset that we never really got to shoot that final episode. So many people were invested in it. I\'ll always be sad about that.','Josh Duhamel','sad'),(3985,'I can\'t say I\'m happy to be talking about John Ritter and his passing. In my 21 years of Entertainment Tonight, this really was one of the most shocking and sad things to have happened.','Mary Hart','sad'),(3986,'When I was in Philadelphia during the Depression in 1930 or \'31, I got a very sad job as a night watchman in a garage. The cars in the garage had been abandoned by their owners, since they had lost their jobs and couldn\'t keep up the payments.','Tom Glazer','sad'),(3987,'I mean, that\'s a sad day in America when you\'re recalled because you did what you said you were going to do, and the public voted you in to do that.','Russell Pearce','sad'),(3988,'It would be sad if my best work had been 20 years ago and now I only had memories.','Demian Bichir','sad'),(3989,'There\'s all this stuff that is happening in Edinburgh now, it\'s a sad attempt to create an Edinburgh society, similar to a London society, a highbrow literature celebrity society.','Irvine Welsh','sad'),(3990,'I so desperately hate to end these movies that the first thing I do when I\'m done is write another one. Then I don\'t feel sad about having to leave and everybody going away.','John Hughes','sad'),(3991,'I think I have a dark view of the world. I have to make everything funny, otherwise it all seems so sad.','Moon Unit Zappa','sad'),(3992,'With out art, without communicating, we wouldn\'t live beyond 30 because we\'d be so sad and depressed.','Wayne Coyne','sad'),(3993,'This was an important part of my life. But it was also sad that we didn\'t play there, cause we had such alot of fans that were waiting for us and Brazilians are great people. It\'s now my second home.','Jim Capaldi','sad'),(3994,'It\'s sad and upsetting when you see somebody crying hysterically, but at the same time it\'s real funny.','Seth Green','sad'),(3995,'To complain now would be kind of sad. I like the way things are going.','Josh Brolin','sad'),(3996,'The sad events that occur in my life are the sad events that happen to everybody, with losing friends and family, but that is a natural occurrence, as natural as being born.','Sergio Aragones','sad'),(3997,'I\'ve got so much to do, I don\'t have time to sit down and be sad.','Norma McCorvey','sad'),(3998,'Some really good things kind of swing both ways and I like to see people that can swing really, really, really sad and horrible and terrible and really, really, really beautiful and funny.','Beth Henley','sad'),(3999,'What I loved about the acting class was that you got to think all day long about a person that wasn\'t you, and figure out why they were sad and what they wanted, what they dreamed.','Beth Henley','sad'),(4000,'Next to a lost battle, nothing is so sad as a battle that has been won.','Arthur Wellesley','sad'),(4001,'It is very sad for a man to make himself servant to a single thing; his manhood all taken out of him by the hydraulic pressure of excessive business.','Theodore Parker','sad'),(4002,'You put a song on the record or on tape and you stop singing it. You just don\'t sit around and sing it anymore unless you\'re performing. That\'s kind of sad.','Rick Danko','sad'),(4003,'You\'ve got a beautiful country with so many beautiful people and so many beautiful things happening and stuff like that lets it down. I feel sad for them.','Robbie Williams','sad'),(4004,'If you win all the time, you lose the drama in life. To make the happy moments happy, you need the sad moments too.','Doug Davidson','sad'),(4005,'In LA, I mean, here\'s this place full of desperate and sad people who take their only pleasure from destroying others for the purposes of their own self-aggrandizement.','Heather Donahue','sad'),(4006,'A lot of our entertainment throws into detail the stagnation and illness of how we live today-it\'s sad and it\'s sick... and it\'s profitable.','Heather Donahue','sad'),(4007,'I like \'Bewitched\' off the first album because it\'s one of the happiest songs I\'ve ever written and, as any writer will tell you, happy songs are a million times more difficult to write than sad songs.','Malcolm Wilson','sad'),(4008,'I probably have the worst wardrobe. It\'s the most ill-fitting with the worst patterns and colors and the most nipple rubbage. There\'s bad chafing, and it\'s always tight in all the wrong places. What\'s sad is that I\'m kinda getting used to it.','Josh Hopkins','sad'),(4009,'I think that the Information Age is great, but there\'s a downside to it obviously as well, and it\'s that false information can be perpetuated so quickly. And it\'s sad that so many people will believe it.','Josh Hopkins','sad'),(4010,'A marriage is no amusement but a solemn act, and generally a sad one.','Queen Victoria','sad'),(4011,'Well, I did Marlene 15 years ago and that\'s in the style. It\'s somehow similar and not similar because Marlene was much more aggressive, funny and sad.','Maximilian Schell','sad'),(4012,'Scientology is probably one of the most misunderstood things, and it\'s sad that it\'s so misunderstood.','Stanley Clarke','sad'),(4013,'I think it\'s sad to me that I had to make a decision to not play the game that I feel like I\'m best at and that I love. But if it was just about the game itself, I\'d be there in a heartbeat. But that\'s not how the real world works.','Tiffeny Milbrett','sad'),(4014,'I don\'t know how the poor farmers deal with such situations in real life. It\'s really sad.','Sanjay Dutt','sad'),(4015,'I\'m convinced I got signed because of who I am. And it makes me sad.','Jeff Buckley','sad'),(4016,'I am not a sad clown. I am not a sad clown.','Nathan Lane','sad'),(4017,'I think that the majority of messages are validating messages to confirm the survival of conscious. And many times that validation message is negative or sad.','John Edward','sad'),(4018,'Nolan has the strangest affect on people. You know, I think there\'s something very sad and little boy about him, but at the same time the way he goes about everything is so awkward and obnoxious. He can never say the right thing, you know? And I think if he just didn\'t try so hard and calmed down, people might actually like him a bit more!','Gabriel Mann','sad'),(4019,'I mean, I was just one of the ones who got exposed, and because of the position I was in, where I was in my life, it went mainstream. A lot of people got out of it after my situation, not because I went to prison but because it was sad for them to see me go through something that was so pointless, that could have been avoided.','Michael Vick','sad'),(4020,'I would never have become music director of the Chicago Symphony, which would have been an extremely sad loss.','Georg Solti','sad'),(4021,'I was so sad from losing two of my dogs and my mother. I had this vision of all these animals sitting behind bars. They had no control and were scared. That\'s why I got into fostering and adopting animals out.','Linda Blair','sad'),(4022,'When I was leaving I kind of felt a little bit sad, because I made some friends down in skid row.','Pras Michel','sad'),(4023,'I only really watch sport. That\'s where you see real joy. I don\'t like watching much else on TV, because it\'s generally either twisted or sad.','Roger Milla','sad'),(4024,'I wanted to be a dancer my whole life. And when I gave it up to act, I always had a really sad part of myself that missed it and missed performing and missed