k of losing one\'s home.','Harry Connick, Jr.','sad'),(4165,'It is sad to grow old but nice to ripen.','Brigitte Bardot','sad'),(4166,'Crying is cleansing. There\'s a reason for tears, happiness or sadness.','Dionne Warwick','sad'),(4167,'Heavy hearts, like heavy clouds in the sky, are best relieved by the letting of a little water.','Christopher Morley','sad'),(4168,'You get used to sadness, growing up in the mountains, I guess.','Loretta Lynn','sad'),(4169,'The reason for the sadness of this modern age and the men who live in it is that it looks for the truth in everything and finds it.','Edmond de Goncourt','sad'),(4170,'Your joys and sorrows. You can never tell them. You cheapen the inside of yourself if you do tell them.','Greta Garbo','sad'),(4171,'Sad will be the day for any man when he becomes contented with the thoughts he is thinking and the deeds he is doing - where there is not forever beating at the doors of his soul some great desire to do something larger; which he knows he was meant and made to do.','Phillips Brooks','sad'),(4172,'What else does anxiety about the future bring you but sorrow upon sorrow?','Thomas a Kempis','sad'),(4173,'Time takes away the grief of men.','Desiderius Erasmus','sad'),(4174,'Sorrows are like thunderclouds, in the distance they look black, over our heads scarcely gray.','Jean Paul','sad'),(4175,'The saddest thing that befalls a soul Is when it loses faith in God and woman.','Alexander Smith','sad'),(4176,'God is in the sadness and the laughter, in the bitter and the sweet.','Neale Donald Walsch','sad'),(4177,'We tell our triumphs to the crowds, but our own hearts are the sole confidants of our sorrows.','Edward G. Bulwer-Lytton','sad'),(4178,'Those who gave away their wings are sad not to see them fly.','Antonio Porchia','sad'),(4179,'Actually, the moment of victory is wonderful, but also sad. It means that your trip is ended.','Bill Toomey','sad'),(4180,'Every human walks around with a certain kind of sadness. They may not wear it on their sleeves, but it\'s there if you look deep.','Taraji P. Henson','sad'),(4181,'Nobody understands another\'s sorrow, and nobody another\'s joy.','Franz Schubert','sad'),(4182,'First, accept sadness. Realize that without losing, winning isn\'t so great.','Alyssa Milano','sad'),(4183,'I had sadness for breakfast.','Andy Milonakis','sad'),(4184,'Red is the ultimate cure for sadness.','Bill Blass','sad'),(4185,'They say it\'s better to bury your sadness in a graveyard or garden that waits for the spring to wake from its sleep and burst into green.','Conor Oberst','sad'),(4186,'Sadness is also a kind of defence.','Ivo Andric','sad'),(4187,'One should either be sad or joyful. Contentment is a warm sty for eaters and sleepers.','Eugene O\'Neill','sad'),(4188,'You have to let it all hang out, let go of the ideas that were more comfortable and embrace some of the sadness in your life.','Madeleine Peyroux','sad'),(4189,'Everything\'s complicated, even those things that seem flat in their bleakness or sadness.','Nick Hornby','sad'),(4190,'The excursion is the same when you go looking for your sorrow as when you go looking for your joy.','Eudora Welty','sad'),(4191,'I don\'t have many sad days.','Billy Graham','sad'),(4192,'War is very sad and small life is pathetically fragile at times.','Henry Rollins','sad'),(4193,'A lot of sad stories in a row - that wears on you.','Elizabeth Edwards','sad'),(4194,'Among the reasons people keep sad stories to themselves is that they do not want anyone to feel sorry for them. I don\'t. I don\'t want you to feel sorry for me.','Judith Moore','sad'),(4195,'I\'ve got to be high class... Which is sad, because I like bars.','Daniel Craig','sad'),(4196,'The sad thing is that I feel so boring because \'Twilight\' is literally how every conversation I have these days begins - whether it\'s someone I\'m meeting for the first time or someone I just haven\'t seen in a while. The first thing I want to say to them is, \'It\'s insane! And, as a person, I can\'t do anything!\'','Kristen Stewart','sad'),(4197,'There\'s never been a culture that wasn\'t obsessed with food. The sort of sad thing is that our obsession is no longer with food, but with the price of food.','Jonathan Safran Foer','sad'),(4198,'Our religion is itself profoundly sad - a religion of universal anguish, and one which, because of its very catholicity, grants full liberty to the individual and asks no better than to be celebrated in each man\'s own language - so long as he knows anguish and is a painter.','Charles Baudelaire','sad'),(4199,'I have a piece of great and sad news to tell you: I am dead.','Jean Cocteau','sad'),(4200,'I was a very good girl for a long time, that\'s what really drew me to acting. The stage was the perfect place to be outrageous, to be sad, to be angry, to be all these different things.','Joan Allen','sad'),(4201,'It is a sad commentary of our times when our young must seek advice and counsel from \"Dear Abby\" instead of going to Mom and Dad.','Abigail Van Buren','sad'),(4202,'It\'s much easier to write when you\'re sad. But you can end up isolated and depressed because you almost need to put yourself in that situation to have that angst to write from.','Natalie Imbruglia','sad'),(4203,'I\'ll always be sad that my marriage ended.','Shania Twain','sad'),(4204,'For my wrap present, Colin Farrell gave me a first edition book. I got so involved with this character and I was so sad when the movie was over that when I got home and I tried to read the book I got really emotional and I started crying.','Salma Hayek','sad'),(4205,'When you\'re going through something, whether it\'s a wonderful thing like having a child or a sad thing like losing somebody, you often feel like \'Oh my God, I\'m so overwhelmed; I\'m dealing with this huge thing on my own.\' In fact, poetry\'s a nice reminder that, no, everybody goes through it. These are universal experiences.','Caroline Kennedy','sad'),(4206,'But I\'m not like sad, depressed miserable person. I guess sometimes I give off that impression.','Edward Furlong','sad'),(4207,'There were points in my life where I felt oddly irresistible to women. I\'m not in that state now and that makes me sad.','Jack Nicholson','sad'),(4208,'I think I would be very sad if I wasn\'t able to have a baby.','Nicole Kidman','sad'),(4209,'The monarchy is foremost a business, and it\'s important to them that the British public continue to finance the excessive luxurious lifestyles of the now quite enormous, wasteful and useless \'royal\' family. I find it very sad.','Steven Patrick Morrissey','sad'),(4210,'What I really tried to do with Helen was make her show this sad side of her. She was married off at 16, was so young and living in this castle that can\'t leave because of how she looks, and married to a man she hates and three times her age.','Diane Kruger','sad'),(4211,'You can\'t have an up without a down, a right without a left, a back without a front - or a happy without a sad.','Harlan Coben','sad'),(4212,'I would love to be married. But it\'s not a necessity like the way that I feel I need and want to have children. It would be wonderful to have a husband, and I would feel blessed to do it. But I would feel sad for the rest of my life if I had no kids.','Mindy Kaling','sad'),(4213,'I don\'t know what to say to that, but I have to agree with Johnny that, yeah, we do touch upon things that most men would rather not admit: That we feel pain, we cry, get sad and sometimes don\'t deal well with disappointment.','Peter Steele','sad'),(4214,'Acting gave me the opportunity to do outrageous things. It allowed me to be sad, happy, angry and lustful, even if it was just vicariously.','Joan Allen','sad'),(4215,'At a time when 2500 American soldiers have given their lives for the cause of bringing democracy to Iraq, it is sad and frustrating to watch the Republican establishment disgrace the exercise of democracy in our own House of Representatives.','Earl Blumenauer','sad'),(4216,'It\'s a sad fact about our culture that a poet can earn much more money writing or talking about his art than he can by practicing it.','W. H. Auden','sad'),(4217,'I think it is really sad that when people lose their homes they kind of lose their minds too.','Margaret Cho','sad'),(4218,'The \'80s were fabulous. The \'90s sucked, and the \'70s were just a sad, sad time in human history. Go 1980s! There\'s something that\'s just so cute about that time. And not just yellow nail polish and \'I\'m a loner.\'','Jennifer Sky','sad'),(4219,'I was sad that Corpse Bride was so short. I would\'ve liked to have had her around for way longer. She doesn\'t actually have that many scenes.','Helena Bonham Carter','sad'),(4220,'As a writer, or as a filmmaker, you have to present yourself, and part of what yourself is is what you\'re interested in, or what you think is funny, or what you think is sad, or what you think is horrible.','Charlie Kaufman','sad'),(4221,'You know, why at the end of your life should you assemble thousands of pages of \'Why am I so sad, why am I so depressed?\' Instead, assemble thousands of pages of why you\'re so content.','Elizabeth Gilbert','sad'),(4222,'As somebody who, in my second marriage, insisted on a prenuptial agreement, I can also testify that sometimes it is an act of love to chart the exit strategy before you enter the union, in order to make sure that not only you, but your partner as well, knows that there will be no World War III should hearts and minds, for any sad reason, change.','Elizabeth Gilbert','sad'),(4223,'It\'s sad that the most glorious of sexual experiences can make us feel guilty, ashamed, embarrassed, and abnormal.','Sue Johanson','sad'),(4224,'The funny thing is I\'m not bothered or sad about being on my own - after all I\'ve never had a husband.','Francesca Annis','sad'),(4225,'With my schedule being so crazy, I can\'t call every day or hang out with my friends like I used to and that\'s definitely sad.','Jordin Sparks','sad'),(4226,'My comedy is for children from three to 93. You do need a slightly childish sense of humour and if you haven\'t got that, it\'s very sad.','Norman Wisdom','sad'),(4227,'I remember a time when all my fans were crying and sad and going through hell. Now, we\'re trying to uplift each other and accept ourselves for who we are, even if nobody else does.','Mary J. Blige','sad'),(4228,'The attacks on the World Trade Center and the Pentagon shook our nation to the core. Americans were deeply frightened, sad, and angry, and they rallied around a President who, at the time, showed impressive certitude and calm.','Eliot Spitzer','sad'),(4229,'The sad duty of politics is to establish justice in a sinful world.','Reinhold Niebuhr','sad'),(4230,'Watergate provides a model case study of the interaction and powers of each of the branches of government. It also is a morality play with a sad and dramatic ending.','Bob Woodward','sad'),(4231,'I was at the Olympic Games winning medals and I still doubted my image. I doubted what I looked like. That\'s sad.','Shawn Johnson','sad'),(4232,'People say you should read your criticism because it will make you a better person but it doesn\'t. It just makes you a sad bitter old showbiz nightmare.','Jo Brand','sad'),(4233,'It is sad to see a woman sacrificing the ties of the affections even to do good.','Maria Mitchell','sad'),(4234,'My dad was a homicide cop in the gay neighborhood in the city when gay neighborhoods were desperate, depressing, sad places run by the mob. The only gay people he\'d met when I came out to him were corpses.','Dan Savage','sad'),(4235,'As a songwriter I hate this whole, \'If it\'s a sad song, it has to sound like a sad song thing.\' And that goes all the way back to my days with the Format. I\'m an insane narcissist, so if I have to get something off my chest, I\'ll get something off my chest.','Nate Ruess','sad'),(4236,'Well the country songs themselves are three-chord stories, ballads which are mostly sad. If you are already feeling sorry for yourself when you listen to them they will take you to an even sadder place.','Willie Nelson','sad'),(4237,'I do not take steroids. I never have. It\'s sad to me that people want to point fingers. I don\'t do that. That\'s not me. I wouldn\'t feel like a human being.','Jackie Joyner-Kersee','sad'),(4238,'I\'ve met so many fans of daytime television who\'ve watched the shows with their moms and grandmas and feel like they\'ve known the characters their whole lives. It\'s sad for them to have to say goodbye to their favorite soaps and characters. We don\'t want that to happen to the \'Days\' fans.','Alison Sweeney','sad'),(4239,'I\'m not sad at all about turning 40.','Halle Berry','sad'),(4240,'Morality comes with the sad wisdom of age, when the sense of curiosity has withered.','Graham Greene','sad'),(4241,'Nobody wants to hear R&B. It\'s sad. If you want to be on the radio you got to stay young.','Jamie Foxx','sad'),(4242,'Marketing has supplanted story as the primary force behind the worthiness of making a film, and that\'s a very sad thing. It\'s film only as a function of consumerism rather than as an important component of our culture, and that\'s everywhere around the world.','Alexander Payne','sad'),(4243,'The question I love to get asked is: \'What\'s the hardest part of your job?\' And literally, the answer is probably real sad, but it\'s to just to be me. Like, it\'s really hard, because I think people, you know, have a set idea of what a pop star should be.','Kelly Clarkson','sad'),(4244,'The best quality about Kobe Bryant? You want me to be honest? I don\'t know. I\'ll tell you why. I open my arms to everybody. But he never stepped forward for the embrace. So I never really got to know him. I don\'t know anything about him, and it\'s kinda sad.','Shaquille O\'Neal','sad'),(4245,'Dwight is a sad clown. You\'ve seen those paintings of sad clown.','Rainn Wilson','sad'),(4246,'I know what I look 