nd three times her age.','Diane Kruger','sad'),(4623,'You can\'t have an up without a down, a right without a left, a back without a front - or a happy without a sad.','Harlan Coben','sad'),(4624,'I would love to be married. But it\'s not a necessity like the way that I feel I need and want to have children. It would be wonderful to have a husband, and I would feel blessed to do it. But I would feel sad for the rest of my life if I had no kids.','Mindy Kaling','sad'),(4625,'I don\'t know what to say to that, but I have to agree with Johnny that, yeah, we do touch upon things that most men would rather not admit: That we feel pain, we cry, get sad and sometimes don\'t deal well with disappointment.','Peter Steele','sad'),(4626,'Acting gave me the opportunity to do outrageous things. It allowed me to be sad, happy, angry and lustful, even if it was just vicariously.','Joan Allen','sad'),(4627,'At a time when 2500 American soldiers have given their lives for the cause of bringing democracy to Iraq, it is sad and frustrating to watch the Republican establishment disgrace the exercise of democracy in our own House of Representatives.','Earl Blumenauer','sad'),(4628,'Good humor is the health of the soul, sadness is its poison.','Lord Chesterfield','sad'),(4629,'It\'s a sad man my friend who\'s livin\' in his own skin and can\'t stand the company.','Bruce Springsteen','sad'),(4630,'We\'re taught to be ashamed of confusion, anger, fear and sadness, and to me they\'re of equal value to happiness, excitement and inspiration.','Alanis Morissette','sad'),(4631,'I can see the humorous side of things and enjoy the fun when it comes; but look where I will, there seems to me always more sadness than joy in life.','Jerome K. Jerome','sad'),(4632,'Can I see another\'s woe, and not be in sorrow too? Can I see another\'s grief, and not seek for kind relief?','William Blake','sad'),(4633,'Do not make best friends with a melancholy sad soul. They always are heavily loaded, and you must b