ean King','sad'),(4752,'Just because I\'m talking about something that might have been a sad or painful situation doesn\'t mean that I\'m sad or tortured 24 hours a day any more than anybody else is.','Lucinda Williams','sad'),(4753,'When you are joyous, look deep into your heart and you shall find it is only that which has given you sorrow that is giving you joy. When you are sorrowful look again in your heart, and you shall see that in truth you are weeping for that which has been your delight.','Khalil Gibran','sad'),(4754,'Every man has his secret sorrows which the world knows not; and often times we call a man cold when he is only sad.','Henry Wadsworth Longfellow','sad'),(4755,'It\'s sad when someone you know becomes someone you knew.','Henry Rollins','sad'),(4756,'If my world were to cave in tomorrow, I would look back on all the pleasures, excitements and worthwhilenesses I have been lucky enough to have had. Not the sadness, not my miscarriages or my father leaving home, but the joy of everything else. It will have been enough.','Audrey Hepburn','sad'),(4757,'Sadness is but a wall between two gardens.','Khalil Gibran','sad'),(4758,'I seldom think about my limitations, and they never make me sad. Perhaps there is just a touch of yearning at times; but it is vague, like a breeze among flowers.','Helen Keller','sad'),(4759,'Affliction comes to us, not to make us sad but sober; not to make us sorry but wise.','H. G. Wells','sad'),(4760,'A sad soul can kill quicker than a germ.','John Steinbeck','sad'),(4761,'Make the most of your regrets; never smother your sorrow, but tend and cherish it till it comes to have a separate and integral interest. To regret deeply is to live afresh.','Henry David Thoreau','sad'),(4762,'Participate joyfully in the sorrows of the world. We cannot cure the world of sorrows, but we can choose to live in joy.','Joseph Campbell','sad'),(4763,'Live by this credo: have a little laugh at life and look around you for happiness instead of sadness. Laughter has always brought me out of unhappy situations.','Red Skelton','sad'),(4764,'I\'ve cried, and you\'d think I\'d be better for it, but the sadness just sleeps, and it stays in my spine the rest of my life.','Conor Oberst','sad'),(4765,'Isn\'t it sad to go to your grave without ever wondering why you were born? Who, with such a thought, would not spring from bed, eager to resume discovering the world and rejoicing to be part of it?','Richard Dawkins','sad'),(4766,'And I remember going to the record studio and there was a park across the street and I\'d see all the children playing and I would cry because it would make me sad that I would have to work instead.','Michael Jackson','sad'),(4767,'The word \'happiness\' would lose its meaning if it were not balanced by sadness.','Carl Jung','sad'),(4768,'The walls we build around us to keep sadness out also keeps out the joy.','Jim Rohn','sad'),(4769,'The tragedy of life is in what dies inside a man while he lives - the death of genuine feeling, the death of inspired response, the awareness that makes it possible to feel the pain or the glory of other men in yourself.','Norman Cousins','sad'),(4770,'I do believe that if you haven\'t learnt about sadness, you cannot appreciate happiness.','Nana Mouskouri','sad'),(4771,'One must not let oneself be overwhelmed by sadness.','Jackie Kennedy','sad'),(4772,'We look before and after, And pine for what is not; Our sincerest laughter With some pain is fraught; Our sweetest songs are those that tell of saddest thought.','Percy Bysshe Shelley','sad'),(4773,'Sad things happen. They do. But we don\'t need to live sad forever.','Mattie Stepanek','sad'),(4774,'Every life has a measure of sorrow, and sometimes this is what awakens us.','Steven Tyler','sad'),(4775,'It is sadder to find the past again and find it inadequate to the present than it is to have it elude you and remain forever a harmonious conception of memory.','F. Scott Fitzgerald','sad'),(4776,'For all sad words