ks around with a certain kind of sadness. They may not wear it on their sleeves, but it\'s there if you look deep.','Taraji P. Henson','sad'),(5330,'Nobody understands another\'s sorrow, and nobody another\'s joy.','Franz Schubert','sad'),(5331,'First, accept sadness. Realize that without losing, winning isn\'t so great.','Alyssa Milano','sad'),(5332,'I had sadness for breakfast.','Andy Milonakis','sad'),(5333,'Red is the ultimate cure for sadness.','Bill Blass','sad'),(5334,'They say it\'s better to bury your sadness in a graveyard or garden that waits for the spring to wake from its sleep and burst into green.','Conor Oberst','sad'),(5335,'Sadness is also a kind of defence.','Ivo Andric','sad'),(5336,'One should either be sad or joyful. Contentment is a warm sty for eaters and sleepers.','Eugene O\'Neill','sad'),(5337,'You have to let it all hang out, let go of the ideas that were more comfortable and embrace some of the sadness in your life.','Madeleine Peyroux','sad'),(5338,'Everything\'s complicated, even those things that seem flat in their bleakness or sadness.','Nick Hornby','sad'),(5339,'The excursion is the same when you go looking for your sorrow as when you go looking for your joy.','Eudora Welty','sad'),(5340,'I\'ve been on Prozac for 12 years and I\'m off it now. I know what it feels like to be excited and sad again. I haven\'t felt like this in 12 years; I\'m like a giddy little kid.','Jonathan Davis','sad'),(5341,'Whenever the lion fish in the fish tank in the captain\'s ready room died it was always a sad moment.','Patrick Stewart','sad'),(5342,'To the indefinite, uncertain mind of the American radical the most contradictory ideas and methods are possible. The result is a sad chaos in the radical movement, a sort of intellectual hash, which has neither taste nor character.','Emma Goldman','sad'),(5343,'Ladies and gentlemen, it is with great sadness that I announce that I will resign as Australia\'s Minister for Foreign Affairs. I am sad because I love this job. I\'m totally dedicated to the work that we are doing in Australia\'s name around the world, and I believe that we have achieved many good results for Australia, and I\'m proud of them.','Kevin Rudd','sad'),(5344,'You know how sad your life is when you know the release date of DVDs.','Heston Blumenthal','sad'),(5345,'It makes me so desperately sad to witness just how unforgivably wretched our world has become.','Ralph Steadman','sad'),(5346,'We\'re sad about some of the losses of members of great seniority and distinction in the Congress, and some very new members, who will no longer be serving with us.','Nancy Pelosi','sad'),(5347,'All he cares about is going out there with his Jack Daniels bottle. Nothing has changed. That\'s kind of sad. If David was doing better than he used to be, then that would be different. But it was a joke and he made it that way.','Sammy Hagar','sad'),(5348,'People say, oh it\'s a shame, you\'re not nostalgic about the \'60s. Well actually, it\'s quite good, when you think of it. Wouldn\'t it be sad if I was sitting here wishing it back?','Robert Wyatt','sad'),(5349,'Divorce was very sad, obviously, but now I\'ve gotten over it.','Natalie Imbruglia','sad'),(5350,'I like singer-songwriters, and I find sad songs comforting rather than depressing. It makes you realise you\'re not alone in the world.','Natalie Imbruglia','sad'),(5351,'I have had stalkers over the years. The police deal with it but it is very scary. One man kept turning up where we filmed \'Countdown in Leeds,\' which was scary. It was sad as he\'d been sectioned and thought I was talking to him through the TV.','Carol Vorderman','sad'),(5352,'\'The Taxi Ride,\' from my second album, is one people want to hear a lot. I\'m consciously trying to walk on the sunny side of the street, to really lift myself into a place of greater positivity, and that\'s a sad song.','Jane Siberry','sad'),(5353,'I find it amusing on one level, poignant on another, when people try to get recognition from an outside source. It\'s sad.','Grace Slick','sad'),(5354,'Ideally, I would love to mix singing and acting, but you can only be a pop star for so many years. I mean, at 30 it\'s a little bit sad, right?','Rachel Stevens','sad'),(5355,'I think a lot of people think that my parents\' deaths is why I write such sad songs, but that\'s not true. Those songs may just be the woman I am.','Shelby Lynne','sad'),(5356,'I\'m sad to see the passing of the great drug warriors. I certainly did my part in that battle and I don\'t regret any of it.','Marc Maron','sad'),(5357,'As virtuous men pass mildly away, and whisper to their souls to go, whilst some of their sad friends do say, the breath goes now, and some say no.','John Donne','sad'),(5358,'It\'s incredible that they censor films. It\'s sad.','Dario Argento','sad'),(5359,'I\'ve always been drawn to Marilyn Monroe, but certain aspects of her story may be too sad to tell.','Sherilyn Fenn','sad'),(5360,'My mother sent me to psychiatrists since the age of four because she didn\'t think little boys should be sad. When my brother was born, I stared out the window for days. Can you imagine that?','Andy Kaufman','sad'),(5361,'Even modern English people are imperious, superior, ridden by class. All of the hypocrisy and the difficulties that are endemic in being British also make it an incredibly fertile place culturally. A brilliant place to live. Sad but true.','Pete Townshend','sad'),(5362,'It\'s sad when people break up.','Pete Townshend','sad'),(5363,'I feel quite sad for the young musicians coming up because they may never get to pay their rent properly. It doesn\'t matter what the genre; nowadays, it\'s so much harder than it ever was.','Bryan Adams','sad'),(5364,'I\'ve never thought of my characters as being sad. On the contrary, they are full of life. They didn\'t choose tragedy. Tragedy chose them.','Juliette Binoche','sad'),(5365,'It\'s a sad indication of where Washington has come, where policy differences almost necessarily become questions of integrity. I came to Washington in the late \'70s, and people had the ability in the past to have intense policy differences but didn\'t feel the need to question the other person\'s character.','Eric Holder','sad'),(5366,'The sad thing about artificial intelligence is that it lacks artifice and therefore intelligence.','Jean Baudrillard','sad'),(5367,'You had to be into sport and, sad to say, I\'m a traitor to my country because I don\'t have a sporting bone in my body.','Geoffrey Rush','sad'),(5368,'Here in the United States, our profession is much maligned, people simply don\'t trust or like journalists anymore and that\'s sad.','Christiane Amanpour','sad'),(5369,'You know what I have noticed? And this is really sad. Flying first class is less scary than flying coach. They speak to you and they\'re so nice to you and they want to help you and they know you want a drink before the plane takes off. And they bring it to you without asking. If you\'re sitting in coach and hoping for a drink, good luck.','Hope Davis','sad'),(5370,'I\'ve never met a woman who thinks they\'ve got a good enough figure - however perfect they look - which is sad, because no one else can see these perceived flaws; they\'re entirely internal.','L\'Wren Scott','sad'),(5371,'Well in the end the world can crank itself up to sanctions, as it has with Zimbabwe, another sad case.','Helen Clark','sad'),(5372,'It\'s sad that people listen to music and decide how the singer should look.','Joss Stone','sad'),(5373,'Nowadays you really have to pump out that blockbuster in order to have the luxury of getting a body of work, and that\'s sad because the work suffers. Today everything is based on money. The older actors, they inspire me.','Dylan McDermott','sad'),(5374,'Everybody likes Johnny Cash. I think the sad part of it is his health is givin\' him problems.','Merle Haggard','sad'),(5375,'I love New York. I was sad, depressed and incredibly moved by our fellow countrymen and what they\'ve done. I wanted to give people a chance to see something funny, have a distraction.','Ben Stiller','sad'),(5376,'Because the sad fact is that the Enron Corporation and others manipulated with unfortunately great effect the energy market in the West Coast starting in 2000.','Jay Inslee','sad'),(5377,'Elaine is just in pain. I think Elaine has become very, very sad woman. She is someone who is in deep need of many hours of analysis and I like to think that I\'m not that type of person.','Julia Louis-Dreyfus','sad'),(5378,'It\'s sad when you can\'t make everyone happy, though. It\'s impossible but, at the same time, you still hope. You think, \'Maybe I can do it,\' but you know you can\'t. But gosh, if I had to rely on giving people what they wanted, I would have had to write 40 billion different books and even then, I wouldn\'t get it right.','Stephenie Meyer','sad'),(5379,'Wrap parties can be really sad, actually, disorienting.','Josh Lucas','sad'),(5380,'President Bush spent last night calling world leaders to support the war with Iraq and it is sad when the most powerful man on earth is yelling, \'I know you\'re there, pick up, pick up.','Craig Kilborn','sad'),(5381,'And for some reason, when I\'m sad, I do listen to Leonard Cohen, I do listen to Joni Mitchell. I do find myself going to the music that\'s actually reflecting my mood, as opposed to sticking on Motown, which might actually bring my mood up.','Glen Hansard','sad'),(5382,'The sad truth is that opportunity doesn\'t knock twice.','Gloria Estefan','sad'),(5383,'What\'s really sad is that so many young women between the ages of 16 and 25 are ignorant and they already believe that women get the same pay as men. They don\'t even really understand that equality hasn\'t happened with the pay force.','Bell Hooks','sad'),(5384,'I\'m sad to say that stardom is a commodity in our culture.','Christine Baranski','sad'),(5385,'Money is a tremendous advantage in just about everything, but in terms of reproduction, if you\'re a poor woman and you are infertile, it\'s like too bad, so sad. And if you are a wealthy woman, you can kind of buy whatever you want.','Jennifer Weiner','sad'),(5386,'Our family has gone through a very difficult time. My husband and I have taken the brunt of it. I\'ve never known what it truly felt like to be so sad and desperate inside.','Tracey Gold','sad'),(5387,'The waltz can be sad and at the same time uplifting. You have to see life from both sides, and the waltz encapsulates that. If you\'re in my audience you give yourself to me and the waltz will grab you.','Andre Rieu','sad'),(5388,'It feels really sad, to me, to go to a dark bedroom. It\'s like surrendering to the night or something.','James Franco','sad'),(5389,'It\'s an indication of how cynical our society has become that any kind of love story with a sad theme is automatically ridiculed as sentimental junk.','Winona Ryder','sad'),(5390,'It\'s a sad fact about our culture that a poet can earn much more money writing or talking about his art than he can by practicing it.','W. H. Auden','sad'),(5391,'I think it is really sad that when people lose their homes they kind of lose their minds too.','Margaret Cho','sad'),(5392,'The \'80s were fabulous. The \'90s sucked, and the \'70s were just a sad, sad time in human history. Go 1980s! There\'s something that\'s just so cute about that time. And not just yellow nail polish and \'I\'m a loner.\'','Jennifer Sky','sad'),(5393,'I was sad that Corpse Bride was so short. I would\'ve liked to have had her around for way longer. She doesn\'t actually have that many scenes.','Helena Bonham Carter','sad'),(5394,'As a writer, or as a filmmaker, you have to present yourself, and part of what yourself is is what you\'re interested in, or what you think is funny, or what you think is sad, or what you think is horrible.','Charlie Kaufman','sad'),(5395,'You know, why at the end of your life should you assemble thousands of pages of \'Why am I so sad, why am I so depressed?\' Instead, assemble thousands of pages of why you\'re so content.','Elizabeth Gilbert','sad'),(5396,'As somebody who, in my second marriage, insisted on a prenuptial agreement, I can also testify that sometimes it is an act of love to chart the exit strategy before you enter the union, in order to make sure that not only you, but your partner as well, knows that there will be no World War III should hearts and minds, for any sad reason, change.','Elizabeth Gilbert','sad'),(5397,'It\'s sad that the most glorious of sexual experiences can make us feel guilty, ashamed, embarrassed, and abnormal.','Sue Johanson','sad'),(5398,'The funny thing is I\'m not bothered or sad about being on my own - after all I\'ve never had a husband.','Francesca Annis','sad'),(5399,'With my schedule being so crazy, I can\'t call every day or hang out with my friends like I used to and that\'s definitely sad.','Jordin Sparks','sad'),(5400,'My comedy is for children from three to 93. You do need a slightly childish sense of humour and if you haven\'t got that, it\'s very sad.','Norman Wisdom','sad'),(5401,'I remember a time when all my fans were crying and sad and going through hell. Now, we\'re trying to uplift each other and accept ourselves for who we are, even if nobody else does.','Mary J. Blige','sad'),(5402,'The attacks on the World Trade Center and the Pentagon shook our nation to the core. Americans were deeply frightened, sad, and angry, and they rallied around a President who, at the time, showed impressive certitude and calm.','Eliot Spitzer','sad'),(5403,'The sad duty of politics is to establish justice in a sinful world.','Reinhold Niebuhr','sad'),(5404,'Watergate provides a model case study of the interaction and powers of each of the branches of government. It also is a morality play with a sad and dramatic ending.','Bob Woodward','sad'),(5405,'I was at the Olympic Games winning medals and I still doubted my image. I doubted what I looked like. That\'s sad.','Shawn Johnson','sad'),(5406,'People say you should read your criticism because it will make you a better person but it doesn\'t. It just makes you a sad bitter old showbiz nightmare.','Jo Brand','sad'),(5407,'It is sad to see a woman sacrificing the ties of the affections even to do good.','Maria Mitchell','sad'),(5408,'My dad was a homicide cop in the gay neighborhood in the city when gay neighborhoods were desperate, depressing, sad places run by the mob. The only gay people he\'d met when I came out to him were corpses.','Dan Savage','sad'),(5409,'As a songwriter I hate this whole, \'If it\'s a sad song, it has to sound like a sad song thing.\' And that goes all the way back to my days with the Format. I\'m an insane narcissist, so if I have to get something off my chest, I\'ll get something off my chest.','Nate Ruess','sad'),(5410,'Well the country songs themselves are three-chord stories, ballads which are mostly sad. If you are already feeling sorry for yourself when you listen to them they will take you to an even sadder place.','Willie Nelson','sad'),(5411,'I do not take steroids. I never have. It\'s sad to me that people want to point fingers. I don\'t do that. That\'s not me. I wouldn\'t feel like a human being.','Jackie Joyner-Kersee','sad'),(5412,'I\'ve met so many fans of daytime television who\'ve watched the shows with their moms and grandmas and feel like they\'ve known the characters their whole lives. It\'s sad for them to have to say goodbye to their favorite soaps and characters. We don\'t want that to happen to the \'Days\' fans.','Alison Sweeney','sad'),(5413,'I\'m not sad at all about turning 40.','Halle Berry','sad'),(5414,'Morality comes with the sad wisdom of age, when the sense of curiosity has withered.','Graham Greene','sad'),(5415,'I don\'t have many sad days.','Billy Graham','sad'),(5416,'War is very sad and small life is pathetically fragile at times.','Henry Rollins','sad'),(5417,'A lot of sad stories in a row - that wears on you.','Elizabeth Edwards','sad'),(5418,'Among the reasons people keep sad stories to themselves is that they do not want anyone to feel sorry for them. I don\'t. I don\'t want you to feel sorry for me.','Judith Moore','sad'),(5419,'I\'ve got to be high class... Which is sad, because I like bars.','Daniel Craig','sad'),(5420,'The sad thing is that I feel so boring because \'Twilight\' is literally how every conversation I have these days begins - whether it\'s someone I\'m meeting for the first time or someone I just haven\'t seen in a while. The first thing I want to say to them is, \'It\'s insane! And, as a person, I can\'t do anything!\'','Kristen Stewart','sad'),(5421,'There\'s never been a culture that wasn\'t obsessed with food. The sort of sad thing is that our obsession is no longer with food, but with the price of food.','Jonathan Safran Foer','sad'),(5422,'Our religion is itself profoundly sad - a religion of universal anguish, and one which, because of its very catholicity, grants full liberty to the individual and asks no better than to be celebrated in each man\'s own language - so long as he knows anguish and is a painter.','Charles Baudelaire','sad'),(5423,'I have a piece of great and sad news to tell you: I am dead.','Jean Cocteau','sad'),(5424,'I was a very good girl for a long time, that\'s what really drew me to acting. The stage was the perfect place to be outrageous, to be sad, to be angry, to be all these different things.','Joan Allen','sad'),(5425,'It is a sad commentary of our times when our young must seek advice and counsel from \"Dear Abby\" instead of going to Mom and Dad.','Abigail Van Buren','sad'),(5426,'It\'s much easier to write when you\'re sad. But you can end up isolated and depressed because you almost need to put yourself in that situation to have that angst to write from.','Natalie Imbruglia','sad'),(5427,'I\'ll always be sad that my marriage ended.','Shania Twain','sad'),(5428,'For my wrap present, Colin Farrell gave me a first edition book. I got so involved with this character and I was so sad when the movie was over that when I got home and I tried to read the book I got really emotional and I started crying.','Salma Hayek','sad'),(5429,'When you\'re going through something, whether it\'s a wonderful thing like having a child or a sad thing like losing somebody, you often feel like \'Oh my God, I\'m so overwhelmed; I\'m dealing with this huge thing on my own.\' In fact, poetry\'s a nice reminder that, no, everybody goes through it. These are universal experiences.','Caroline Kennedy','sad'),(5430,'But I\'m not like sad, depressed miserable person. I guess sometimes I give off that impression.','Edward Furlong','sad'),(5431,'There were points in my life where I felt oddly irresistible to women. I\'m not in that state now and that makes me sad.','Jack Nicholson','sad'),(5432,'I think I would be very sad if I wasn\'t able to have a baby.','Nicole Kidman','sad'),(5433,'The monarchy is foremost a business, and it\'s important to them that the British public continue to finance the excessive luxurious lifestyles of the now quite enormous, wasteful and useless \'royal\' family. I find it very sad.','Steven Patrick Morrissey','sad'),(5434,'What I really tried to do with Helen was make her show this sad side of her. She was married off at 16, was so young and living in this castle that can\'t leave because of how she looks, and married to a man she hates and three times her age.','Diane Kruger','sad'),(5435,'You can\'t have an up without a down, a right without a left, a back without a front - or a happy without a sad.','Harlan Coben','sad'),(5436,'I would love to be married. But it\'s not a necessity like the way that I feel I need and want to have children. It would be wonderful to have a husband, and I would feel blessed to do it. But I would feel sad for the rest of my life if I had no kids.','Mindy Kaling','sad'),(5437,'I don\'t know what to say to that, but I have to agree with Johnny that, yeah, we do touch upon things that most men would rather not admit: That we feel pain, we cry, get sad and sometimes don\'t deal well with disappointment.','Peter Steele','sad'),(5438,'Acting gave me the opportunity to do outrageous things. It allowed me to be sad, happy, angry and lustful, even if it was just vicariously.','Joan Allen','sad'),(5439,'At a time when 2500 American soldiers have given their lives for the cause of bringing democracy to Iraq, it is sad and frustrating to watch the Republican establishment disgrace the exercise of democracy in our own House of Representatives.','Earl Blumenauer','sad'),(5440,'The good times of today, are the sad thoughts of tomorrow.','Bob Marley','sad'),(5441,'For me, singing sad songs often has a way of healing a situation. It gets the hurt out in the open into the light, out of the darkness.','Reba McEntire','sad'),(5442,'It is sad not to love, but it is much sadder not to be able to love.','Miguel de Unamuno','sad'),(5443,'Usually when people are sad, they don\'t do anything. They just cry over their condition. But when they get angry, they bring about a change.','James Russell Lowell','sad'),(5444,'I am convinced that material things can contribute a lot to making one\'s life pleasant, but, basically, if you do not have very good friends and relatives who matter to you, life will be really empty and sad and material things cease to be important.','David Rockefeller','sad'),(5445,'A comfortable old age is the reward of a well-spent youth. Instead of its bringing sad and melancholy prospects of decay, it would give us hopes of eternal youth in a better world.','Maurice Chevalier','sad'),(5446,'Every word, facial expression, gesture, or action on the part of a parent gives the child some message about self-worth. It is sad that so many parents don\'t realize what messages they are sending.','Virginia Satir','sad'),(5447,'Hear me, my chiefs! I am tired. My heart is sick and sad. From where the sun now stands, I will fight no more forever.','Chief Joseph','sad'),(5448,'Let my soul smile through my heart and my heart smile through my eyes, that I may scatter rich smiles in sad hearts.','Paramahansa Yogananda','sad'),(5449,'The sad truth is that most evil is done by people who never make up their minds to be good or evil.','Hannah Arendt','sad'),(5450,'I hold the world but as the world, Gratiano; A stage where every man must play a part, And mine is a sad one.','William Shakespeare','sad'),(5451,'I had rather have a fool to make me merry than experience to make me sad and to travel for it too!','William Shakespeare','sad'),(5452,'I didn\'t really want to live, so anything that was an investment in time made me angry... but also I just felt sad. When the hopelessness is hurting you, it\'s the fixtures and fittings that finish you off.','Angelina Jolie','sad'),(5453,'It is a very sad thing that nowadays there is so little useless information.','Oscar Wilde','sad'),(5454,'So many gods, so many creeds, so many paths that wind and wind while just the art of being kind is all the sad world needs.','Ella Wheeler Wilcox','sad'),(5455,'Christmas makes everything twice as sad.','Doug Coupland','sad'),(5456,'You can never control who you fall in love with, even when you\'re in the most sad, confused time of your life. You don\'t fall in love with people because they\'re fun. It just happens.','Kirsten Dunst','sad'),(5457,'If we don\'t make earnest moves toward real solutions, then each day we move one day closer to revolution and anarchy in this country. This is the sad, and yet potentially joyous, state of America.','Louis Farrakhan','sad'),(5458,'For I have learned to look on nature, not as in the hour of thoughtless youth, but hearing oftentimes the still, sad music of humanity.','William Wordsworth','sad'),(5459,'And in real life endings aren\'t always neat, whether they\'re happy endings, or whether they\'re sad endings.','Stephen King','sad'),(5460,'The closing of a door can 