,'Shana Alexander','sad'),(5674,'It\'s sad that women characters have lost so much ground in popular movies. Didn\'t \'Thelma and Louise\' prove that women want to see women doing things on film? Thelma and Louise were in a classic car; they were being chased by cops; they shot up a truck - and women loved it.','Robin Quivers','sad'),(5675,'I\'m terribly sad about Farrah\'s passing. She was incredibly brave, and God will be welcoming her with open arms.','Cheryl Ladd','sad'),(5676,'You have to keep hobbies in L.A. Otherwise, it\'s sad.','Lake Bell','sad'),(5677,'I was always depressed growing up. There wasn\'t a reason for it, I just was. I was sad and morose. I cried a lot, I wrote a lot, and I read a lot; and that was how I dealt with it.','Amanda Hocking','sad'),(5678,'There is the glamour side of it, which allows you to meet great variety of people with whom you simply can have a good time, but there\'s also the sad side of it that drags you into a superficial and artificial world.','Karolina Kurkova','sad'),(5679,'I didn\'t know my mother had it. I think a lot of women don\'t know their mothers had it; that\'s the sad thing about depression. You know, you don\'t function anymore. You shut down. You feel like you are in a void.','Marie Osmond','sad'),(5680,'It can make you sad to look at pictures from your youth. So there\'s a trick to it. The trick is not to look at the later pictures.','Jerry Stiller','sad'),(5681,'\'The Killing\' has a really great combination of qualities: Even though it\'s very sad and deals with mourning and grief, it\'s still exciting. It\'s about real people and it doesn\'t shy from the painful points of life.','Joel Kinnaman','sad'),(5682,'You see so many artists who are so talented end up living sad, empty lives. This industry takes so much out of you that without the accountability and leaving God in the center, you can be left so empty and void.','Stacie Orrico','sad'),(5683,'I\'ve been getting into Nick Drake lately, the folk singer