orrow upon sorrow?','Thomas a Kempis','sad'),(5734,'Time takes away the grief of men.','Desiderius Erasmus','sad'),(5735,'Sorrows are like thunderclouds, in the distance they look black, over our heads scarcely gray.','Jean Paul','sad'),(5736,'The saddest thing that befalls a soul Is when it loses faith in God and woman.','Alexander Smith','sad'),(5737,'God is in the sadness and the laughter, in the bitter and the sweet.','Neale Donald Walsch','sad'),(5738,'We tell our triumphs to the crowds, but our own hearts are the sole confidants of our sorrows.','Edward G. Bulwer-Lytton','sad'),(5739,'Those who gave away their wings are sad not to see them fly.','Antonio Porchia','sad'),(5740,'Actually, the moment of victory is wonderful, but also sad. It means that your trip is ended.','Bill Toomey','sad'),(5741,'Every human walks around with a certain kind of sadness. They may not wear it on their sleeves, but it\'s there if you look deep.','Taraji P. Henson','sad'),(5742,'Nobody understands another\'s sorrow, and nobody another\'s joy.','Franz Schubert','sad'),(5743,'First, accept sadness. Realize that without losing, winning isn\'t so great.','Alyssa Milano','sad'),(5744,'I had sadness for breakfast.','Andy Milonakis','sad'),(5745,'Red is the ultimate cure for sadness.','Bill Blass','sad'),(5746,'They say it\'s better to bury your sadness in a graveyard or garden that waits for the spring to wake from its sleep and burst into green.','Conor Oberst','sad'),(5747,'Sadness is also a kind of defence.','Ivo Andric','sad'),(5748,'One should either be sad or joyful. Contentment is a warm sty for eaters and sleepers.','Eugene O\'Neill','sad'),(5749,'You have to let it all hang out, let go of the ideas that were more comfortable and embrace some of the sadness in your life.','Madeleine Peyroux','sad'),(5750,'Everything\'s complicated, even those things that seem flat in their bleakness or sadness.','Nick Hornby','sad'),(5751,'The excursion is the same when you go looking for your sorrow as when you go looking for your joy.','Eudora Welty','sad'),(5752,'When you are joyous, look deep into your heart and you shall find it is only that which has given you sorrow that is giving you joy. When you are sorrowful look again in your heart, and you shall see that in truth you are weeping for that which has been your delight.','Khalil Gibran','sad'),(5753,'Every man has his secret sorrows which the world knows not; and often times we call a man cold when he is only sad.','Henry Wadsworth Longfellow','sad'),(5754,'It\'s sad when someone you know becomes someone you knew.','Henry Rollins','sad'),(5755,'If my world were to cave in tomorrow, I would look back on all the pleasures, excitements and worthwhilenesses I have been lucky enough to have had. Not the sadness, not my miscarriages or my father leaving home, but the joy of everything else. It will have been enough.','Audrey Hepburn','sad'),(5756,'Sadness is but a wall between two gardens.','Khalil Gibran','sad'),(5757,'I seldom think about my limitations, and they never make me sad. Perhaps there is just a touch of yearning at times; but it is vague, like a breeze among flowers.','Helen Keller','sad'),(5758,'Affliction comes to us, not to make us sad but sober; not to make us sorry but wise.','H. G. Wells','sad'),(5759,'A sad soul can kill quicker than a germ.','John Steinbeck','sad'),(5760,'Make the most of your regrets; never smother your sorrow, but tend and cherish it till it comes to have a separate and integral interest. To regret deeply is to live afresh.','Henry David Thoreau','sad'),(5761,'Participate joyfully in the sorrows of the world. We cannot cure the world of sorrows, but we can choose to live in joy.','Joseph Campbell','sad'),(5762,'Live by this credo: have a little laugh at life and look around you for happiness instead of sadness. Laughter has always brought me out of unhappy situations.','Red Skelton','sad'),(5763,'I\'ve cried, and you\'d think I\'d be better for it, but the sadness