e Williams','sad'),(6564,'It\'s a sad indication of where Washington has come, where policy differences almost necessarily become questions of integrity. I came to Washington in the late \'70s, and people had the ability in the past to have intense policy differences but didn\'t feel the need to question the other person\'s character.','Eric Holder','sad'),(6565,'The sad thing about artificial intelligence is that it lacks artifice and therefore intelligence.','Jean Baudrillard','sad'),(6566,'You had to be into sport and, sad to say, I\'m a traitor to my country because I don\'t have a sporting bone in my body.','Geoffrey Rush','sad'),(6567,'Here in the United States, our profession is much maligned, people simply don\'t trust or like journalists anymore and that\'s sad.','Christiane Amanpour','sad'),(6568,'You know what I have noticed? And this is really sad. Flying first class is less scary than flying coach. They speak to you and they\'re so nice to you and they want to help you and they know you want a drink before the plane takes off. And they bring it to you without asking. If you\'re sitting in coach and hoping for a drink, good luck.','Hope Davis','sad'),(6569,'I\'ve never met a woman who thinks they\'ve got a good enough figure - however perfect they look - which is sad, because no one else can see these perceived flaws; they\'re entirely internal.','L\'Wren Scott','sad'),(6570,'Well in the end the world can crank itself up to sanctions, as it has with Zimbabwe, another sad case.','Helen Clark','sad'),(6571,'It\'s sad that people listen to music and decide how the singer should look.','Joss Stone','sad'),(6572,'Nowadays you really have to pump out that blockbuster in order to have the luxury of getting a body of work, and that\'s sad because the work suffers. Today everything is based on money. The older actors, they inspire me.','Dylan McDermott','sad'),(6573,'Everybody likes Johnny Cash. I think the sad part of it is his health is givin\' him problems.','Merle Haggard','sad'),(6574,'I love New York. I was sad, depressed and incredibly moved by our fellow countrymen and what they\'ve done. I wanted to give people a chance to see something funny, have a distraction.','Ben Stiller','sad'),(6575,'Because the sad fact is that the Enron Corporation and others manipulated with unfortunately great effect the energy market in the West Coast starting in 2000.','Jay Inslee','sad'),(6576,'Elaine is just in pain. I think Elaine has become very, very sad woman. She is someone who is in deep need of many hours of analysis and I like to think that I\'m not that type of person.','Julia Louis-Dreyfus','sad'),(6577,'It\'s sad when you can\'t make everyone happy, though. It\'s impossible but, at the same time, you still hope. You think, \'Maybe I can do it,\' but you know you can\'t. But gosh, if I had to rely on giving people what they wanted, I would have had to write 40 billion different books and even then, I wouldn\'t get it right.','Stephenie Meyer','sad'),(6578,'Wrap parties can be really sad, actually, disorienting.','Josh Lucas','sad'),(6579,'President Bush spent last night calling world leaders to support the war with Iraq and it is sad when the most powerful man on earth is yelling, \'I know you\'re there, pick up, pick up.','Craig Kilborn','sad'),(6580,'And for some reason, when I\'m sad, I do listen to Leonard Cohen, I do listen to Joni Mitchell. I do find myself going to the music that\'s actually reflecting my mood, as opposed to sticking on Motown, which might actually bring my mood up.','Glen Hansard','sad'),(6581,'The sad truth is that opportunity doesn\'t knock twice.','Gloria Estefan','sad'),(6582,'What\'s really sad is that so many young women between the ages of 16 and 25 are ignorant and they already believe that women get the same pay as men. They don\'t even really understand that equality hasn\'t happened with the pay force.','Bell Hooks','sad'),(6583,'I\'m sad to say that stardom is a commodity in our culture.','Christine Baranski','sad'),(6584,'Money is a tremendous advantage in just about everything, but in terms of reproduction, if you\'re a poor woman and you are infertile, it\'s like too bad, so sad. And if you are a wealthy woman, you can kind of buy whatever you want.','Jennifer Weiner','sad'),(6585,'Our family has gone through a very difficult time. My husband and I have taken the brunt of it. I\'ve never known what it truly felt like to be so sad and desperate inside.','Tracey Gold','sad'),(6586,'The waltz can be sad and at the same time uplifting. You have to see life from both sides, and the waltz encapsulates that. If you\'re in my audience you give yourself to me and the waltz will grab you.','Andre Rieu','sad'),(6587,'It feels really sad, to me, to go to a dark bedroom. It\'s like surrendering to the night or something.','James Franco','sad'),(6588,'It\'s an indication of how cynical our society has become that any kind of love story with a sad theme is automatically ridiculed as sentimental junk.','Winona Ryder','sad'),(6589,'Crying is cleansing. There\'s a reason for tears, happiness or sadness.','Dionne Warwick','sad'),(6590,'Heavy hearts, like heavy clouds in the sky, are best relieved by the letting of a little water.','Christopher Morley','sad'),(6591,'You get used to sadness, growing up in the mountains, I guess.','Loretta Lynn','sad'),(6592,'The reason for the sadness of this modern age and the men who live in it is that it looks for the truth in everything and finds it.','Edmond de Goncourt','sad'),(6593,'Your joys and sorrows. You can never tell them. You cheapen the inside of yourself if you do tell them.','Greta Garbo','sad'),(6594,'Sad will be the day for any man when he becomes contented with the thoughts he is thinking and the deeds he is doing - where there is not forever beating at the doors of his soul some great desire to do something larger; which he knows he was meant and made to do.','Phillips Brooks','sad'),(6595,'What else does anxiety about the future bring you but sorrow upon sorrow?','Thomas a Kempis','sad'),(6596,'Time takes away the grief of men.','Desiderius Erasmus','sad'),(6597,'Sorrows are like thunderclouds, in the distance they look black, over our heads scarcely gray.','Jean Paul','sad'),(6598,'The saddest thing that befalls a soul Is when it loses faith in God and woman.','Alexander Smith','sad'),(6599,'God is in the sadness and the laughter, in the bitter and the sweet.','Neale Donald Walsch','sad'),(6600,'We tell our triumphs to the crowds, but our own hearts are the sole confidants of our sorrows.','Edward G. Bulwer-Lytton','sad'),(6601,'Those who gave away their wings are sad not to see them fly.','Antonio Porchia','sad'),(6602,'Actually, the moment of victory is wonderful, but also sad. It means that your trip is ended.','Bill Toomey','sad'),(6603,'Every human walks around with a certain kind of sadness. They may not wear it on their sleeves, but it\'s there if you look deep.','Taraji P. Henson','sad'),(6604,'Nobody understands another\'s sorrow, and nobody another\'s joy.','Franz Schubert','sad'),(6605,'First, accept sadness. Realize that without losing, winning isn\'t so great.','Alyssa Milano','sad'),(6606,'I had sadness for breakfast.','Andy Milonakis','sad'),(6607,'Red is the ultimate cure for sadness.','Bill Blass','sad'),(6608,'They say it\'s better to bury your sadness in a graveyard or garden that waits for the spring to wake from its sleep and burst into green.','Conor Oberst','sad'),(6609,'Sadness is also a kind of defence.','Ivo Andric','sad'),(6610,'One should either be sad or joyful. Contentment is a warm sty for eaters and sleepers.','Eugene O\'Neill','sad'),(6611,'You have to let it all hang out, let go of the ideas that were more comfortable and embrace some of the sadness in your life.','Madeleine Peyroux','sad'),(6612,'Everything\'s complicated, even those things that seem flat in their bleakness or sadness.','Nick Hornby','sad'),(6613,'The excursion is the same when you go looking for your sorrow as when you go looking for your joy.','Eudora Welty','sad'),(6614,'We tell them that we believe it will be beautiful because that is our specialty, we only create joy and beauty. We have never done a sad work. Through the drawings, we hope a majority will be able to visualize it.','Christo','sad'),(6615,'It\'s so sad: anything that has to do with God, people want to dispel.','Sylvia Browne','sad'),(6616,'My father comes from a generation of film that actors my age don\'t even know about, which is really sad.','Amber Tamblyn','sad'),(6617,'When I look back at those pictures of my mother performing - and listen to her recordings - it makes me sad to think that all of that joy she found in her work came to an end. I wish she hadn\'t had to make that sacrifice, even if it was for the benefit of my father and siblings and me.','Marlo Thomas','sad'),(6618,'I\'m not a very serious person. You know how they say that clowns are very funny in public and are really sad at home? I\'m really kind of stupid at home and more serious in public.','Roland Joffe','sad'),(6619,'Sad Patience, too near neighbour to despair.','Matthew Arnold','sad'),(6620,'The sad thing about any business I suppose, but in mine you see it particularly, is that you\'re always asked to do what you\'ve already done.','Jeremy Irons','sad'),(6621,'But now Americans, they felt a sense of peace and protection because they\'ve been separated by so many thousands of miles of ocean. And you know, the fact that it\'s come to the U.S. like this is so sad, and yet you know, what can you do? It\'s here.','Patty Hearst','sad'),(6622,'So far, at least, I haven\'t found a way to tell my kind of stories without making them both sad and funny.','Todd Solondz','sad'),(6623,'If you\'re lucky like me, your relationship with your brother has resolved itself on the peaceful side of the fence and has stayed there. But if you\'re someone who\'s got a family that\'s all fractured and finding it hard to relate, that\'s a very sad place to be.','Tom Hardy','sad'),(6624,'To be a character who feels a deep emotion, one must go into the memory\'s vault and mix in a sad memory from one\'s own life.','Albert Finney','sad'),(6625,'It\'s pretty sad when you have to choose between the lesser of two evils.','Meg White','sad'),(6626,'It\'s a sad commentary when I have to say that sometimes in our country we are real sensitive to race.','Oscar Robertson','sad'),(6627,'I mean, the unfair treatment of women and black people and Indians and other groups, that\'s real. Mistreatment of other people because \'I\'m better than you are\' is such a sad part of the world.','Melissa Leo','sad'),(6628,'There are a lot of people who consider themselves \'spiritual,\' but that can mean a lot of things to a lot of people. I don\'t really talk about it that often, because there\'s too much talk in the world. Especially with Christians, there\'s more proselytizing than there is actual living proof of it. That\'s kind of sad.','Zachary Levi','sad'),(6629,'What\'s really sad is that a lot of very talented people are being forced to do things that are very embarrassing and I don\'t intend to be one of them.','Boy George','sad'),(6630,'In film, you can have sad endings.','Anna Torv','sad'),(6631,'I think the thing\'s that perhaps sad really is that younger people haven\'t come in and I think it must have been absolutely fantastic to have worked in the 50\'s when you had all of the great Broadway composers and when West Side Story didn\'t win the Tony Award.','Andrew Lloyd Webber','sad'),(6632,'I wrote the song For A Dancer for a friend of mine who died in a fire. He was in the sauna in a house that burned down, so he had no idea anything was going on. It was very sad.','Jackson Browne','sad'),(6633,'Someone once accused me of being like Eliot Ness. I sad no sir, I\'m not E.N., but I can promise you that I\'m not Al Capone!','Robert Stack','sad'),(6634,'I enjoyed in every way my 12 years of playing Archie, and I wasn\'t personally sad about finishing a long job.','Carroll O\'Connor','sad'),(6635,'Lately, I\'ve been a little sad that I\'m not a gay man.','Gina Gershon','sad'),(6636,'I know for works for me - those wonderful sad love songs.','Toni Braxton','sad'),(6637,'In a sad twist of fate, the bill to reauthorize the Patriot Act was debated on the floor of the House of Representatives the same day that terrorists struck again.','Jim Sensenbrenner','sad'),(6638,'I have a stepladder. It\'s a very nice stepladder but it\'s sad that I never knew my real ladder.','Craig Charles','sad'),(6639,'I\'ve grown as a person. The dynamics on this set are very demanding because we work a lot of hours, it\'s very sad material, so there\'s always someone upset because it\'s really heavy stuff.','Elisabeth Rohm','sad'),(6640,'The South is very beautiful but its beauty makes one sad because the lives that people live here, and have lived here, are so ugly.','James Baldwin','sad'),(6641,'It\'s fun to sing sad songs. And it\'s fun to listen to sad songs. Enjoyable. Satisfying. Something.','Richard Thompson','sad'),(6642,'That\'s what so sad about a lot of modern music, in my opinion, so many young bands never stay around long enough to fulfill their ultimate promise. They only get halfway there or a quarter of the way there.','Alan Vega','sad'),(6643,'It can be really powerful to write something when you\'re sad.','Kathryn Stockett','sad'),(6644,'If you don\'t physically age gracefully, it\'s a bit sad. I think Steven Tyler can get away anything, because he still looks like he did in \'73. Especially from row Z backwards in an arena. As long as the Stones keep their hair and don\'t get fat they\'ll get away with the wrinkles.','Joe Elliott','sad'),(6645,'I\'m proud of my invention, but I\'m sad that it is used by terrorists.','Mikhail Kalashnikov','sad'),(6646,'But I now entered on my fifteenth year - a sad epoch in the life of a slave girl. My master began to whisper foul words in my ear. Young as I was, I could not remain ignorant of their import.','Harriet Ann Jacobs','sad'),(6647,'Since I had the baby I can\'t tolerate anything violent or sad, I saw the Matrix and I had my eyes closed through a lot of it, though I didn\'t need to. I would peek, and then think, oh OK, I can see that.','Lisa Kudrow','sad'),(6648,'What I am sad about is that there is now, in America, no equivalent to the art circuit.','Richard Attenborough','sad'),(6649,'The sad fact is that the same terrorist scenarios, if they occurred in five different States, there could be five different sets of responses to the American people. We need, at a minimum, a level of coordination on communicating threats to the public.','Vito Fossella','sad'),(6650,'If you have ever been in a real tragic or sad situation, the words that come out are hopelessly inadequate and kind of cliched.','Erika Slezak','sad'),(6651,'I know that some endeavor to throw the mantle of romance over the subject and treat woman like some ideal existence, not liable to the ills of life. Let those deal in fancy who have nothing better to deal in; we have to do with sober, sad realities, with stubborn facts.','Ernestine Rose','sad'),(6652,'Of these years nought remains in memory but the sad feeling that we have advanced and only grown older.','Max Muller','sad'),(6653,'His death was the first time that Ed Wynn ever made anyone sad.','Red Skelton','sad'),(6654,'They\'re not willing to admit that I\'ve also shed blood and tears and often paid dearly for my success. This makes me feel extremely sad.','Zhang Ziyi','sad'),(6655,'I love playing football, being out on the pitch with a ball, and I will be a little sad when that ends.','Dennis Bergkamp','sad'),(6656,'I would be sad if it ended now. It\'s been the best job I\'ve had by a long shot, especially creatively because the writing is so good. Every week I get the script and I laugh out loud and get excited for the different stuff we get to do.','S