ow? And I think if he just didn\'t try so hard and calmed down, people might actually like him a bit more!','Gabriel Mann','sad'),(6679,'I mean, I was just one of the ones who got exposed, and because of the position I was in, where I was in my life, it went mainstream. A lot of people got out of it after my situation, not because I went to prison but because it was sad for them to see me go through something that was so pointless, that could have been avoided.','Michael Vick','sad'),(6680,'I would never have become music director of the Chicago Symphony, which would have been an extremely sad loss.','Georg Solti','sad'),(6681,'I was so sad from losing two of my dogs and my mother. I had this vision of all these animals sitting behind bars. They had no control and were scared. That\'s why I got into fostering and adopting animals out.','Linda Blair','sad'),(6682,'When I was leaving I kind of felt a little bit sad, because I made some friends down in skid row.','Pras Michel','sad'),(6683,'I only really watch sport. That\'s where you see real joy. I don\'t like watching much else on TV, because it\'s generally either twisted or sad.','Roger Milla','sad'),(6684,'I wanted to be a dancer my whole life. And when I gave it up to act, I always had a really sad part of myself that missed it and missed performing and missed being physical in that way.','Lyndsy Fonseca','sad'),(6685,'The sad truth is that excellence makes people nervous.','Shana Alexander','sad'),(6686,'It\'s sad that women characters have lost so much ground in popular movies. Didn\'t \'Thelma and Louise\' prove that women want to see women doing things on film? Thelma and Louise were in a classic car; they were being chased by cops; they shot up a truck - and women loved it.','Robin Quivers','sad'),(6687,'I\'m terribly sad about Farrah\'s passing. She was incredibly brave, and God will be welcoming her with open arms.','Cheryl Ladd','sad'),(6688,'You have to keep hobbies in L.A. Otherwise, it\'s sad.','Lake 