 well as the part I\'m not happy with, the sad part.','Roy Haynes','sad'),(6775,'\'Eyes Wide Open\' took shape from two real life events straight from my own past. One was the sad suicide of my young nephew, a troubled kid, who was found at the bottom of a landmark cliff in central California. The second was a chance encounter forty years ago with none other than, ahem, Charles Manson!','Andrew Gross','sad'),(6776,'I have felt terribly from the beginning when I saw the problems and recognized that they would be ongoing. We were hired to put back the contours of the greens as closely as possible to George Thomas\'s designs and were real proud of what we did. It\'s a sad situation now.','Ben Crenshaw','sad'),(6777,'When this sad war is over we will all return to our homes, and feel that we can ask no higher honor than the proud consciousness that we belonged to the Army of the Potomac.','George B. McClellan','sad'),(6778,'It\'s both funny and sad which seem to me to be the two basic ingredients of good comedy.','Tony Hancock','sad'),(6779,'We try to... we are, I suppose to a certain extent all affected and erm, that is both funny and sad I think.','Tony Hancock','sad'),(6780,'The past 6 and a half years have been the most amazing years of my life. It\'s sad it has come to an end but Avril and I are still family and moving forward in the most positive way possible.','Deryck Whibley','sad'),(6781,'The poem is sad because it wants to be yours, and cannot be.','John Ashbery','sad'),(6782,'If the IAAF feel that is the right way to go for TV rights and everything, the rule will stay. As much as I want to be on the podium, tonight is a sad night for athletics.','Kim Collins','sad'),(6783,'A Church which has lost its memory is in a sad state of senility.','Henry Chadwick','sad'),(6784,'Sad old blokes, I\'m told, now dream of me with a whip in hand.','Anne Robinson','sad'),(6785,'All you\'d have to do is get a sad look, and he\'d try to do something for you.','Margaret O\'Brien','sad'),(6786,'Many things have been said about what happened, but I don\'t know either. Maybe someday. One thing I\'m sure of is that all the things that have happened to me, good and bad, happy and sad, have made me what I am today.','Pete Best','sad'),(6787,'It\'s a sad moment, really, when parents first become a bit frightened of their children.','Ama Ata Aidoo','sad'),(6788,'I will be sad. I\'ve gotten very attached to Harry and all that goes on in his world, I guess I\'ll just be kind of tasting every bit of it because it will be the last one.','Mary Grandpre','sad'),(6789,'When you are joyous, look deep into your heart and you shall find it is only that which has given you sorrow that is giving you joy. When you are sorrowful look again in your heart, and you shall see that in truth you are weeping for that which has been your delight.','Khalil Gibran','sad'),(6790,'Every man has his secret sorrows which the world knows not; and often times we call a man cold when he is only sad.','Henry Wadsworth Longfellow','sad'),(6791,'It\'s sad when someone you know becomes someone you knew.','Henry Rollins','sad'),(6792,'If my world were to cave in tomorrow, I would look back on all the pleasures, excitements and worthwhilenesses I have been lucky enough to have had. Not the sadness, not my miscarriages or my father leaving home, but the joy of everything else. It will have been enough.','Audrey Hepburn','sad'),(6793,'Sadness is but a wall between two gardens.','Khalil Gibran','sad'),(6794,'I seldom think about my limitations, and they never make me sad. Perhaps there is just a touch of yearning at times; but it is vague, like a breeze among flowers.','Helen Keller','sad'),(6795,'Affliction comes to us, not to make us sad but sober; not to make us sorry but wise.','H. G. Wells','sad'),(6796,'A sad soul can kill quicker than a germ.','John Steinbeck','sad'),(6797,'Make the most of your regrets; never smother your sorrow, but tend and cherish it till it comes to have a 