r.','Mattie Stepanek','sad'),(6810,'Every life has a measure of sorrow, and sometimes this is what awakens us.','Steven Tyler','sad'),(6811,'It is sadder to find the past again and find it inadequate to the present than it is to have it elude you and remain forever a harmonious conception of memory.','F. Scott Fitzgerald','sad'),(6812,'For all sad words of tongue and pen, The saddest are these, \'It might have been\'.','John Greenleaf Whittier','sad'),(6813,'We never taste a perfect joy; our happiest successes are mixed with sadness.','Pierre Corneille','sad'),(6814,'We all had lots of stories of our sad experiences - they mourned the death of my wife with me - but we were hopeful that the children would return.','Otto Frank','sad'),(6815,'One of the sad commentaries on the way women are viewed in our society is that we have to fit one category. I have never felt that I had to be in one category.','Faye Wattleton','sad'),(6816,'The last few years have been my happiest. I\'m happy in the years that most people are blue and sad and waiting to die. I don\'t feel that a bit. Smiling has a lot to do with it. You can just lift your spirits by smiling a little bit.','William Proxmire','sad'),(6817,'If Michael Steele doesn\'t make you sad, well, then there\'s radio host Rush Limbaugh, no longer content with wanting the President to fail, Rush is now calling out Mr. Obama as a girly man.','David Shuster','sad'),(6818,'You know, they just don\'t make big movie stars the way they used to, maybe because the system has changed, the studio system, but it\'s sad to see people like Jimmy Stewart go, all the giants of the past.','Tom Atkins','sad'),(6819,'It\'s a sad and stupid thing to have to proclaim yourself a revolutionary just to be a decent man.','David Harris','sad'),(6820,'It is a sad day for our country when the moral foundation of our law and the acknowledgment of God has to be hidden from public view to appease a federal judge.','Soledad O\'Brien','sad'),(6821,'Keep it simple, keep it sexy, keep it sad.','Mitch Miller','sad'),(6822,'Sad and sweet and wise Here a child reposes; Dust is on his eyes, Quietly he lies - Satan, strew Roses.','Robert Williams Buchanan','sad'),(6823,'It\'s really sad that the kids today can only relate to Beethoven via a rock version of his music.','Walter Murphy','sad'),(6824,'Our hope, and it\'s a sad hope, is that... well, I mean we need a tip. That\'s why we have such a big reward. We just hope that someone is holding her for her child and that we can, you know, get her back with a tip.','Scott Peterson','sad'),(6825,'I had never felt so lonely and so sad in my entire life.','Susan Smith','sad'),(6826,'Crying is cleansing. There\'s a reason for tears, happiness or sadness.','Dionne Warwick','sad'),(6827,'Heavy hearts, like heavy clouds in the sky, are best relieved by the letting of a little water.','Christopher Morley','sad'),(6828,'You get used to sadness, growing up in the mountains, I guess.','Loretta Lynn','sad'),(6829,'The reason for the sadness of this modern age and the men who live in it is that it looks for the truth in everything and finds it.','Edmond de Goncourt','sad'),(6830,'Your joys and sorrows. You can never tell them. You cheapen the inside of yourself if you do tell them.','Greta Garbo','sad'),(6831,'Sad will be the day for any man when he becomes contented with the thoughts he is thinking and the deeds he is doing - where there is not forever beating at the doors of his soul some great desire to do something larger; which he knows he was meant and made to do.','Phillips Brooks','sad'),(6832,'What else does anxiety about the future bring you but sorrow upon sorrow?','Thomas a Kempis','sad'),(6833,'Time takes away the grief of men.','Desiderius Erasmus','sad'),(6834,'Sorrows are like thunderclouds, in the distance they look black, over our heads scarcely gray.','Jean Paul','sad'),(6835,'The saddest thing that befalls a soul Is when it loses faith in God and woman.','Alexander Smith','sad'),(6836,'God is in the sadness and the laughter, in the bitter and the sweet.','Neale Donald Walsch','sad'),(6837,'We tell our triumphs to the crowds, but our own hearts are the sole confidants of our sorrows.','Edward G. Bulwer-Lytton','sad'),(6838,'Those who gave away their wings are sad not to see them fly.','Antonio Porchia','sad'),(6839,'Actually, the moment of victory is wonderful, but also sad. It means that your trip is ended.','Bill Toomey','sad'),(6840,'Every human walks around with a certain kind of sadness. They may not wear it on their sleeves, but it\'s there if you look deep.','Taraji P. Henson','sad'),(6841,'Nobody understands another\'s sorrow, and nobody another\'s joy.','Franz Schubert','sad'),(6842,'First, accept sadness. Realize that without losing, winning isn\'t so great.','Alyssa Milano','sad'),(6843,'I had sadness for breakfast.','Andy Milonakis','sad'),(6844,'Red is the ultimate cure for sadness.','Bill Blass','sad'),(6845,'They say it\'s better to bury your sadness in a graveyard or garden that waits for the spring to wake from its sleep and burst into green.','Conor Oberst','sad'),(6846,'Sadness is also a kind of defence.','Ivo Andric','sad'),(6847,'One should either be sad or joyful. Contentment is a warm sty for eaters and sleepers.','Eugene O\'Neill','sad'),(6848,'You have to let it all hang out, let go of the ideas that were more comfortable and embrace some of the sadness in your life.','Madeleine Peyroux','sad'),(6849,'Everything\'s complicated, even those things that seem flat in their bleakness or sadness.','Nick Hornby','sad'),(6850,'The excursion is the same when you go looking for your sorrow as when you go looking for your joy.','Eudora Welty','sad'),(6851,'Beauty makes idiots sad and wise men merry.','George Jean Nathan','sad'),(6852,'They say geniuses mostly have great mothers. They mostly have sad fates.','David Herbert Lawrence','sad'),(6853,'I love my past, I love my present. I am not ashamed of what I have had, and 