vement that is hopefully going to bring some awareness and make some noise when it comes to teens who are feeling suicidal or even just sad, outcasts, and being bullied, and really feel like they have nowhere to turn to.','Brittany Snow','sad'),(7008,'The old know what they want; the young are sad and bewildered.','Logan P. Smith','sad'),(7009,'Atari is a very sad story.','Steve Wozniak','sad'),(7010,'Home will always be Northern Ireland but my schedule means for the next few years I won\'t be there as much. I can\'t do the same things that I did a year ago. That is I\'m something conscious of, but I\'m not sad about it. It\'s fine.','Rory McIlroy','sad'),(7011,'I\'m incredibly sad that my mother\'s not here to see my kids and that my kids don\'t get to know her. And she didn\'t meet my husband. That\'s one of the hardest things. I don\'t even know how to put that into words.','Stella McCartney','sad'),(7012,'When I was a child people simply looked about them and were moderately happy; today they peer beyond the seven seas, bury themselves waist deep in tidings, and by and large what they see and hear makes them unutterably sad.','E. B. White','sad'),(7013,'I\'m so grounded, it\'s sad.','Patti LaBelle','sad'),(7014,'With the other fellow actors who have gone astray, I think it\'s sad that society wants to label the business as doing this to people. It\'s really not true.','Tina Yothers','sad'),(7015,'It\'s very rare that things are true about yourself that are on the Internet. It\'s just sad sometimes. So you definitely try and stay away from it as much as possible.','Taylor Lautner','sad'),(7016,'However, we might oppose it, abortion is a sad feature of modern life.','Robert Casey','sad'),(7017,'You will soon find that I am a bit obsessive about my work. And that is a little sad, one often feels strangely restricted, not finding time to simmer, although one actually has many interests.','Arne Jacobsen','sad'),(7018,'Life can be challenging and sad... but music is the easy part.','St. Vincent','sad'),(7019,'What makes me sad about school is that the people who are unhappy are unhappy because they don\'t believe it will change. And I just want to say: \'It does! High school ends and it\'s over.\' I will tell anyone that it\'s OK to be unhappy at school, make lots of mistakes and then it will be over.','Alice Englert','sad'),(7020,'NASA has been one of the most successful public investments in motivating students to do well and achieve all they can achieve. It\'s sad that we are turning the programme in a direction where it will reduce the amount of motivation and stimulation it provides to young people.','Neil Armstrong','sad'),(7021,'If I don\'t make it, I\'ll be very sad that there are things I didn\'t do, but I\'m happy that I\'ve done what I have.','Stephen Jay Gould','sad'),(7022,'So many schools are getting rid of music programs and it\'s really sad because I know that when I started singing and stuff it was something that I always wanted to do and I never believed in myself to be able to do it.','Hilary Duff','sad'),(7023,'Well, you know, too much democracy is a sort of sad thing.','Ann Richards','sad'),(7024,'People are so codified - it\'s sad.','Jean Paul Gaultier','sad'),(7025,'Saturdays and Sundays, America in the year 2009 does not in some ways differ significantly from the country that existed almost 50 years ago. This is truly sad.','Eric Holder','sad'),(7026,'It\'s a sad fact about our culture that a poet can earn much more money writing or talking about his art than he can by practicing it.','W. H. Auden','sad'),(7027,'I think it is really sad that when people lose their homes they kind of lose their minds too.','Margaret Cho','sad'),(7028,'The \'80s were fabulous. The \'90s sucked, and the \'70s were just a sad, sad time in human history. Go 1980s! There\'s something that\'s just so cute about that time. And not just yellow nail polish and \'I\'m a loner.\'','Jennifer Sky','sad'),(7029,'I was sad that Corpse Bride was so short. I would\'ve liked to have had her around for way longer. She doesn\'t actually have that many scenes.','Helena Bonham Carter','sad'),(7030,'As a writer, or as a filmmaker, you have to present yourself, and part of what yourself is is what you\'re interested in, or what you think is funny, or what you think is sad, or what you think is horrible.','Charlie Kaufman','sad'),(7031,'You know, why at the end of your life should you assemble thousands of pages of \'Why am I so sad, why am I so depressed?\' Instead, assemble thousands of pages of why you\'re so content.','Elizabeth Gilbert','sad'),(7032,'As somebody who, in my second marriage, insisted on a prenuptial agreement, I can also testify that sometimes it is an act of love to chart the exit strategy before you enter the union, in order to make sure that not only you, but your partner as well, knows that there will be no World War III should hearts and minds, for any sad reason, change.','Elizabeth Gilbert','sad'),(7033,'It\'s sad that the most glorious of sexual experiences can make us feel guilty, ashamed, embarrassed, and abnormal.','Sue Johanson','sad'),(7034,'The funny thing is I\'m not bothered or sad about being on my own - after all I\'ve never had a husband.','Francesca Annis','sad'),(7035,'With my schedule being so crazy, I can\'t call every day or hang out with my friends like I used to and that\'s definitely sad.','Jordin Sparks','sad'),(7036,'My comedy is for children from three to 93. You do need a slightly childish sense of humour and if you haven\'t got that, it\'s very sad.','Norman Wisdom','sad'),(7037,'I remember a time when all my fans were crying and sad and going through hell. Now, we\'re trying to uplift each other and accept ourselves for who we are, even if nobody else does.','Mary J. Blige','sad'),(7038,'The attacks on the World Trade Center and the Pentagon shook our nation to the core. Americans were deeply frightened, sad, and angry, and they rallied around a President who, at the time, showed impressive certitude and calm.','Eliot Spitzer','sad'),(7039,'The sad duty of politics is to establish justice in a sinful world.','Reinhold Niebuhr','sad'),(7040,'Watergate provides a model case study of the interaction and powers of each of the branches of government. It also is a morality play with a sad and dramatic ending.','Bob Woodward','sad'),(7041,'I was at the Olympic Games winning medals and I still doubted my image. I doubted what I looked like. That\'s sad.','Shawn Johnson','sad'),(7042,'People say you should read your criticism because it will make you a better person but it doesn\'t. It just makes you a sad bitter old showbiz nightmare.','Jo Brand','sad'),(7043,'It is sad to see a woman sacrificing the ties of the affections even to do good.','Maria Mitchell','sad'),(7044,'My dad was a homicide cop in the gay neighborhood in the city when gay neighborhoods were desperate, depressing, sad places run by the mob. The only gay people he\'d met when I came out to him were corpses.','Dan Savage','sad'),(7045,'As a songwriter I hate this whole, \'If it\'s a sad song, it has to sound like a sad song thing.\' And that goes all the way back to my days with the Format. I\'m an insane narcissist, so if I have to get something off my chest, I\'ll get something off my chest.','Nate Ruess','sad'),(7046,'Well the country songs themselves are three-chord stories, ballads which are mostly sad. If you are already feeling sorry for yourself when you listen to them they will take you to an even sadder place.','Willie Nelson','sad'),(7047,'I do not take steroids. I never have. It\'s sad to me that people want to point fingers. I don\'t do that. That\'s not me. I wouldn\'t feel like a human being.','Jackie Joyner-Kersee','sad'),(7048,'I\'ve met so many fans of daytime television who\'ve watched the shows with their moms and grandmas and feel like they\'ve known the characters their whole lives. It\'s sad for them to have to say goodbye to their favorite soaps and characters. We don\'t want that to happen to the \'Days\' fans.','Alison Sweeney','sad'),(7049,'I\'m not sad at all about turning 40.','Halle Berry','sad'),(7050,'Morality comes with the sad wisdom of age, when the sense of curiosity has withered.','Graham Greene','sad'),(7051,'It\'s a sad indication of where Washington has come, where policy differences almost necessarily become questions of integrity. I came to Washington in the late \'70s, and people had the ability in the past to have intense policy differences but didn\'t feel the need to question the other person\'s character.','Eric Holder','sad'),(7052,'The sad thing about artificial intelligence is that it lacks artifice and therefore intelligence.','Jean Baudrillard','sad'),(7053,'You had to be into sport and, sad to say, I\'m a traitor to my country because I don\'t have a sporting bone in my body.','Geoffrey Rush','sad'),(7054,'Here in the United States, our profession is much maligned, people simply don\'t trust or like journalists anymore and that\'s sad.','Christiane Amanpour','sad'),(7055,'You know what I have noticed? And this is really sad. Flying first class is less scary than flying coach. They speak to you and they\'re so nice to you and they want to help you and they know you want a drink before the plane takes off. And they bring it to you without asking. If you\'re sitting in coach and hoping for a drink, good luck.','Hope Davis','sad'),(7056,'I\'ve never met a woman who thinks they\'ve got a good enough figure - however perfect they look - which is sad, because no one else can see these perceived flaws; they\'re entirely internal.','L\'Wren Scott','sad'),(7057,'Well in the end the world can crank itself up to sanctions, as it has with Zimbabwe, another sad case.','Helen Clark','sad'),(7058,'It\'s sad that people listen to music and decide how the singer should look.','Joss Stone','sad'),(7059,'Nowadays you really have to pump out that blockbuster in order to have the luxury of getting a body of work, and that\'s sad because the work suffers. Today everything is based on money. The older actors, they inspire me.','Dylan McDermott','sad'),(7060,'Everybody likes Johnny Cash. I think the sad part of it is his health is givin\' him problems.','Merle Haggard','sad'),(7061,'I love New York. I was sad, depressed and incredibly moved by our fellow countrymen and what they\'ve done. I wanted to give people a chance to see something funny, have a distraction.','Ben Stiller','sad'),(7062,'Because the sad fact is that the Enron Corporation and others manipulated with unfortunately great effect the energy market in the West Coast starting in 2000.','Jay Inslee','sad'),(7063,'Elaine is just in pain. I think Elaine has become very, very sad woman. She is someone who is in deep need of many hours of analysis and I like to think that I\'m not that type of person.','Julia Louis-Dreyfus','sad'),(7064,'It\'s sad when you can\'t make everyone happy, though. It\'s impossible but, at the same time, you still hope. You think, \'Maybe I can do it,\' but you know you can\'t. But gosh, if I had to rely on giving people what they wanted, I would have had to write 40 billion different books and even then, I wouldn\'t get it right.','Stephenie Meyer','sad'),(7065,'Wrap parties can be really sad, actually, disorienting.','Josh Lucas','sad'),(7066,'President Bush spent last night calling world leaders to support the war with Iraq and it is sad when the most powerful man on earth is yelling, \'I know you\'re there, pick up, pick up.','Craig Kilborn','sad'),(7067,'And for some reason, when I\'m sad, I do listen to Leonard Cohen, I do listen to Joni Mitchell. I do find myself going to the music that\'s actually reflecting my mood, as opposed to sticking on Motown, which might actually bring my mood up.','Glen Hansard','sad'),(7068,'The sad truth is that opportunity doesn\'t knock twice.','Gloria Estefan','sad'),(7069,'What\'s really sad is that so many young women between 